title: spicy appetizer franks
directions: Prepare spaghetti sauce mix, adding tomato sauce, water and salad oil as label directs.
Cut franks into bite size pieces or use cocktail.
Heat in sauce; serve with toothpicks.
Keep warm.

title: boiled cookies(an old school lunch recipe)
directions: Mix first 4 ingredients.
Place over low heat.
Boil for 2 minutes (boiling time only).
Remove from heat and add last 4 ingredients and mix thoroughly.
Drop at once on wax paper.

title: banana ice cream
directions: Heat milk in a large saucepan, bringing it almost to a boil. In a large bowl, beat egg yolks until light.
Add salt, stirring constantly.
Slowly pour about half of the milk over the eggs. When well blended, return entire mixture to saucepan.
Add sugar and cook over medium heat, stirring continuously, until mixture is thick enough to coat a spoon.

title: brown sugar pound cake
directions: Bake 1 hour at 350° in tube pan.

title: apple cake
directions: Beat together sugar, eggs and oil.
Sift together flour, salt, soda and cinnamon and add to first mix.
The batter will be heavy. After mixing, add the chopped apples and nuts.
Fold into mixture.
Pour into greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 45 to 50 minutes.

title: sugar cream pie
directions: Combine milk and butter in medium saucepan.
Cook over low heat until butter is melted.
Remove from heat.
Combine sugar and cornstarch in small bowl.
Gradually stir in 1 cup warm milk mixture, stirring constantly to avoid lumps.
Add cornstarch-milk mixture to remaining milk mixture in saucepan.
Cook over medium heat, stirring constantly until thickened.
Remove from heat; add vanilla.
Pour into pie shell.
Dot with butter and sprinkle with nutmeg.
Chill until firm.

title: grandma alzeta's fudge
directions: Mix sugar and cocoa.
Add milk and syrup until completely mixed.
Add salt and butter.
Stir frequently on low heat.
Cook mixture until it forms a hard ball in water.
Add vanilla and egg. Be sure to stir so not to become stringy.
Beat by hand 15 to 20 minutes.
Pour in buttered pan and refrigerate.

title: old fashioned pound cake
directions: Cream sugar, vanilla and shortening until fluffy.
Add eggs, alternately with flour.
Beat until well blended.

title: watermelon pie
directions: Prepare jello according to directions on box.
Cool 15 minutes in refrigerator.
Stir in whipped topping until smooth. Refrigerate for 10 minutes.
Spoon into crust and refrigerate for 4 hours or until firm.

title: poppy seed chicken
directions: Tear meat from boiled chicken breasts. Coat a casserole dish with nonstick spray. In a bowl, mix chicken, cream of chicken soup and sour cream. Crumble up about 1 cup of the Ritz crackers and stir into the mixture. Dump this mixture into the casserole dish and spread evenly. Crush remaining crackers and mix with melted butter. Spoon cracker mixture over chicken. Sprinkle the poppy seeds on top. Bake, uncovered, in a 350° oven for 30 minutes or until crackers are browned.

title: fast fudge pots de creme
directions: In a medium saucepan, stir together pudding mix and milk. Cook over medium heat, stirring constantly, until mixture comes to full boil; remove from heat.
Add chocolate chips; stir until chips are melted and mixture is smooth.
Spoon into creme pots or demitasse cups.
Press plastic wrap directly into surface.
Serve slightly warm or chilled.
Garnish as desired.
Makes 8 servings.

title: orange salad
directions: Combine all ingredients and chill.

title: king ranch casserole
directions: Saute onions and bell pepper.
Layer as follows:
tortilla on bottom, 1/2 chicken, 1/2 green pepper/onion, 1/2 cheese, 1/2 mixture of soups.
Repeat.
Cook at 300° to 350° for 40 minutes to 1 hour.

title: pizza casserole
directions: Prepare noodles according to package directions.
Slice pepperoni to taste.
Brown hamburger; drain.
Mix all ingredients together in a casserole dish.
Top with Mozzarella cheese.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: old time coleslaw(makes about 10 to 12 servings)
directions: In a large bowl, combine cabbage and onion; cover with sugar and let stand for a few minutes.
Meanwhile, in a medium saucepan, combine vinegar, oil, mustard, celery seed, salt and pepper; bring to a boil.
Pour over cabbage mixture and mix.
Let cool, then mix again.
Cover and store overnight in refrigerator.
Serve as a salad, relish or side dish.

title: hot rolls
directions: Mix yeast with a little of the sugar and dissolve in warm water. Set aside. Dissolve 1/2 cup shortening, sugar and salt in hot milk, then allow to cool. Add eggs to mixture, then add 1 cup flour and beat until mixture is smooth. Add yeast mixture and beat until blended. Continue to beat as you add flour, a little at a time, until dough is elastic and cleans easily from hands. Form into a smooth ball; brush with melted shortening and let rise until it is doubled in size. Form into walnut size balls.
Place 2 balls in each greased muffin cup in pan.
Let rise again until doubled in size. Bake at 450° for 15 or 20 minutes.
Brush with butter as soon as rolls are taken from the oven.

title: strawberry ice cream
directions: Crush strawberries in blender.
Mix 2 cups milk, sugar, condensed milk and eggs.
Pour into freezer.
Fill freezer container to fill line with whole milk.
Freeze.

title: italian cauliflower
directions: Separate cauliflower into flowerets.
Put into a saucepan containing a small amount of boiling salt water.
Cook, uncovered, for 5 minutes.
Cover and cook 8 to 10 minutes or until tender. Drain, if necessary, and keep hot.
Heat butter and garlic. Stir in flour and salt. Cook until bubbly. Add tomatoes and bring to boiling, stirring constantly. Cook 1 to 2 minutes.
Mix in green pepper and oregano.
Pour sauce over hot cauliflower.
Makes 6 servings.

title: peach cobbler
directions: Place peaches in a 9-inch baking pan.
Combine margarine, 1/2 cup sugar, milk, flour, baking powder, salt and vanilla in bowl, mixing well.
Spoon over peaches.
Pour mixture of 1 cup sugar and 1/2 cup water over the top of the batter.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Serve hot or cold.
Yields 6 servings.

title: pineapple cheese ball
directions: Mix together and form a ball.
Roll in 1/2 cup pecans, chopped.
Chill.
Serve with your favorite crackers.

title: barbecue pork chops
directions: Combine all ingredients except pork chops; simmer for 15 minutes. Arrange pork chops in baking dish; add barbecue sauce. Cook at 350° for 1 hour, or until tender. Serves 6.

title: thanksgiving squash
directions: Simmer squash, onion, salt and pepper until tender and drain well.
Mix well oleo, dry stuffing mix, sour cream, carrots, green pepper and mushrooms.
Add squash and mix together very well. Place in casserole dish and top with stuffing mix.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes (45 minutes at 325° if Corning Ware is used).

title: easy taco dip
directions: Mix ingredients until well blended; refrigerate.
Serve with assorted chips or vegetable dippers.
Makes 3 cups.

title: granddaddy's microwave roast
directions: Rub meat with meat tenderizer, steak seasoning, instant onion flakes, parsley flakes, Tony's seasoning, onion powder, garlic powder, basil and thyme.
Place roast, fat side down, in a casserole dish.
Mix sauce.

title: cheese wafers
directions: Mix all ingredients together and shape into small balls. Place on ungreased cookie sheet. Flatten ball with fork.
Bake at 350 degrees for approximately 20 minutes or until lightly browned.

title: kibby(national dish of syria)
directions: Drain water from wheat by cupping hands and squeezing out all moisture.
In large bowl, mix wheat, ground meat, onion, mint, salt and pepper; knead well.
You can pat in greased pan and score into diamond shapes.
Bake at 375° about 1/2 hour or brown.
Spoon butter before eating.

title: slow-cooked chunky beef stew
directions: Preheat the oven to 250°. Combine all ingredients except tomato juice and peas in a large roaster or Dutch oven. Stir well. Pour tomato juice over mixture. Cover and bake at 250° for 5 hours. Stir in peas and return to oven for 10 more minutes. Makes 6 servings.

title: mexican pizza crust
directions: Lightly spoon flour into measuring cup; level off.
Combine all ingredients in medium bowl.
Stir until blended, about 40 to 50 strokes.
Lightly grease bottom and sides of a 13 x 9-inch cookie sheet or 12-inch round pizza pan.
Spread dough out evenly on pan. Bake in 400° oven for 10 to 15 minutes after placing sauce and other pizza ingredients on it.

title: german chocolate cake
directions: Mix pecans and coconut in bottom of ungreased 9 x 13-inch pan. Mix cake milk by directions.
Mix cream cheese, butter and powdered sugar.
Spoon on top of cake mixture.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes.

title: corn-rice casserole
directions: Cook rice as directed on box and add salt and butter.
While still hot, grate in the pepper (don't get into the skin).
Add grated cheese and pepper.
Pour in milk to right consistency (not soupy).
Fold in corn.

title: strawberry margarita
directions: Can be reduced, if preferred. Mix in blender until ice is shaved. Serve in champagne glasses. Serves 4 to 6.

title: snowball cake
directions: Dissolve 4 tablespoons ice water with gelatine.
Add 1 cup boiling water.
Cool.
Combine pineapple, salt, sugar and lemon juice.
Pour into gelatine and let thicken a little.
Beat Dream Whip and fold half into gelatine mixture.
In a long pan put a layer of cake and a layer of gelatine, then a layer of cake and a layer of gelatine.
Top with rest of Dream Whip and coconut.

title: wheat germ bread
directions: In a large bowl, mix 1 1/2 cups flour, yeast, wheat germ and salt.
Add water, molasses, shortening and egg; mix again. Gradually stir in remaining flour to make a stiff dough.
Cover; let rise until double in bulk, about 1 hour.
Punch down dough. Place in greased 9-inch loaf pan or 2-quart casserole.
Cover and let rise about 45 minutes.
Bake at 375° for 35 to 50 minutes or until deep, golden brown.
Remove from pan and cool before slicing.

title: jezebel dip
directions: Mix well in blender and refrigerate overnight.
Mixture will appear
thin when blended, but will have a preserve like consistency after being refrigerated.
Keeps for a long period of time.
Serve over 8 ounce package of cream cheese with Ritz or similar
crackers.
May
also
serve
as
a dip for boiled shrimp.

title: king arthur flour pancake "mix"
directions: In a large bowl, combine the flours, wheat germ or bran, dry milk, salt, sugar and baking powder and mix well.
Cut in the shortening until it is evenly distributed.
(It is important to use shortening rather than butter, because it remains stable at room temperature.)

title: 3 bean salad
directions: Drain beans.
Pour into large bowl. Add remaining ingredients. Cover and chill several hours.

title: hot taco rice
directions: Chop up onion; add to ground beef.
Brown until done, then drain.
Stir in jar of salsa and chicken bouillon cube; let come to a boil.
Cover; cook on low heat for 30 minutes.
Serve over rice.

title: potato chowder
directions: Fry bacon bits until crisp and drain fat.
Combine all ingredients, except milk, in crock-pot.
Add water to cover.
Cook on high for 2 hours, then switch to low for 4 hours (automatic 5 hours).
Before serving, stir in milk and heat.
Serves 6.

title: cream puff pudding
directions: Bring to a boil the oleo and water.
Add at once to flour; beat in.
Let cool.
Add eggs; beat until smooth.
Put in greased cake pan.
Bake at 400° for 20 to 30 minutes.
Cool.

title: angel (date) pudding
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Put into a greased square pan. Bake 30 minutes at 375 degrees.
Serve with whipped cream or whipped topping.

title: baked sole fillets
directions: Sprinkle fish with salt, pepper and onion powder.
Place in baking dish.
Lightly squeeze lemon and lime over fish.
Roll fillets and secure with toothpicks.
Dice lemon, lime and orange. Sprinkle over fish.
Bake at 375° for 10 minutes or until fish flakes.
Serves 2.

title: marinated carrots
directions: Cook sliced carrots until tender-crisp.
Bring to a boil the tomato soup, oil, sugar, vinegar, onion, green pepper, Worcestershire sauce, mustard and salt.
Remove from heat and pour over drained and cooled carrots.
Let marinate at least 2 days before serving.
Will keep two weeks in refrigerator.

title: eggnog
directions: Beat egg and sugar.
Then beat in milk and flavoring of your choice.
Serve cold, sprinkled lightly with cinnamon and nutmeg.

title: coconut macaroons
directions: In medium-size bowl, combine all ingredients until well blended.
Drop by teaspoonfuls, about 1 inch apart, onto well-greased cookie sheet.
Bake in a moderate oven (350°) for 8 to 10 minutes, or until lightly browned.
Immediately remove from baking sheet.
Cool.

title: chocolate covered cherries
directions: Drain cherries on paper towels for 10 to 15 minutes.
Put cherries on a cookie sheet and freeze.
(Make sure the cherries are not touching each other, or you won't be able to separate them while frozen.)
While cherries are freezing, mix sugar, milk, and melted butter.
Shape into 1 inch balls.
Flatten one ball and wrap around a frozen cherry.
As cherries are wrapped, put back on cookie sheet.
Chill for several hours.
If you run out of cherries and have mixture left, you can make chocolate covered cream drops with the rest.
Yield:
100 to 120 Cherries.

title: orange delight salad
directions: Sprinkle the dry Jell-O just as it comes from the package, into the cottage cheese.
(Do not dissolve the Jell-O in water.) Stir well and set aside in the refrigerator for about 2 hours.

title: wheat brown bread
directions: Sift together in a large bowl the first 5 ingredients.
Stir in the eggs and buttermilk.
Blend well.
Oil a large (10 x 5-inch) loaf pan.
Pour batter in and bake about 1 hour at 350°. When done it will pull away from the sides and lift out easily. Cool on a rack.
Makes 1 (10 x 5-inch) loaf.

title: sensation salad dressing
directions: Mix all ingredients in quart jar with tight fitting lid. Shake to blend.
Store in refrigerator at least 24 hours before using.
Toss with salad greens, which have been salted.

title: pecan tarts
directions: Mix
margarine and cheese.
Add flour.	Roll into balls and chill
overnight.
Press
into small tart tins.
Sprinkle crushed pecans on bottom of each tart and add following, mixed together: brown
sugar, eggs, butter, vanilla and salt.
Bake at 350°
for 20 to 25 minutes, or until well-browned.
Makes 4 to 5 dozen tarts.

title: hamburger casserole
directions: Cook together the hamburgers, pepper and onion with the chili pepper and seasonings.
Combine with the tomatoes, corn and corn meal.
Pour into casserole and top with Spoon Bread made as follows.

title: hershey's syrup brownies
directions: Cream oleo and sugar.
Add eggs.
Sift flour and baking soda. Add vanilla to Hershey's syrup.
Blend all mixtures together.
Add chopped nuts, if desired.
Pour in greased and floured 9-inch pan. Bake 40 minutes at 350°.
Ice with any chocolate icing, store bought or homemade.

title: sutlac(rice pudding)
directions: Pour milk and sugar in a large saucepan and stir.
Put the pan on the stove on mid-high heat.
Add almonds, vanilla and egg. Blend the mixture at low speed.
Bring it to a boil and add the boiled rice and dissolved starch into the mixture slowly. Continue to heat the mixture for 2 to 3 minutes, until it is slightly thickened.
Remove the pan from heat.
Put the mix into small cups and serve cold.
Garnish with coconut if desired. Serves 10.

title: one pan curly-roni
directions: Brown beef and cook until almost done.
Add onion and garlic. Cook until onion is tender.
Stir in water, tomato sauce and seasonings.
Bring to boil.
Add curly-roni and return to boil. Remove from heat.
Stir in cheese until thickened.
Serve.
Makes 6 servings.

title: chocolate oatmeal pan cookies
directions: Mix together sugar, butter, milk and cocoa in a large cast-iron skillet on medium heat.
Let cook about 1 minute.
Remove from heat; add oats.
Spoon onto waxed paper; let cool.

title: strawberry bread(makes 2 loaves)
directions: Beat eggs and oil until fluffy.
Add strawberries and mix well. Combine flour, soda, salt, cinnamon and sugar and add to egg mixture, stirring until well blended.
Stir in chopped pecans. Pour batter into two greased and lightly floured 9 x 5-inch loaf pans.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour and 15 minutes or until a wooden pick inserted in center comes out clean.
Blend together cream cheese and strawberry jam and spread between two pieces of this bread to make delightful tea sandwiches.

title: marshmallow salad
directions: Soak gelatin in cold water or juice for 5 minutes.
Dissolve in boiling water.
Add salt, sugar, vinegar and lemon juice. Cool. When gelatin begins to thicken, add remaining ingredients (marshmallows, pineapple, nuts and mayonnaise mixed with cream cheese).
Let stand until firm.
Serve on lettuce.

title: potato salad
directions: Mix together first 4 ingredients in bowl.
In separate bowl, combine next 5 ingredients.
Add to potatoes; mix well.
The longer it sets in refrigerator, the better.

title: braunschweiger ball
directions: Put aluminum foil in large bowl and mix ingredients.
Put in refrigerator and cool for 1 hour.
Mix 1 large package Philadelphia cream cheese with a little milk and Worcestershire sauce.
Mix with beater until soft.
Remove foil from ball and coat with mixture. Halve olives and garnish on top of completed ball.

title: squash casserole
directions: Stir together all ingredients and bake 30 to 40 minutes at 375°.

title: rice pilaf
directions: Brown rice & onion in butter until brown, stirring frequently. Put rice in baking dish, pour bouillon over rice, stir; cover & foil. Bake at 350 for 30-35 minutes, fluff with fork, season to taste. Cook 10-15 minutes longer if necessary for correct consistency.

title: baked rice casserole
directions: Melt
margarine
in
frying
pan.
Add onion and saute. Add salt,
garlic
powder and oregano.	Add uncooked rice and chopped mushrooms (juice and all).	Simmer with lid on pan for 20 minutes. Stir every few minutes to keep from sticking.
Put in
a greased casserole dish and add beef consomme and 1/4 can of water.	Bake 1 hour at 400°.

title: chocolate icing
directions: Mix thoroughly.
May need to add a little more milk to get to spreading consistency.

title: zucchini, cheese casserole
directions: Saute zucchini and onions in oil.
Whip the cottage cheese with basil and oregano in blender.
Place layers of squash, cottage cheese and tomatoes in a 1 1/2-quart casserole.
Top with Parmesan cheese.
Bake, uncovered, for 25 or 30 minutes.
Yields 6 servings, 130 calories per serving.

title: easy hot dish
directions: In casserole dish, place ingredients in layers.
Salt and pepper to taste.
Cover and bake at 350° for 2 hours or until warm in center.

title: grape jelly
directions: Stir sugar into water.
Place on high heat, stirring constantly.
Bring to a full rolling boil that can't be stirred down.
Boil hard 1 minute.
Remove from heat.
Stir in Certo.
(Be sure to use Certo; do not substitute dry pectin!)
Add grape juice. Mix well.
If not thick enough, pour in a little more Certo.
Pour into 8 to 12 ounce glass jars (6 ounce or larger).

title: rhubarb upside-down cake
directions: Spread rhubarb in bottom of greased 9 x 13-inch cake pan.
Mix sugar and gelatin powder and pour over rhubarb, then marshmallows. Then pour white cake mix batter over top.
Bake 50 to 60 minutes at 350° until done.
Let stand several minutes before turning over so cake is not too runny.

title: bread sponge pudding
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Pour over bread dough rolled into little balls (approximate size of walnut) that have started to rise.
Bake 30 minutes at 350°.
Enjoy!!

title: zucchini bars
directions: Cream butter with sugars.
Add eggs, then stir in vanilla. Combine flour, baking powder, salt and cinnamon and stir into batter.
Stir in zucchini, coconut and nuts.
Spread in greased 12 x 9-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes.
Cut into bars.

title: jalapeno cornbread
directions: Cook the first 4 ingredients until limp, then make cornbread mixture.

In greased 9 x 13 x 2-inch baking dish, layer 1/2 of the cornbread mix, then half meat mixture, layer 2 cups cheese over the beef layer, then make the top layer of the other half of cornbread mixture.
Bake 30 minutes in a 350° oven or until cornbread is brown on top.

title: egg noodles
directions: Beat eggs and add cold water.
Add flour, salt and baking powder.
Roll thin and place up to dry.
Roll again and slice fine.
Put in boiling broth and cook 15 minutes, slowly.

title: apple butter oatmeal bars
directions: Mix flour, soda and salt.
Add sugar and oats.
Add melted margarine.
Blend well. Press 1/2 of mixture firmly into greased (12 x 8 x 2-inch) pan.
Spread apple butter, then cover with remaining oat mixture.
Pat lightly.
Bake at 350° for 45 to 55 minutes.
Cool and cut into bars.

title: wild peanut butter dip
directions: With steel blade, blend peanuts until smooth.
Add remaining ingredients, process until smooth.
Serve with crackers.

title: white chocolate fudge
directions: Mix milk, syrup, and margarine and melt slightly.
Remove from heat and add sugar until it's dissolved.
Put back on stove and bring to rolling boil.
Cook over medium heat 8 minutes, stirring constantly.
Remove from heat and stir in vanilla chips. Add vanilla.
Add marshmallow cream.
Stir until blended.
Mix in nuts.
Pour into ungreased pan.
Cool to set before cutting.

title: peanut butter cups
directions: Melt butter, sugar and peanut butter in double boiler. Mixture will be thick.
You can add 1 teaspoon of milk if needed. Spread into 9 x 13-inch pan.
Melt candy bars in double boiler and spread over peanut butter mixture.
Place in a cool, dry place until hard, then cut into squares.

title: raspberry cream cheese muffins
directions: In small bowl combine raspberries, 2 tablespoons fruit sweetener and 1/4 cup Ricotta cheese.
Set aside.

title: sweet and sour meatballs
directions: Combine first 2 ingredients mixing well.
Shape into 1 inch balls.
Cook in a large skillet over medium heat until browned. Drain.
Combine remaining ingredients except pineapple and mix well.
Pour over meatballs.
Simmer 10 minutes, stirring occasionally.
Add pineapple chunks and simmer 10 minutes more, stirring often.
Makes about 3 1/2 dozen.

title: t m i academy's peanut butter cookies
directions: Combine shortening, salt, soda and peanut butter. Add sugar and brown sugar. Cream together thoroughly.
Add beaten eggs, mixing well. Blend in flour. Drop from teaspoon on baking sheet. Press with fork.
Bake at 350° until brown.

title: nutty tuna salad
directions: Combine tuna, egg, pickles and nuts in a bowl.
In a separate bowl combine onion, mayonnaise, juice and mustard.
Season with salt and pepper.
Combine all together.
Serve as sandwich on whole grain bread or serve the salad with whole grain crackers over lettuce, or stuffed in tomato.

title: broccoli and cheez whiz casserole
directions: Cook butter, celery and onion in a saute pan until celery is almost tender.
Mix all ingredients together and cook in a casserole dish for 20 - 30 minutes at 350 degrees.

title: mexican cheese sauce
directions: Melt cheese and blend in tomatoes and chilies. Mix well and add hamburger. Cool. You can melt cheese in Microwave. Serve with tortilla chips.

title: sheet cake
directions: Mix oleo, cocoa, Crisco and water.
Bring to a boil.
Pour over mixture of sugar and flour.
Mix well, then add buttermilk, eggs, soda, vanilla and cinnamon.
Mix well.
Pour into greased jelly roll pan 16 x 11 1/2-inch.
Bake 20 minutes at 400°.

title: easy german potato salad
directions: Fry bacon until crisp. Set aside.

title: ham fingers
directions: Mix ham, cheese, mayonnaise and mustard together.
Spread 10 slices of bread with margarine and 10 slices of bread with mixture. Put together.
Trim crust and cut each sandwich in 3 "fingers". Cover with plastic wrap or aluminum foil.
Chill until needed.

title: deep dish peach pie
directions: Roll pastry to cover sides and bottom of a 3-inch deep quart casserole.
Put peaches in. Add sugar and brandy.
Cover with pastry; slash.
Bake at 450° for 10 minutes; reduce to 350°. Dredge with confectioners sugar and bake 5 minutes more.
Yields 6 servings.

title: chocolate sweetmeats
directions: Melt chocolate over low heat.
Beat egg slightly, then gradually beat the sugar into the egg.
When thoroughly mixed, stir egg mixture into the melted chocolate and cook over boiling water 3 minutes.
This makes a very thick, smooth mixture when beaten hard.
When smooth, stir in the slivered almonds.
Shape into a roll; wrap in waxed paper and chill in the refrigerator a full hour.
Makes 20 slices.

title: meat and cheese dip
directions: Brown beef and sausage in skillet with seasoning.

title: peanut butter fudge
directions: Place can of cream, confectioners sugar and stick of margarine in kettle.
Bring to a boil, stirring constantly.
Boil on medium heat until soft ball stage (about 8 minutes).
Take off heat and add vanilla, Marshmallow Creme and peanut butter.
Beat until well mixed.
Pour into buttered pan.

title: marinated vegetable salad
directions: Bring all ingredients to a boil in a large skillet or pan at medium heat, stirring occasionally.
Reduce heat to low and simmer 5 minutes.
(If you use Sweet 'N Low or Equal, etc., add after mixture has been heated.)
Refrigerate at least 24 hours.
Serve cold.

title: beef stew
directions: Place all ingredients in a deep pan and bake at 350° for 2 hours.
Then add the bag of mixed vegetables and bake for 1 additional hour.
An alternative way to cook is to place all of the listed ingredients in a crock-pot and cook from 5 to 8 hours.

title: stuffed rice tomatoes
directions: Wash and remove stems from stem end of tomatoes.
Take out seeds and pulp.
Sprinkle inside of tomatoes with salt or sugar, if no onion is desired.
Cook onion in butter until brown.
Add rice and tomatoes from which the water has been drained.
Salt and pepper.
Heat thoroughly.
Refill tomatoes with mixture.
Cover with buttered bread crumbs.
Bake 10 to 15 minutes in moderate oven.

title: quick hot rolls
directions: Mix all ingredients together in a large mixing bowl.
Pour into a 12-inch muffin pan.
Bake for 10 minutes at 450°.

title: tuna nunu
directions: Cook macaroni.
Put in large bowl and combine flaked tuna, peas, cream of chicken soup and croutons. Stir and put in casserole pan. Bake for 25 to 30 minutes in a 350° oven.

title: chocolate mousse
directions: Warm chocolate liqueur in small saucepan.
Cut up bar of chocolate into small pieces into blender.
Cut up butter and place in blender.
Pour heated liqueur into blender.
Mix contents thoroughly.
In separate large mixing bowl, stiffen egg whites and gradually add confectioners sugar until mixture is stiff. Place egg yolks in blender; mix.
Put chocolate mixture from blender into bowl with egg whites. With a spatula, fold chocolate mixture until completely blended with egg whites.
Put bowl in refrigerator and chill 4 to 6 hours. Remove and serve.

title: shrimp with cabbage
directions: Clean the shrimp well.
Take out the veins and wash in salt water.
Put a spoonful of grease or butter to saucepan.
Add shrimp, cabbage, onion and tomatoes.
Cover and simmer for 30 to 40 minutes.

title: westerner cake
directions: Have eggs and butter at room temperature.
Cream butter; add brown sugar and beat until fluffy.
Add eggs 1 at a time; beat well after each addition.
Sift flour; add gradually to batter. Add lemon juice and vanilla; mix well.
Bake in 10-inch greased and floured tube pan at 325° for about 1 hour.
Cool 4 minutes, then invert pan.
I use confectioners sugar instead of brown sugar.

title: italian chicken
directions: Sprinkle chicken with salt.
Brown slowly in skillet in hot oil.
Combine spaghetti sauce mix, tomato sauce and water.
Pour over chicken.
Cover and simmer 35 minutes until tender.
Add mushrooms the last 15 minutes of cooking.

title: curried shrimp
directions: Cook onion and bell pepper in butter or oil until tender. Blend in flour and seasonings.
Add milk gradually and cook until thick, stirring constantly.
Add cooked shrimp and heat until bubbly.
Serve over cooked rice or pasta.
Serves 4.

title: vegetable chowder
directions: Cook onion, celery and green pepper in butter or margarine for 5 minutes.
Add potatoes, water or stock and seasonings.
Cover and simmer until potatoes are tender, about 20 minutes.
Add corn and beans.
Cover and simmer 10 minutes longer or until beans are tender.
Mix flour with small amount of milk; add to remaining milk.
Stir into cooked vegetable mixture.
Cook, stirring constantly until slightly thickened.

title: garden pasta salad
directions: Cook, rinse, drain and cool pasta; place in bowl with other ingredients.

title: grits casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients well.
Bake in greased casserole for 1 hour at 325°.

title: rainbow punch
directions: Combine juices in punch bowl. Add scoops of sherbet. Pour ginger ale over sherbet. Makes about 25 small servings.

title: banana muffins
directions: Combine dry ingredients - flour, oat bran, wheat bran, raisins and brown sugar.
Mash bananas.
Beat egg; add milk.
Add dry ingredients.
Mix only until blended.
Fill greased muffin tins 2/3 full.
Bake at 400° for 15 minutes.
Makes 12 muffins.

title: george washington salad
directions: Mix jello in water; add undrained pineapple and pie filling. Pour into a 9 x 12 x 2-inch dish.
Let set.

title: corn casserole
directions: Drain corn and reserve 1/4 cup of liquid.
Mix everything, except cheese, together and pour into greased or Pam sprayed pan. Bake at 350° for 15 minutes.
Sprinkle cheese on top and bake 30 to 40 minutes longer, until set.

title: lime congealed salad
directions: Drain crushed pineapple and measure juice.
Pour pineapple juice, plus enough water to equal 2 cups liquid, into a saucepan. Add cream cheese and marshmallows.
Heat, stirring occasionally, until cheese and marshmallows melt.
Add to jello 2 cups of boiling water.
Add cheese, marshmallows and pineapple juice mixture to the jello mixture.
Place in refrigerator.

title: mom's easy rolls
directions: Combine together and spoon into greased muffin pan.
Bake at 350° until brown.

title: mandarin salad
directions: Mix Eagle Brand milk and lemon juice. Add Cool Whip to this mixture. Gently mix in oranges and pineapple. Refrigerate overnight before serving to allow flavors to blend.

title: strawberry gelatin salad
directions: Mix in a large bowl everything but sour cream.
Put half of mixture in long Pyrex dish, congeal 15 minutes.
Stir in sour cream until soupy.
Spread over mixture, then add remainder of jello mixture.
Refrigerate.

title: shrimp dip
directions: Beat together and add enough mayonnaise for right consistency.

title: meat-cheese roll
directions: Combine beef, egg, bread crumbs, onion, 1/3 cup tomato sauce, salt and pepper.
Mix well and pat into a flat rectangle, about 10 x 12-inches, on a piece of wax paper.
Sprinkle cheese evenly over meat mixture.

title: lemon meringue pie
directions: Mix cornstarch,
cup
of
sugar and salt; slowly add water. Stir
regularly
over boiling water until thick enough to mound slightly (should turn clear), about 10 minutes.
Beat egg yolks and
cup
of
sugar, then stir into hot mixture a little
at
a time.
Cook
minutes,
stirring
constantly. Remove from heat;
add margarine, lemon rind and juice.
Cool to room temperature.
Turn into pie shell.

title: cookie cheese cake
directions: Mix the first 3 ingredients well.
Pat evenly in lightly greased 9 x 13-inch pan. Sprinkle with the nuts.
Mix the eggs, cream cheese and powdered sugar well and top cake.
Bake at 300° until brown.

title: apricot salad
directions: Dissolve both gelatins in 3 cups juice from cans of pineapple and apricots. Cool.
Mash apricots (blender or automatic mixer). Mix with pineapple and sour cream.
Add to cool gelatin.
Mix and pour into mold or molds. Serves 24.

title: turkey burgers
directions: Lightly spray rack of broiler pan with cooking spray.
In medium bowl, combine turkey, oats, onion, red pepper, zucchini, ketchup, garlic and salt, mixing lightly but thoroughly.
Shape into 6 (1/2-inch) thick patties.
Broil patties 7 to 9 minutes on each side or until golden brown and no longer pink in center. Serve on buns with one tablespoon sour cream, lettuce and tomato. Makes 6.

title: easy tamale casserole
directions: Spray a 13 x 9-inch glass baking dish with no-stick cooking spray.
Put crushed tortilla chips in bottom of dish (generous amount).
Take paper off tamales and place on chips.
Heat chili in pan just slightly.
Pour over all.
Top with cheese.
Bake at 350° for about 25 to 30 minutes, until heated through and cheese melts.

title: baked beans and hot dogs
directions: Heat together until flavors blend.

title: tiny's meat loaf
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Pack in pan.
Bake at 350° until done.

title: stephanie's sweet potato bake
directions: Bake sweet potatoes until done.
Peel and mash.
Add sugar, butter, spices and salt.
Add enough milk to moisten.
Pour into buttered 1 1/2-quart casserole dish.

title: tortellini-vegetable kabobs
directions: Combine first 8 ingredients in a saucepan; gradually stir in water and vinegar.
Bring to a boil; cook 30 seconds, stirring with a wire whisk.
Remove from heat and let cool.
Cut 6 artichoke hearts into quarters; reserve remaining artichokes for another use.
(I do them all.)
Alternate tortellini, cherry tomatoes and artichokes on 24 (6-inch) skewers; place in a 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking dish.
Pour cider vinegar mixture over kabobs, turning to coat.
Cover and marinate
in refrigerator 4 hours, turning occasionally.
(I put them in a square Tupperware container with a good seal and just turn them upside down and upright again.)
Drain and place on a serving platter.
Yield:
24 appetizers.

title: hutspot
directions: Peel carrots and potatoes.
Cut them and cook them together. In the last 10 minutes of the cooking time, add the peeled and sliced onions and cook them also.
When everything is tender, put it in a strainer and let it drain.
Mash everything together and serve.

title: green tomato pickles
directions: Slice tomatoes and onions, and sprinkle with salt.
Let stand overnight.
Drain, rinse with cold water and drain again.

title: cream cheese pound cake
directions: Beat at high speed the cream cheese and butter until fluffy. Add sugar, eggs, vanilla and lemon.
Beat until fluffy at high speed.
Add flour slowly, then beat at high speed for 8 minutes. Bake in tube pan for 1 1/2 hours at 350°.

title: sweet cream pound cake
directions: Beat egg whites and add sugar.
Put in refrigerator.
Cream butter.
Add sugar and egg yolks.
Add flour and milk.
Fold in egg whites.
Bake in tube pan at 350° for 1 1/2 hours.

title: chocolate eclair pie
directions: Spray a 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan with cooking spray. Layer bottom with graham crackers. In mixing bowl, pour pudding mix and 3 cups of milk. Beat for 1 minute until it starts to thicken. Fold in container of Cool Whip until smooth. Spread evenly over graham crackers. Add another layer of graham crackers over pudding mixture. Take container of chocolate frosting and put in mixing bowl. Mix 2 tablespoons of milk in and mix well. Spread on top layer. Refrigerate overnight.

title: vegetable pizza
directions: Spread out rolls on a large cookie sheet.
Bake according to package directions.
Mix sour cream, dressing mix, mayonnaise and cream cheese, using mixer to blend well.
Spread onto cooled crust and top with veggies (about 1 1/2 cups of 4 kinds).
Suggestions are broccoli, green peppers, cauliflower, tomatoes, carrots, celery, bacon bits, olives, pepperoni, etc.
Top with cheese and pat down firmly so that when serving, it does not fall apart when picked up.

title: *cinnamon apples
directions: Let sugar and water come to a boil.
Add sliced lemon.
Add quartered apples.
Boil for 5 minutes.
Take apples and lemon out. Cook juice until it jells, then add apples and lemon.
Sprinkle with cinnamon.

title: whatcom visiting nurse sugar cookies
directions: Cream butter, powdered sugar, extracts.
Beat in egg. In separate bowl, combine flour, soda, cream of tartar and salt. Gradually add to creamed mixture.
Chill well.
Roll out and cut in shapes.
Place on ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake at 375 F for 6-8 minutes or until very lightly brown. (They burn easily).

title: hot meat dip
directions: Brown meat. Put soup, tomatoes and cheese in crock-pot.
Add meat.
Melt cheese and keep hot. Serve with chips.

title: macaroni and cheese
directions: Mix macaroni, cottage cheese and Cheddar cheese.
Pour into a greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Pour boiling water over top and mix well.
Bake at 350° for 45 to 55 minutes.

title: microwave custard
directions: Measure milk.
Cook uncovered at High for 4 minutes.

Combine with beaten eggs, sugar and vanilla in bowl, adding gradually. Pour into 4 (1/2 cup) custard bowls. and sprinkle with nutmeg. Place cups into glass baking dish with 1 inch hot water in dish. Microwave uncovered 10 minutes and cool.

title: hanky-panks
directions: Cook ground beef and sausage together; season to taste.
Drain fat.
Stir in cheese cubes and microwave a few minutes, stirring every 30 seconds to melt.
Place spoonfuls onto rye bread which has been placed on cookie sheets and bake approximately 8 to 10 minutes at 350°.

title: quick 'n easy cookie bars
directions: Thoroughly combine cracker crumbs, flour and baking soda; set aside.
Combine melted margarine and brown sugar; stir in eggs, water and vanilla.
Gradually add flour mixture; mix well.
Stir in 1 cup chocolate chips and nuts.
Spread evenly in a greased 13 x 9-inch baking pan.
Bake at 375° for about 16 to 18 minutes or until lightly browned; remove from oven.
Immediately sprinkle remaining 1 cup chocolate chips over warm surface.
Let stand until chips soften; spread evenly.
Cool completely; cut into bars.
Makes 24 (2-inch) bars.

title: broccoli cornbread
directions: Melt oleo
in
9 x 13-inch pan.
Add the other ingredients. Mix
well (dough will be stiff).
Bake in 375° oven for 45 minutes.
Delicious.
Time	of
preparation:
15 minutes + baking time.
Serves 12.

title: apple bread
directions: Grease and flour three 7 1/2 x 3 1/2 x 2-inch or two 8 x 4 x 2-inch loaf pans; set aside.
Combine flour, soda, salt, cinnamon and baking powder; set aside.
Combine eggs, apple, sugar, oil and vanilla.
Stir in flour mixture just until moistened.
Pour into prepared pans.
Bake in a 325° oven 45 to 55 minutes or until toothpick comes out clean.
Cool 10 minutes.
Remove from pans. Cool. Wrap; store overnight before slicing.
Yield: 30 slices.

title: chocolate pie
directions: Mix all ingredients in large saucepan.
Bring to a heavy boil and pour into a graham cracker crust.
Top with meringue.

title: earthquake cake
directions: Grease a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Sprinkle nuts on bottom.
Put coconut on top of nuts.
Pour prepared cake mix over this.
Melt oleo and cream cheese together.
Add confectioners sugar and mix. Pour over cake batter.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.
Cool and cut into squares.

title: cornbread pie
directions: Brown meat and onions; add other ingredients.
Cook 15 minutes.
Pour into baking dish and top with a mixture of 3/4 cup cornmeal and 3/4 cup milk.
Bake for 1 hour at 350°.

title: fallen fudge cake
directions: Mix cocoa and sugar; add margarine.
Mix well.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating after each addition.
Add remaining ingredients.
Pour batter into oblong pan.
Place in a 350° oven. After cake has baked for 10 minutes, remove from oven and shake until it falls.
Repeat this as cake rises two more times.
Top with favorite chocolate frosting while cake is still in pan.

title: chocolate pecan pie(blue ribbon winner at georgia state fair)
directions: Turn on broiler.
Spread chocolate chips in pie crust.
Place under broiler for about 1 minute, just long enough to soften chips.
Remove from oven; spread chocolate chips evenly around crust to coat.
Place aside.
Change oven to preheat at 350°.

title: christmas lizzies
directions: Cream butter and sugar.
Add eggs; mix.
Put 1 cup of sifted flour over nuts and raisins.
Sift 2 cups of flour and spices together.
Add soda, milk and cooking wine (or grape juice) to sugar mixture.
Add flour and spices, then add candied fruit.
Add nuts and raisins; mix well.
Bake on a greased cookie sheet at 325° for 25 minutes (drop by teaspoonful).
Mixture doesn't spread, so can be baked close together.
Makes 10 dozen.

title: scalloped potatoes
directions: Stir soup until smooth.
Add milk and pepper.
In buttered 1 1/2-quart casserole, alternate layers of potatoes, onion, sauce and cheese.
Dot with butter and paprika.
Cover and bake at 375° for 1 hour.
Uncover and bake 15 minutes.
Serves 6.

title: sue's cheese balls
directions: Mix grated cheese and cream cheese with mayonnaise, horseradish, Worcestershire and onion.
Sprinkle garlic powder over mixture.
Mix and roll into 2 balls.
Roll in chopped nuts and chill.
Will serve about 40 people on Triscuits or Ritz.

title: miss muffet's salad
directions: Fold the gelatin into the whipped topping.
Add other ingredients into this mixture and fold.
Chill.
Garnish with fruit.

title: fudge cake
directions: Sift flour, soda and salt.
Add brown sugar, shortening, buttermilk and vanilla.
Beat for 2 minutes. Add eggs and melted chocolate and beat for another 2 minutes.
Pour into two 9-inch pans (be sure to use big pans) and bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.

title: big sandwich
directions: Slice bread across into 3 pieces.
Butter one layer.
Add ham, Swiss cheese, tomato and lettuce.
Mayonnaise the bottom layer with turkey and American or Cheddar cheese.
Stack layers.
Cut into wedges and serve.
Makes 8 servings.

title: sweet potato casserole
directions: Wash sweet potatoes and cut into thirds.
Boil until tender. Drain, cool, peel and mash.
Add melted butter, raisins and cinnamon.
(If not sweet enough for your taste, some honey may be added.)
Bake, uncovered, for 45 minutes at 350°.

title: parmesan chicken
directions: Dip chicken in melted margarine, then roll in bread crumbs and cheese mixture. Place in any baking pan (no lid).
Drizzle remaining margarine over chicken. Bake in preheated 350° oven for 1 hour. Serves 4 to 6.

title: fried ice cream
directions: Mix all ingredients except ice cream.
Use a fork to mix. Put the mix on a cookie sheet spread it out.
Set oven on about 350°. Put cookie sheet in the oven for about 3 to 5 minutes or until it bubbles.
Take it out of oven, put part of the mix on the bottom of a 9 x 13 inch pan.
Then take the half gallon of ice cream, cut it into slices and put it on top of the mix; spread it even.
Put the rest of the mix on top.
Put it in the freezer. Best if in freezer for at least 1 hour.
Enjoy.

title: a. j. bumps carrot casserole
directions: Boil onion and carrots.
When carrots are soft, drain; save the carrot water.
Mash carrots.
Add butter, salt, pepper, soda crackers (crushed in your hand) and at least 2/3 cup of the carrot water.
Stir.
Put in baking dish.
Add cheese on top.
Bake at 350° for 15 minutes.
Serves 4.

title: mom's fresh apple cake
directions: This cake must be mixed by hand.

title: banana pudding
directions: Line 9 x 13-inch pan or dish with vanilla wafers and sliced bananas.
In a separate bowl, combine 1 large package of instant vanilla pudding and 3 cups milk.
Add one can Eagle Brand condensed milk and Cool Whip.
Pour over vanilla wafers and bananas.
Chill 3 hours or more.

title: shrimp ball dip
directions: Dissolve gelatin in water.
Set aside.
Flake shrimp with a fork until crumb like.
Add cream cheese, mayo, celery, and onions. Set aside. Heat soup until warm, then add gelatin into soup until dissolved.
Add soup to shrimp mixture.
Store in refrigerator for at least 6 hours prior to serving (can be made the night before also).

title: easy chicking-n-dumplings
directions: Cook dumplings in salt water until tender, using just enough water to cover.
Do not drain.
Add chicken, margarine and broth. Bring to a boil; cover.
Reduce heat and simmer for about 45 minutes.
Add salt and pepper to taste.

title: baked pork chops
directions: Mix in Pyrex baking dish.
Place pork chops on top of rice and vegetables.
Bake 1 hour at 350° (until rice is cooked).

title: earthquake cake
directions: Spray or grease 9x13 pan. Spread with pecans & coconut. Prepare cake mix according to instructions. Pour over nuts & coconut. Melt oleo and cream cheese. Beat in powdered sugar. Spoon over cake batter. Bake 45-50 minutes at 350°.
Very Good!

title: cucumber salad
directions: Dissolve jello in boiling water. Set aside until party congealed.
Mix other ingredients together and fold into jello. Refrigerate until firm.

title: chocolate syrup cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease a 13 x 9-inch pan.
Beat butter and sugar until light.
Beat in eggs and syrup, then flour.
Pour into pan.
Bake for 25 minutes.
Cool completely, then frost.

title: party mix
directions: Melt margarine in microwave, add salt and sauce, may add a few shakes of garlic salt, if desired.
Add cereal and pretzels and stir well.
Microwave 6 minutes, stirring good every 2 minutes. Spread on paper towel to cool.
Store airtight.

title: custard pie
directions: Beat eggs; add sugar, salt, vanilla and almond extract.
Mix well; add milk and mix.
Bake in 1 1/2-quart casserole or pie crust.
Before baking, sprinkle with nutmeg.
Bake until knife comes out clean.

title: german slaw
directions: Chop cabbage and onion.
Add 1 cup sugar and let sit while making dressing.
Mix vinegar, oil, celery seed, salt, dried mustard and 1 tablespoon sugar.
Bring to a boil and pour over cabbage while hot.
It is better next day.

title: pistachio nut salad
directions: Mix all ingredients together and chill overnight or for a few hours.

title: sweet pickles
directions: Pack cucumbers tightly in a gallon glass jar with metal lid. Put salt, alum and pickling spice over cucumbers.
Fill jar with vinegar.
Seal.
Wait at least 3 months before using.

title: shipwreck
directions: Peel and slice potatoes.
Place half of slices in a greased 2-quart casserole.
Add ground meat, salt, pepper, kidney beans and onions.
Arrange remaining potatoes on top.
Combine tomatoes and water and spoon over all.
Cover and bake at 350° for 1 1/2 hours.

title: big batch tomato sauce
directions: In 8-quart Dutch oven, over medium heat in hot oil, cook onion, carrots, green peppers and garlic until tender.
Add tomatoes and remaining ingredients.
Over high heat, heat to boiling.
Reduce heat to medium-low and cook 2 hours, stirring occasionally.
Freeze and use up to 1 year.

title: lemon delight
directions: Soak gelatine in cold water.
Boil together slightly beaten egg yolks, sugar, lemon juice and rinds.
Stir constantly and boil until mixture coats spoon.
Add gelatine and stir until dissolved. Cool until set.
Beat egg whites stiff; add sugar gradually. Beat until sugar is blended and egg whites form peaks.
Carefully fold mixture into gelatine mixture.
Break angel food cake into bite size pieces.
Layer in Pyrex cake pan; pour the lemon mixture over the cake to cover.
Chill several hours or overnight.
Top with whipped topping.

title: turkey tetrazzini
directions: *Also may use shrimp.

title: peanut butter fudge
directions: Butter sides and bottom of a large Dutch oven, leaving excess butter in pan.

Add sugar and evaporated milk, stirring well. Bring mixture to a boil over medium heat, stirring occasionally. Cook, stirring constantly, until mixture reaches soft ball stage or a candy thermometer registers 234°.
Remove from heat; add peanut butter and marshmallow cream, beating with a wooden spoon until blended.
Pour into a buttered 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking pan or dish; cool.

title: bran muffins
directions: In large bowl, mix Raisin Bran, oil and sugar.
Mix the following and add to the Raisin Bran mix:
eggs, flour, buttermilk, baking soda and salt.
Do not stir.
Put in covered container; will keep for 6 weeks.
Do not stir after it's been refrigerated, just spoon out into muffin tins.
Bake at 400° for 15 to 20 minutes.

title: pickled green tomato relish
directions: In a large pot, bring salt, sugar and vinegar to a rolling boil.
Add vegetables and cook only until onions are barely limp. Place into clean, hot jars and seal.

title: york town stew
directions: Brown beef and drain.
Stir in vegetables and simmer 1 hour. Great with corn bread.

title: bavarian chocolate pie
directions: Prepare pie shell; cool.
In saucepan, sprinkle gelatin over 1 cup milk; let stand 2 minutes to soften.
Combine sugar and cocoa; add to mixture in saucepan.
Cook over low heat, stirring constantly, until mixture boils.
Remove from heat; add butter and stir until melted.
Blend in remaining 2/3 cup milk and vanilla. Cool.
Chill until mixture begins to set, stirring.
Beat cream until stiff; carefully fold into chocolate mixture.
Pour into pie shell.
Chill until set.

title: cabbage casserole
directions: Grease a casserole dish.
Put cabbage in bottom.
Brown meat and onions; add rice and stir.
Add beef mixture to cabbage on top; add tomatoes.
Use as many as you like.
I also use tomato sauce.
Bake in a 350° oven for 1 to 1 1/2 hours.
Cover before baking.

title: corned beef dip
directions: Boil water with bouillon cubes; add jello and dissolve.
Set aside.
Mix all ingredients, stirring well.
Pour into mold or ring pan.
Refrigerate until jelled.
Great dip on crackers or chips.

title: heavenly cheese cake
directions: Melt the oleo and in a bowl, put the crumbs and melted oleo. Mix them good together, then press the mixture evenly over the bottom of an ungreased 10-inch spring-form pan (with the band in place).
Bake in a preheated oven at 350° until lightly browned about 10 minutes.
Set aside.
Now set oven on 375°.
In a medium bowl, with an electric mixer, beat the eggs slightly; add the sugar and beat on high speed until thickened and lemon-color; set aside.
Without washing the beaters, in a large bowl beat the cream cheese at medium speed until fluffy.
Gradually beat in the egg mixture until smooth.
Pour over the baked crumb mix in the spring-form pan.
Bake on the middle rack of the oven at 375° for 30 minutes.
Remove from oven.
You can put a topping of any kind of fruit.

title: berry pecan tart
directions: Preheat oven to 325°.
Combine first four ingredients and spread over bottom of tart shell pan.
Bake 10 to 12 minutes until lightly brown.
Remove and cool.
Mix cream cheese, 1/2 cup sugar and vanilla and spread over cooled tart shell.
Place berries and nuts over cream cheese mixture.
In a small saucepan, heat the cranberry juice, cornstarch, lemon juice, 1/2 cup sugar and jam. Cook over low heat about 2 minutes.
Mixture will thicken.
Remove from heat and allow to cool to room temperature.
Pour over the fruit and chill tart before serving.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Boil
chicken until done and cut into bite-size pieces. Place in	buttered
casserole
dish.
Mix together soup, sour cream and celery salt.
Pour over chicken.
Crush crackers and spread
over top.
Pour margarine over this.
Bake at 325° for 45 minutes.

title: bread dressing
directions: Combine seasoning from Stove Top with 2 cups water and 1 stick of margarine.
Boil for 5 minutes.
Add onion; boil covered on low heat for 5 more minutes.
Remove from heat.
Add stuffing packet and 8 slices of bread, toasted and crumbled into small pieces.
Add 3 boiled eggs, diced small; stir and add warm water until dressing is moist.
(May use 1 cup of chicken broth with the warm water.) Mix in cream of chicken soup.
Put half of dressing in a large baking dish.
Place chicken pieces on top of the dressing, then put the last half of the dressing on top of the chicken.
Add several thin slices of margarine on top.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour or until golden brown.

title: homemade stew
directions: Open all of the cans; put them in one cooker on low.
Put the roast beef on high in the oven for 20 minutes at 350° to 400°. Mix all together; cook at a boil for about 30 minutes on high. Add cheese if you wish when it begins to boil.

title: neiman-marcus cake
directions: Mix together cake mix, oleo, eggs, pecans and coconut.
Pour into 9 x 13-inch greased and floured pan.
Mix powdered sugar, vanilla and cream cheese.
Put on top of first layer.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Serve cold.
Keep refrigerated.

title: chicken wings
directions: Use a large boiler with a lid.
Brown wings in oil.
Place hot sauce, margarine and lemon juice in boiler.
Bring to a boil. Place wings in boiler, half of wing first, then other half.
Place lid on boiler and shake vigorously, covering all wings with mixture.
Pour into serving dish, for wet wings.
Drain, then pour into dish, for dry wings.

title: broccoli salad
directions: Toss broccoli, raisins, onion, nuts, and bacon.
In separate bowl, mix sugar, vinegar and mayonnaise.
Pour mixture over broccoli and toss to coat.
Refrigerate for at least 2 hours.

title: holiday fruit salad
directions: Drain fruit in separate bowl.
Dice all fruit in medium size chunks. Mix fruit well and add 3/4 to all of juice as needed.
Add 1 to 1 1/2 cups of sugar.
Let stand 20 minutes and then chill. Use any size can desired, small cans make about 10 to 12 servings.

title: pineapple marshmallow sweet potatoes
directions: Mix all ingredients except marshmallows and beat until light and fluffy.
Use more milk or fruit juice, if needed.
Place in well-greased casserole and bake in a moderate oven (350°) until heated through, 20 to 30 minutes.
Remove from oven and cover top with marshmallows.
Return to oven to brown.
Serves 6.

title: quick pigs in blanket
directions: Spread chopped cabbage in a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Brown meat and onion.
Stir in rice.
Heat tomato soup and water to boiling; pour over cabbage and meat.
Cover with foil; bake at 350° for approximately 1 hour.

title: apple and nut salad dressing
directions: Cook until thick.
Fold dressing into apples and pecans.

title: sour cream rhubarb squares
directions: Combine sugar, nuts and butter.
Mix until crumbly; set aside. Cream together brown sugar, shortening and egg.
Combine flour, salt and baking soda.
Stir well.
Add dry ingredients to creamed mixture alternately with sour cream.
When well blended stir in rhubarb.
Turn into well greased and floured 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan. Sprinkle with crumb topping.
Bake at 350° for 45 to 50 minutes. Cut into squares.

title: sweet potato pie
directions: Peel and boil them in as little water as possible. Try to cook until all water is gone, but don't burn. When done, mash them very well. Add sugar, butter, allspice, flavoring, eggs and milk. Mix well and pour into unbaked pie crust. Bake at 350° until pie is set, crust is browned and knife inserted in center comes out clean, probably 30 to 40 minutes.

title: malcolm's cornmeal cookies
directions: Mix sugar and butter with beater.
Add egg yolks; mix well. Add lemon peel, flour and cornmeal.
Mix dough in plastic; chill 3 to 4 hours.

title: green bean casserole
directions: Combine vegetables and dressing in casserole; cover and marinate for 1 hour.
Bake for 25 minutes at 350°.
Mix crumbs with Parmesan cheese; add to casserole.
Return to oven for 5 minutes.
Serve hot or cold.
Makes 8 servings.

title: dolmadakia (grape leaves)
directions: Combine all except grapevine leaves.
Remove leaves from jar; rinse and drain.
Cut off stems.
Place leaves underside up, with stem ends toward you.
Spoon a heaping teaspoonful of filling near the stem end.
Fold lower edge of leaf over filling to cover.
Fold in sides and roll up from stem end.
Line bottom of 9 x 13-inch pan with extra leaves.
Arrange seam side down in 1 to 2 layers.
Pour 1 cup water over rolls.
Cover with foil.
Bake at 325° for 1/2 hour.
Yields 50.

title: hot chocolate mix
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Try the different Coffee-mate flavors for "gourmet" flavors.
Makes great gifts when put into pretty containers.
Takes approximately 1/4 cup mix to 1 cup hot water.
Store in airtight container.

title: spanish pork chops
directions: From a beef roast, set aside 2 cups roast beef; cut up along with diced onion, diced green and red pepper.
You may use pimentos for color instead.
Bring to a boil 2 cups of beef liquid; dissolve Knox gelatine.
Mix in beef, onion and pepper.
Pour into lightly buttered loaf pan and place into refrigerator until molded.
Slice and serve.
Some like to sprinkle with vinegar.

title: apple dumplins
directions: Roll out biscuits; fill with applesauce.
Fold over and seal with fork prongs.
Place in a greased bake dish.
Mix margarine, sugar, spice and 7-Up; bring to a boil.
Pour over dumplings; bake for 30 minutes at 375°.
Serve with Cool Whip or ice cream.

title: hershey chocolate pie
directions: Melt Hershey bars in microwave.
Stir a minute to cool a little.
Combine with 2/3 of the Cool Whip and pour into graham cracker crust.
Top with remaining Cool Whip.
Quick, easy and elegant!

title: broccoli beef stir-fry
directions: In large skillet, melt margarine over medium heat.
Add meat; saute until browned.
Remove meat from skillet.
Drain skillet. Saute rice mix as package directs.
Stir in two cups water, onion, garlic, ginger and contents of packet.
Bring to boil over high heat.
Cover; reduce heat to low.
Simmer 8 minutes.
Stir in meat and peppers; cover.
Simmer until liquid is absorbed.

title: cranberry tea
directions: Place water, cloves, cinnamon sticks and sugar in a saucepan. Cover and bring to a boil.
Remove cinnamon sticks.
Remove pan from heat.
Dip tea bags in the solution; cover and brew for 3 minutes or longer if a stronger tea is desired.
Remove tea bags. Add cranberry juice cocktail; return to a boil.
Serve hot.
Makes 12 (1/2-cup) servings.

title: sicilian meat roll
directions: Mix together the first 10 ingredients.
Pat mixture into 12 x 9-inches on a large piece of wax paper or foil.
Layer ham, then cheese over meat.
Leave a 1-inch border.
Roll like jelly roll from short end.
Press ends and seam to seal.
Put on lightly greased baking pan, seam side down.
Smooth surface with spatula. Bake at 350° for 1 to 1 1/2 hours.
Makes 8 to 10 servings.

title: sweet potato casserole
directions: Boil and mash potatoes. Add other ingredients. Put in casserole. Put on topping.

title: black forest dessert
directions: Melt the margarine in pan.
Add flour and pecans.
Press in bottom of an 11 x 13-inch pan and bake for 30 minutes at 350°. Cool.

title: no guilt best-ever chocolate cake
directions: Mix cake mix with pumpkin and water. Bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes. Let cake cool and ice with fat-free Cool Whip. Absolutely moist and delicious!

title: spiced nuts
directions: Mix the first 4 ingredients, then mix the pecans well with the mixture. Spread thinly onto cookie sheet and bake at 250° for 1 hour.
Stir several times.

title: cheese ball
directions: Grate Cheddar cheeses;	put in bowl.
Add other cheese. Let stand
until
room	temperature.
Using
mixer, blend all cheeses, until
smooth.
Add
Worcestershire sauce and onion; mix well. Chill to work.
Shape into 2 balls.
Sprinkle chili powder and nuts on wax paper; roll cheese balls in it.

title: merry christmas cookies
directions: Mix sugar, eggs, milk and butter.
Add the sifted flour, soda and cinnamon, a little at a time.
Stir in dates, fruit and pecans.
Drop by teaspoonful on cookie sheet.
Bake at 300° for 20 minutes.
Makes 200 cookies.

title: broccoli cornbread
directions: Thaw and drain broccoli in mixing bowl; combine everything but corn mix.
Stir muffin mix into first mixture.
Pour into 9 x 13 x 2-inch pan.
Bake in 400° oven for 20 minutes or until done.

title: inside-outside chocolate bundt cake
directions: Combine pudding mix, cake mix, chocolate chips, milk and eggs in a bowl.
Mix by hand until well blended, about 2 minutes.
Pour into a greased and floured 12-cup tube or Bundt pan.
Bake at 350° for 50 to 60 minutes or until done.
Do not overbake.
Cool 15 minutes in pan and remove from pan.
Continue cooling on rack. Serve each slice heated 10 seconds in microwave and then top with a scoop of vanilla ice cream.

title: holiday punch
directions: Mix all juices together until well blended. Add sugar to taste, ginger ale and ice.

title: apple crisp
directions: Place apples in a glass baking dish.
Mix flour, sugar, baking powder, salt and cinnamon in mixing bowl.
Add egg; mix with a fork until crumbly.
Sprinkle over apples.
Pour melted butter over all.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes.
Serve with ice cream.

title: baked corn
directions: Mix all well and pour into an 8 x 8-inch cake pan, buttered. Bake at 400° for 35 minutes.

title: old fashioned soft sugar cookies
directions: Mix shortening, sugar and egg.
Add vanilla and buttermilk, then dry ingredients.
Roll out and cut into cookies.
Bake on cookie sheet.
Bake at 425° for 12 minutes.
Makes 2 1/2 dozen cookies.
Do not overbake.

title: vegetable sandwich
directions: Mix together. Better when made and refrigerated day before.

title: chicken flavored rice
directions: Saute peppers and
onions
in
olive oil in a pot.
Add Swanson broth,
bring
to boil.
Add 4 packages Steero instant broth, salt and pepper.
Add rice and stir with a fork.

title: hilda uhlig's rice pudding
directions: Combine first 5 ingredients.
Bring to boil.
Slow boil for 1 hour.
Beat eggs until fluffy; pour over rice.
Pour back and forth 6 or 7 times.
(If raisins desired, plump raisins and add first time.)

title: tuna fish salad for a crowd
directions: Mix all ingredients together in large bowl. Salt and pepper to taste. This will serve a large crowd.

title: gooey butter cake
directions: Mix together dry cake mix and 2 eggs.
Pat into a greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Set aside.

title: beef stew
directions: Put beef, carrots, onion and celery in large casserole dish. Combine V-8 juice, tapioca and spices.
Pour over beef and vegetables.
Cover casserole and bake for 2 1/2 hours at 300°. Take off cover and add potatoes.
Cook 1 hour, uncovered.
This is also good served over rice or egg noodles.

title: cocoa krispies marble bars
directions: Cook over medium heat the sugar, syrup and peanut butter.
Add chocolate morsels and cereal.
Remove from heat and press into buttered 13 x 9-inch pan.
Cut into squares and serve.

title: hamburger and tater tot hot dish
directions: Brown meat and onion. Mix oatmeal, milk, egg and soup.
Add to meat.
Fold in Tater Tots and place in greased dish.
Season and bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: quick pecan pie
directions: Beat the egg white until stiff.
Add sugar slowly.
Add crackers, nuts and vanilla.
Pour into a buttered pie plate and bake at 350° about 25 minutes until lightly browned.
(You can stick a toothpick in it.)
Cool and top with Cool Whip.

title: lo-cal congealed salad
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Chill before serving.

title: german christmas stretz
directions: Let rise until doubled in bulk in a warm place.
Knead down and put into 4 greased loaf pans.
Allow to double in bulk.
Bake in a moderate oven at 350° about 1 hour.
Serve hot or cold. Germans make up this bread at Christmastime and continue eating it for months.
Recipe brought over to this country by a woman who gave it to Mrs. Leinback in Salem about 1825.
This recipe from a very old Moravian cookbook from my hometown in Indiana.

title: mamaw myra's old fashioned tea cakes
directions: Cream margarine and sugar until light and fluffy.
Add eggs and beat well.	Add remaining ingredients and mix well.
Form dough balls about the size of a walnut and place onto an ungreased cookie sheet.
Press flat with the bottom of a glass that has been coated with sugar.
Bake at 350° for 10- 11 minutes or until lightly brown.
Makes 7-8 dozen.

title: sweet potatoes and apples
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Arrange alternate slices of sweet potatoes and apples in a baking dish that has been sprayed with a nonstick cooking spray.

title: german style bratwurst and sauerkraut
directions: Cook bacon in large skillet over medium high heat until crisp.
Remove bacon; drain and crumble on paper towel, set aside. Drain off all but 2 tablespoons drippings in skillet.
Add onion and garlic to dripping; cook over medium heat until tender, stirring occasionally.
Stir in sauerkraut, potatoes, 1 1/2 cups of water, juice, brown sugar, bouillon, caraway and dried bay leaf. Add remaining water if necessary to cover potatoes.
Bring to boil over high heat.

title: cherry or blueberry dessert
directions: Crush graham crackers.
Melt margarine in a 9 x 13-inch pan. Add crackers and sugar.
Take out 2 tablespoons for to sprinkle on the top.
Press in pan and bake 10 minutes in 325° oven.
Cool. Melt in double boiler marshmallows and 1 cup milk.
Cool.
Add whipped topping.
Put the cherry or blueberry filling on crust, then the marshmallow mixture.
Sprinkle the 2 tablespoons crumbs on top.
Refrigerate several hours.
Serves 12.

title: beef and spinach supreme
directions: Brown ground meat. Add sauteed onion.
Add garlic, oregano, mushrooms, salt and pepper. Cook 3 minutes. Stir in drained spinach, celery soup, sour cream and uncooked rice.
Put in a 9 x 13-inch dish. Top with cheese. Bake 15 to 20 minutes at 350°.

title: tyrolean bacon dumplings
directions: Finely chop onion, bacon and salami.
Add salt and marjoram. Fry together until bacon is crisp.
Drain off fat.
Cut rolls into cubes; mix with eggs.
Add bacon mixture; add milk and flour in quantity needed just to bind; mix very well.
Allow to stand 1/2 hour.

title: fresh apple cake
directions: In large bowl, mix oil, eggs, sugar and lemon extract.
In separate bowl, sift together flour, soda, salt, cinnamon and baking powder.
Add to first mixture.
Stir in nuts and apples.
Mix well. Spread mixture in greased 13 x 9-inch pan.
Sprinkle butterscotch chips over batter.
Bake at 350° for 55 to 60 minutes.
Brush top of warm cake with butter and rum.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: chicken salad
directions: Bake the chicken and remove the meat from the bones. There should be 4 cups or more of chicken. Add chopped celery, grapes, water chestnuts, pineapple and slivered almonds.
Mix mayonnaise with curry powder, soy sauce and lemon juice. Pour into other ingredients. Mix well and chill.
Hard-boiled eggs and 1 cup cooked chopped potatoes can be added to this salad. Serve on lettuce garnished with strawberries or sliced oranges.

title: mandarin orange cake
directions: Mix together; beat 2 minutes. Place in 2 round cake pans (floured or sprayed). Bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes.

title: ham loaf
directions: Have ham and pork ground together.
Mix all ingredients together and bake at 350° for 2 1/2 to 3 hours.
(For 1/2 loaf, bake 1 1/2 hours.)

title: leslie's easy apple pie
directions: Prepare vanilla pudding according to directions on box.
Spoon apple pie filling into baked pie crust.
Spread vanilla pudding over filling.
Top with whipped cream.
Sprinkle with nutmeg or cinnamon.

title: the impossible pie
directions: Put all ingredients in blender or mixer; blend until all mixed together.
Pour into buttered 10-inch pie pan.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
When done, the crust will be on the bottom, the custard in the middle and the coconut on top.

title: ranch potato crisps
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Cut potatoes, in crinkle-cut fashion if desired, into 1/4 inch thick slices.
Place in large bowl.
Add oil; mix lightly.
Add dressing mix; toss to coat evenly
Arrange potato slices in single layer on
greased baking sheet.
Do not overlap.
Bake 40-45 minutes or until potatoes are browned and tender.
Serve warm with sour cream, if desired.

title: carrot cake
directions: Cream together oil and sugar.
Add eggs (one at a time).
Sift together and add flour, soda, salt and cinnamon.
Last, add carrots.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 45 minutes.
Makes a large cake or 2 (9-inch) layers.

title: orange julius
directions: Mix all ingredients in blender.
Blend until desired consistency.

title: aunt bess' pecan pie
directions: To the eggs add sugar, corn syrup and butter.
Add next three ingredients, mixing well.
Add pecans.
Pour in unbaked pie shell. Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: irish potato casserole
directions: Cook potatoes in boiling water, about 30 minutes.
Drain potatoes and mash.
Beat cream cheese with electric mixer until smooth.
Add potatoes and remaining ingredients, except paprika. Spoon into lightly buttered 2-quart casserole dish.
Sprinkle with paprika.
Cover and refrigerate overnight.
Remove and bake at 350° for 30 minutes until heated.

title: bran muffins
directions: Grease muffin pans.
Preheat oven to 400°.
In a small bowl, stir together the first four ingredients.
In a large bowl, stir together the cereal and milk.
Let stand for 2 minutes.
Add egg and oil; stir.
Add flour mixture, 1/3 at a time.
Blend between each addition.
Do not beat.
Fill muffin cups 3/4 full.
Bake for 18 to 20 minutes or until a toothpick comes out clean.

title: lemon pie
directions: Stir sugar, water, egg yolk and pie filling in saucepan (medium).
Stir over medium heat until it comes to a full boil. Pour into baked pie crust.
Add your choice of topping or meringue.

title: shipwreck casserole
directions: In greased casserole put ingredients in layers in the following order:
potatoes, onions, celery, rice, hamburger, kidney beans and tomato juice.
Salt and pepper may be added between layers.
Cover and bake at 350°
for 1 1/2 hours.
Serves 4.
Approximately 500 calories per serving.

title: vegetable lentil soup(delicious!!)
directions: In Dutch oven, over medium heat, in olive oil, add diced carrots, chopped celery, chopped onion and minced garlic, stirring until tender and very light brown.
Stir in stewed tomatoes, dry lentils, cubed potatoes, chicken broth and 3 cups water.
Over high heat, bring to a boil.
Turn heat to low and simmer 50 minutes.
(Slice escarole thin and stir into soup until it wilts.) Serve.
May be served with Italian bread!

title: green bean casserole
directions: Mix drained beans and soup together.
Cook at 350° for about 15 to 20 minutes.
Top with cheese, then onion rings and cook for 3 to 5 minutes more.

title: seafood chowder
directions: In a large pot mix together chicken broth, mushrooms, carrot, onion, garlic, marjoram and Bay leaf.
Bring to a boil, and boil for 2 minutes.
Add remaining ingredients and simmer until cooked. Garnish with parsley and grated lemon peel if desired.

title: banana date cookies(no sugar, 95 calories in 2 cookies)
directions: Mix bananas, dates and oil.
Add remaining ingredients and mix lightly.
Let stand for a few minutes.
Drop by teaspoon onto ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake in preheated 350° oven for 15 to 17 minutes.
Let cool completely before removing.

title: onion pretzels
directions: Place broken pretzels in 9 x 13-inch pan.
Melt butter in saucepan, add onion soup mix.
Pour over pretzels and stir around. Bake at 250° for 1 1/2 hours.

title: table rolls(bread machine)
directions: Put the dry active yeast in the inner pot.
Add the remaining ingredients, except water.
Carefully then, pour in warm water. Press the select button for "manual".
Press the start button. Beep sound indicates that the final rising process is finished.

title: raw cranberry salad
directions: *Or 1 can crushed pineapple.

title: bread pudding
directions: Soak bread in milk.
Add cream, eggs, sugar and vanilla. Put into well-buttered casserole dish and bake at 375° for 20 to 25 minutes.
Before baking, sprinkle cinnamon on top.

title: old-fashioned apple cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
In a large bowl, combine dry cake mix, pie filling, eggs, water and nuts.
Blend at low speed until completely moistened.
Beat at medium speed for 2 minutes.
Spread batter in a greased and floured 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan.

title: glazed meatballs
directions: Soak bread in milk until soft.
Add eggs, horseradish, 1 teaspoon salt and 1/4 teaspoon pepper.
Beat until smooth.
Add beef; mix well.
Shape into 3/4-inch meatballs.
Place on rack in shallow baking dish.
Bake at 450° for 10 to 15 minutes.

title: microwave fudge
directions: Butter a 13 x 9-inch pan.
Microwave margarine in a 3-quart microwave-safe bowl on High 1 minute or until melted.
Stir in sugar and evaporated milk.
Microwave on High 10 minutes, stirring every two minutes.
Add chocolate chips, Marshmallow Creme and vanilla all at once.
Stir until melted and blended.
Pour into buttered pan.
Cook until firm.

title: canned tomato soup
directions: Cook first 6 ingredients altogether and run through a sieve to make juice.
Melt butter and stir in flour; add to juice and bring to a boil.
Can in pints or freeze.
Boiling water bath for 30 minutes.
Makes 8 to 10 quarts.

title: prawn avocado salad for 4
directions: Mix thawed prawns with mayonnaise, ketchup and juice of 1/2 lemon.
Place halved avocados on a spread of lettuce.
Fill cored avocados with prawn mixture.
Slice remaining lemon and divide among the four.
Garnish with fresh parsley and sprinkle with fresh ground pepper.

title: steamtown yumm
directions: Mix everything together.
Put in ungreased cookie sheet and bake 25 to 30 minutes at 350°.

title: cheese toast
directions: Mix cheese, dressing and mayonnaise.
Spread on top of bread. Bake at 400° until cheese melts and bread is brown on bottom.

title: broiled lunch sandwich
directions: Toast bread; place slice of cheese on toast and broil until cheese begins to melt.
Add tomato and bits of cooked bacon. Broil until tomato is hot.
Serve immediately.
Makes 1 sandwich.

title: strawberry and cheese spread
directions: Mix cheese, pecans, mayo and scallions.
Pack into a 6 inch mold.
Chill for 5 to 6 hours.
Unmold and place strawberry jam in center of mold.
Serve with crackers, putting cheese and jam on each cracker for unusual taste.

title: randy's pork chops
directions: Mix all ingredients, except jam.
Marinate 4 or 5 pork chops 2 to 3 hours.
Grill or broil chops until done, 15 to 20 minutes. Mix marinade with jam in saucepan and bring to a boil.
Baste pork chops the last ten minutes.
Leftover marinade can be used as dip for the meat.

title: chicken fricassee
directions: Make your favorite meatball recipe, using unflavored breadcrumbs or matzo meal.
Put oil in bottom of large saucepan with onions and paprika.
Sear your chicken.
Then add meatballs to saucepan.
Add boiling water just to cover meat.
Salt and pepper to taste.
Simmer until chicken is tender.
Carefully stir once or twice.
When done, thicken gravy with cornstarch.

title: dill weed dip
directions: Mix all ingredients together and chill.

title: potato - potluck
directions: Mix above ingredients together.
Place in buttered 9 x 13-inch dish.
Top with 2 cups crushed corn flakes and 1/4 cup melted butter.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes.

title: fran adams' summer squash casserole
directions: Boil onion and squash for 5 minutes.
Drain.
Mix in carrot, soup and sour cream.
Set aside.
Add margarine and herbs to stuffing mix.
Pour 1/2 of stuffing mixture in bottom of casserole dish.
Add vegetable mixture and top with remaining stuffing mix. Bake 30 minutes at 350°.

title: tater tots casserole
directions: Cook tots according to bag.
Brown meat, drain off grease, add soup, milk to hamburger meat and mix.
Take tater tots out of oven, put in a casserole dish, pour meat and soup mixture over tots. Let cook for 20 minutes in 350 degree oven.
Take out of oven and cover with grated cheese.
Put back in oven and let cook until cheese is melted.

title: oatmeal raisin cookies
directions: Cream shortening and sugars.
Add eggs and vanilla.
Add flour and raisins.
Mix.
Add oatmeal and raisins.
Mix.
Drop onto a greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 10 to 12 minutes.
Makes 4 dozen.

title: oatmeal cookies
directions: Use no liquids.
Bake in moderate oven.
These are drop cookies.

title: pistachio pound cake
directions: Bake cake according to box; use a Bundt pan.
Remove from pan and place on dish.
While cake is still hot, mix glaze and drizzle over hot cake.

title: large cream cheese log
directions: Mix first 3 ingredients together.
Roll out Velveeta cheese flat between 2 pieces of wax paper.
Not too thin or not too thick.
Place cream cheese filling in center.
Fold Velveeta cheese over cream cheese.
Pinch edges closed.
Chill until ready to serve.
Serve with crackers.

title: aztec chicken
directions: Microwave chicken in covered 3 or 4 quart casserole dish in 1/4 cup water on High for 13 to 16 minutes or until chicken is cooked.
Turn once during cooking.
Remove chicken from bones and cut up into large bite-size pieces.

title: sugar coated pecans
directions: Put water, sugar
and cinnamon in iron frypan, bring to a boil.
Put in pecans;
boil and stir until all liquid is out and nuts are dry and
coated
with a dry white look.
Pour out on a cookie sheet,
only
one
thickness.
Put in oven at 250° for about 30 minutes;
stir
about 3 times.
Remove from oven; let cool.
Store in jars or plastic bags.

title: hot pepper spinach
directions: Saute onion and garlic. Add spinach.
Mix. Heat until hot. Add beaten egg, Parmesan cheese and garlic salt. When really hot, add chunks of pepper cheese. Stir until melted.
Pour into casserole. Bake at 350° until bubbly. Garnish with bacon bits on top.

title: joel's favorite blue ribbon blueberry muffins
directions: Beat egg with a fork.
Stir in milk and oil.
Blend dry ingredients and stir in just until flour is moistened.
Batter will be lumpy.
Add blueberries.
Fold in.
Fill muffin cups 2/3 full.
Makes 1 dozen.
Bake 20 to 22 minutes at 400°.

title: sour cream casserole
directions: Combine first 4 ingredients. Add tomato sauce and simmer. Then add mushroom soup, mushrooms and onion soup mix. Let simmer. While simmering, cook about 3/4's of 12 ounce package of noodles by directions. Mix all together. Put into casserole dish. Top with sour cream, then top with grated Cheddar cheese. Bake at 350° until cheese melts and gets brown and bubbly.

title: rice and cabbage goulash
directions: Brown meat in shortening, stirring occasionally to crumble. Add onion; cook 5 minutes. Add tomato sauce, salt and pepper to meat. Stir in remaining ingredients in order listed. Bring to a boil. Cover and simmer 30 to 40 minutes until rice and cabbage are tender.

title: cranberry mold
directions: Dissolve jello in water.
Add remaining ingredients and pour into mold.

title: broccoli cheese dip
directions: Melt cheese, soup and broccoli in a fondue pot.
Use Tostitos to dip with.

title: fireside mocha
directions: In each large coffee mug, put one package hot chocolate (the make-with-water kind); fill mug with Cinnamon Coffee.

title: "different" pie crust
directions: Cut shortening into mixed dry ingredients with a pastry blender.
Mix
the	beaten	egg, water and vinegar.
Stir into first mixture.
Roll out on floured board and use for any type of pie.
It
will keep up to 5 weeks in refrigerator.	Makes 2 double crust pies.

title: spicy barbecued pork
directions: Cook pork chops in 12-inch skillet over medium heat until brown on both sides.
Mix remaining ingredients; pour over pork in skillet.
Heat to boiling; reduce heat.
Simmer, uncovered, about 20 minutes, spooning sauce frequently over pork, until pork is no longer pink in center.
Serve pork with sauce.
Makes 8 servings.

title: baked brisket
directions: Place brisket on foil in large pan.
Sprinkle meat with the 3 salts, Lipton onion soup mix and liquid smoke.
Wrap and let stand in refrigerator overnight.
Next morning, pour on Worcestershire sauce.
Wrap in foil.
Bake 5 hours at 275°.

title: raw vegetable salad
directions: Chop all vegetables.
Mix other ingredients.
Pour mixture over vegetables.
Better if made 1 to 2 days ahead of the day you will be serving it.

title: wonder bars
directions: Mix syrup and sugar together.
Microwave 1 minute.
Stir. Microwave 1 1/2 minutes; stir.
Add peanut butter; stir together as one.
Add Special K cereal and mix together.
Pour in a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Press down in pan.
