title: broccoli casserole
directions: Mix oleo, onion soup, chestnuts and pecans.
Drain broccoli. Put in 9 1/2 x 13-inch glass casserole.
Prepare a day ahead. Cover with 4 cups crushed Rice Krispies mixed with 2 tablespoons melted butter.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: beef stew
directions: Brown beef.
Place in roaster with all other ingredients. Cover.
Bake at 250° for 4 hours.
Can also be placed in crock-pot on low for 8 hours.
May also add corn, peas and green beans, if desired.

title: spanish rice
directions: Heat 2 tablespoons oil in large skillet; add rice.
Brown lightly, stirring frequently.
Add remaining 1 tablespoon oil, onion, green pepper and celery; cook until soft.
Add remaining ingredients.
Cover pan tightly.
Simmer for 20 to 30 minutes.

title: strawberry shortcake
directions: Stir together berries and 1/4 cup of the sugar; set aside. Stir together remaining sugar, flour and baking powder.
Cut in margarine until mixture resembles coarse crumbs.
Combine egg and milk; add all at once to dry ingredients.
Stir just to moisten. Spread into a greased 8 x 1 1/2-inch round baking pan, building up edge slightly.
Bake in a 450° oven for 15 to 18 minutes or until toothpick inserted in center comes out clean.
Cool in pan 10 minutes.
Remove from pan.
Split into 2 layers.
Spoon the fruit and whipped cream between layers and over top.

title: broccoli and dressing casserole
directions: Cook broccoli; drain and set aside.
Saute celery and onion in stick of oleo.
Mix 1 cup warm water into dressing.
Add celery and onion mix to dressing.
Make paste of flour and butter over medium heat in saucepan.
Add milk and stir until white sauce is smooth.
Add broken chunks of cheese to white sauce and stir until melted.

title: oven fried chicken breasts
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Melt butter in large rectangular casserole dish.
Dip chicken in milk and then roll in flour. Place in casserole dish.
Salt and pepper.
Bake on one side until brown.
Turn and brown on other side.

title: chicken dressing
directions: Mix all this together real well and pour into a well-greased pan.
Cook at 375° until lightly brown on top.

title: basic hot salsa
directions: Dice tomatoes (drain if very watery), combine all other ingredients. Add tomatoes, cover and refrigerate for a day or more for best flavor. Makes 1 cup.

title: christmas cherries
directions: Mix shortening, sugar, egg yolk, grated orange, lemon rind, vanilla and lemon juice until light and fluffy.
Add flour and beat just long enough to mix.
Chill until easy to handle.
Form dough into 1/2-inch balls; roll in egg white and then in nuts. Place on greased cookie sheets.
Press cherry into top of each cookie.
Bake at 350° for approximately 10 minutes.

title: grits
directions: Add butter and salt to boiling water.
Slowly stir in the grits.
Cover and cook slowly for about 30 to 40 minutes.
Stir often.

title: cheese bars
directions: Press one package of crescent rolls to edges of 9 x 13-inch ungreased pan.

title: easy pasta salad
directions: Mix together pasta and vegetables.
Toss with dressing until well moistened.

title: angel biscuits
directions: Mix dry ingredients.
Add shortening until well mixed.
Add buttermilk and dissolved yeast.
Work together until flour is moistened.
Put in large mixing bowl with tight fitting lid.
Put in refrigerator until ready to use.
As desired, take out as much dough as needed.
Roll out on floured pastry sheet to 1/2-inch thickness and cut.
Bake at 400° on cookie sheet for 12 to 15 minutes, or until browned.
Makes 5 to 6 dozen.

title: sugar cookies
directions: Cream the sugar and butter.
Add eggs, milk and vanilla; mix until creamy.
Add dry ingredients 1 cup at a time.
Chill dough overnight.
Roll out on floured surface; bake on ungreased cookie sheet at 350° 5 to 8 minutes.
Ice when cool.

title: lemon pie
directions: Cook pie crust.
Combine 1 cup sugar, cornstarch, egg yolks and boiling water in a double boiler.
Cook until thick.
Put in cooked pie crust and add meringue.
To make meringue, beat the egg whites until stiff.
Add 2 tablespoons sugar.
Put on pie and bake in oven until brown.

title: salsa caliente
directions: Combine tomatoes and chili salsa in medium bowl.
Add vinegar; stir until mixed well.
Let sit 15 minutes.
Add remaining ingredients; blend thoroughly.
Cover and refrigerate for at least 24 hours.

title: cornbread
directions: Place all ingredients in a mixing bowl and mix thoroughly. Preheat oven to 450 degrees.
Coat a well-seasoned black iron skillet or corn-stick pan with enough bacon grease to cover. IMPORTANT:
Place greased skillet or pan in preheated oven until it begins to smoke (three to four minutes) to create a crunchy crust on the bottom.
When the pan is ready, add the cornbread mixture and return to the hot oven.
Bake for 20-25 minutes or until golden brown (bake muffins and corn-sticks 15-20 minutes).
Serve while hot with softened butter.

title: glazed fruit salad
directions: Drain mandarin oranges and chunk pineapple good and save juice. Mix the 2 juices.
In meantime, rinse cherries in cold water and cut in halves.
Put 1 c. of juice in saucepan.
Add vanilla pudding.
Bring to boil and cool until clear and thick.
Cool the pudding mixture and then pour over the drained fruit and cherries. Just before serving, add bananas, cut in chunks.
Can be kept in refrigerator quite a while without the bananas.
They should only be added just before serving.

title: buttermilk pie("a delicate custard pie...one you will love!")
directions: Mix sugar and flour; add buttermilk, beaten eggs and vanilla. Melt the butter over low heat. Add to buttermilk mixture and mix well. Pour into pie crust and bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes.

title: shrimp rice casserole
directions: Cook rice; saute together celery, green onions and bell pepper until tender, using part of margarine.
While rice is hot, add rest of margarine, soups and sauteed onions, peppers and celery. Boil shrimp.
Peel and cut into bite size pieces.
Grate cheese, reserving a small amount for topping.
Add cheese and shrimp to rice mixture.
Add garlic powder, salt and pepper to taste.
Red pepper may be added if desired.
Top with cheese.
Bake in 9 x 13-inch baking dish for 30 to 40 minutes at 350°.
Cover with foil while baking.
Serves 8.

title: seven layer salad
directions: Refrigerate 24 hours before serving.

title: linguine and clam sauce
directions: Steam clams in 1 cup water until clams just open, about 8 minutes.
Save clam broth.
Chop clam meat and set aside.
Saute garlic in olive oil until soft.
Add broth, wine and seasonings and cook about 5 minutes.
Add clams to broth and pour over fresh cooked pasta.
Serve hot; garnish with Parmesan cheese and parsley.

title: 7-up lime jello
directions: Mix
Jell-O
and
hot water.
Cool slightly, then add 1 small 7-Up
and 1 small flat can crushed pineapple.
Then add 1/4 cup chopped nuts.
Chill well before serving.

title: ham rolls
directions: Mix together ingredients and spread on top and bottom of rolls.
Wrap in foil and bake in 350° oven for 20 minutes.

title: crusty chicken casserole
directions: Mix all together.
Put in dish.
Cover with 1 cup Pepperidge herb stuffing.
Bake 30 minutes or until brown and bubbly at 350°.

title: dishpan cookies
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Form into balls and place on an ungreased cookie sheet. Bake at 350° for 10 to 12 minutes.
Makes a dishpan full of cookies.

title: wacky cake
directions: Sift first 4 ingredients in an ungreased 9 x 13-inch cake pan. Stir in remaining ingredients.
Mix all together in cake pan.
No need to grease or flour pan.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes. Easy enough for a ten year old to make.
Great warm with ice cream or cool with Cool Whip.

title: pretzel salad
directions: Mix pretzels, butter and 3 tablespoons of sugar in a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake for 8 minutes.
Cool.

title: easy peach cobbler
directions: Melt oleo in a 10 x 10-inch pan.
Mix together Bisquick, sugar and milk.
Pour over melted oleo.
Pour large can drained peaches or equivalent of fresh peaches over dough.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.
(Can use other fruits, also.)

title: jezebel sauce
directions: Mix together and pour over cream cheese.
Serve with crackers. Keeps in refrigerator almost forever.

title: mr. b's frosting cake
directions: Mix together all the ingredients except the frosting.
After all are well blended, add the can of frosting and mix well again. Spray Bundt cake pan well with Pam and flour also.
Set oven to 350°.
Pour in cake pan and bake for 45 to 60 minutes.
Test for doneness with a toothpick.

title: fried apples
directions: Cook apples for 15 minutes; sprinkle with sugar, cinnamon and nutmeg.

title: stuffed mushrooms
directions: Saute mushrooms stems (chopped).
Add onions in margarine, then add rest of ingredients.
Stuff caps.
Bake at 350° for 15 minutes.
Serve hot.

title: vera's best pumpkin pie
directions: Mix in order and cook until thick.
Cool.
Beat egg whites and fold into mixture when cool.
Put in baked pie shells and bake until set.
Makes 2 pies.

title: no bake cookies
directions: Mix sugar, cocoa, milk and margarine.
Bring to boil and cook 5 minutes.	Remove from heat; add peanut butter and oatmeal.
Drop by spoons on greased cookie sheet.

title: hot artichoke dip
directions: Mix all ingredients except paprika; sprinkle with paprika. Bake 30 minutes at 350°.
Serve hot with crackers.
Yummy!!

title: nancy's refreshing drink
directions: Squeeze juice from both oranges and lemons.
Add sugar and water and stir well.
Very tasty on a hot, humid day.

title: bishop bread
directions: Mix into crumbs.
Save 3/4 cup crumbs for topping.
Add to crumb mixture 1 egg, 1/2 teaspoon soda, milk and baking powder. Beat well and pour into 2 cake pans.
Cover with crumb mixture. Bake for 30 minutes at 375°.

title: apple crumb pie
directions: Mix apples, sugar and cinnamon; pour over pie crust.

title: hello dollies
directions: Melt oleo; add oleo and cracker crumbs to a 9 x 13-inch pan. Press into bottom.
Layer remaining ingredients, except milk, in order listed.
Pour milk evenly over top.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: sue's candy fudge
directions: Boil the milk and sugar for 8-9 minutes. Add the remaining ingredients, stirring until all melts.
Makes about five pounds of wonderful fudge.

title: lime cooler
directions: Blend ingredients except sherbet in blender.
Pour in tall glasses and top with a scoop of sherbet.
Serves 4 to 6.

title: self-filled cupcakes
directions: Mix cake according to package directions.
Cream the cheese with sugar.
Beat in egg and salt.
Stir in chocolate chips.
Fill muffin pan 2/3 full with cake mix.
Drop 1 teaspoon cheese mixture into middle of each cupcake.
Bake as package directs for cupcakes.

title: congo squares
directions: Mix in order given.
Makes 2 cookie sheets.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.
Do not overcook.

title: reuben casserole
directions: Warm potatoes slightly to soften.
Place in bowl with sauerkraut and green onions.
Mix well.
Spoon 2/3 into greased 3-quart baking dish.
Cover with corned beef and cheese.
Top with remaining potato mixture.
Bake, uncovered, at 350° for 30 to 45 minutes or until heated through.
Makes 6 to 8 servings.

title: meat loaf ring(microwave)
directions: Thoroughly combine all ingredients except catsup.
Pack lightly into a 9-inch glass dish making a well in center.
Place empty glass, right side down, in center of dish.
Microwave (High) 6 minutes, rotating 1/4 turn halfway through cooking.
Drizzle catsup over top.
Microwave (High) 5 minutes longer, rotating 1/4 turn halfway through cooking.
Rest 5 minutes.
Remove glass; baste off drippings.
Serves 5 to 6.

title: lemon chicken
directions: Dip chicken in flour.
In large skillet, heat oil and margarine over medium high heat.
Add chicken and cook for 5 minutes on each side.
Remove from skillet, set aside.
In same skillet, stir in lemon juice and parsley into oil mixture.
Pour over chicken.
Keep warm.
In same skillet, prepare Rice-A-Roni as package directs, stirring in broccoli after rice has simmered for 10 minutes.
Top with chicken, parsley-lemon sauce, sprinkle with cheese.

title: carrot cake
directions: Mix sugar and oil, adding eggs one at a time.
Beat well after each egg.
Slowly add flour sifted with salt, soda and cinnamon. Add carrots and beat well.	Pour into an 11 x 14 pan and bake at 350° for 45 to 55 minutes.

title: whipped sweet potatoes
directions: Peel potatoes; boil until soft, then mash.
Add 3 tablespoons sugar, butter, egg (beaten until light), salt and cream.
Turn into buttered dish and put in slow oven for 15 to 20 minutes.
Put marshmallows on top and brown.

title: apple bread
directions: Beat together first 4 ingredients.
Sift together flour, soda and cinnamon.
Combine mixtures and add shredded apples (be sure and use a cooking type apple, not any of the Delicious varieties). Add chopped pecans (no walnuts, changes the flavor).
Grease two loaf pans.
Bake for 1 hour at 350°.

title: chocolate chip cheesecake
directions: Heat oven to 300°.
Combine crumbs, cocoa, sugar and butter; press evenly into bottom of 9-inch pan.
Beat cream cheese until fluffy; add milk and beat until smooth.
Add eggs and vanilla and mix well.
In small bowl, toss 1/2 chips with flour to coat; add to cheese mixture.
Pour in pan.
Sprinkle remaining chips over top.
Bake 1 hour.
Turn oven off; allow to cool 1 hour in oven. Remove from oven; cool to room temperature.
Refrigerate leftovers.

title: shrimp and cocktail wiener batter
directions: In a small mixing bowl, sift the flour, sugar, baking powder, seasoned salt and chili powder.
Add eggs, milk and oil or butter; stir until smooth.
Heat oil in fondue pot to 375°.
Spear shrimp or wieners and dip into batter; drain well.
Place in hot oil, resting fork on edge of pot.
Do not use more than 8 forks at a time.
Fry until batter is golden brown, about 3 to 4 minutes. Remove and cool slightly.
Serve with tartar or seafood sauce, ketchup, mustard or barbecue sauce.
Makes batter for 20 to 25 shrimp or wieners.

title: mexican dip
directions: Prepare beef according to taco seasoning directions.
Melt Velveeta in crock-pot.
Add beef mixture and chilies.
Heat 20 to 30 minutes.
Serve with chips.
Store in refrigerator.

title: pumpkin pie recipe
directions: Combine the sugar, salt and spices in a small bowl. Beat eggs lightly in a large bowl and stir in the cooked pumpkin and sugar/spice mixture. Gradually stir in the evaporated milk. Pour into the pie shell.

title: four layer cake
directions: Cut butter into flour.
Pat in a 13 x 9-inch pan and bake at 375° for 15 minutes.
Let cool.

title: oklahoma style fried cucumbers
directions: Dip cucumber slices in egg; dredge in breadcrumbs. Fry cucumber slices in hot oil (375°) in a skillet until browned, turning once. Drain well on paper towels. Serve with dill sauce or horseradish sauce.

title: fruit salad
directions: Mix altogether and serve.

title: mud dessert
directions: We used this on our Hobo Day.
Mix together pudding and milk. In separate bowl, cream the cream cheese and add to the pudding. Add the Cool Whip.
Beat well and pour on top of half of the Oreo cookie mixture that's been pushed into a pan or dish.
Top with remaining cookie mixture.
Refrigerate.

title: blueberry icebox cake
directions: Slice angel food cake into 3 layers.
Mix sugar and cream cheese.
Blend until smooth.
Add Cool Whip (if too thick add just a little milk).
Spread this mixture on first layer of cake; then blueberries.
Second layer the same, then third layer the same.

title: pasta hanleyardi
directions: Steam broccoli just until tender in saucepan or in microwave oven in a covered dish, about 5 minutes.
Cook pasta in large pot of boiling water and salt according to package directions.
While pasta is cooking, heat olive oil on medium flame in 12-inch frying pan.
Saute garlic for about 1 minute, then add shrimp.
Saute another few minutes until shrimp are heated through.
Drain pasta and place on platter.
Place drained broccoli over pasta.
Pour shrimp and olive oil over broccoli.
Serve with lemon and Parmesan cheese if desired.

title: salad dressing cake
directions: Mix ingredients together.
Put in greased 13 x 9-inch pan. Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: stewed apples
directions: Peel, core and slice apples. In a bowl combine all ingredients, except apples.
Microwave on Full power (100%) until melted.
Toss apples into mixture and microwave, covered, until apples are tender, approximately 5 minutes.

title: roast duck with orange-raisin stuffing
directions: Stuff ducks with a dressing prepared as follows:
Saute onion and celery in butter for about 5 minutes.
Add raisins, orange rind, salt, thyme and a dash of pepper.
Add bread crumbs and mix. Place stuffed ducks on a rack in roasting pan and roast about 30 minutes at 450°.
Serve with Orange Sauce.

title: salsa
directions: Mix all ingredients. Serve with chips. Refrigerate leftovers.

title: blueberry pie
directions: Cook 1 cup blueberries with 3/4 cup sugar and water for 10 minutes until blueberries are cooked.
Puree, then add cornstarch and cinnamon; cook until thickened.
Blend in butter and Cointreau; cool.
Fold in rest of blueberries and pour into shell. Chill.

title: baked salmon loaf
directions: Heat oven to 375°.
Mix salmon and liquid in a mixing bowl. Add bread crumbs and milk; blend well.
Add egg and remaining ingredients; mix well.
Turn mixture into a well-greased loaf pan for about 40 minutes.
Serve with sauce made by using 1 cup white sauce, 1/4 cup mayonnaise, chopped almonds and olives.

title: sesame-cheddar bread
directions: In mixing bowl, combine flour, sugar, baking powder and salt. Blend well; cut in butter until it resembles coarse meal.
Stir in cheese and oregano.
In small bowl, blend milk and egg; add to flour mixture and stir until moistened.
Spread in greased 9-inch square pan.
Sprinkle with sesame seeds.
Bake at 400° for 25 to 30 minutes and cut into slices (make muffins, bake at 15 to 20 minutes).

title: vegetable casserole
directions: Mix together.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: old-fashioned meat loaf
directions: In a large mixing bowl, mix ground beef and sausage.
Grate onion and bell pepper.
Mix meat, onion and green pepper.
Put mixture into a loaf pan and spread ketchup over the top.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes or until brown.

title: yellow angel food cake
directions: Sift dry ingredients together.
Add alternately with water. Pour into a greased angel food pan.
Bake at 325°.

title: absolute auction onion rings
directions: Slice onions. Mix all ingredients. Dip onion slices in batter and deep-fry.

title: butterscotch pie
directions: Mix milk, egg yolks and flour together thoroughly.
Melt the butter and brown sugar in a heavy iron skillet.
Let sugar brown a little.
Add the milk mixture and cook over medium heat until mixture thickens.
Let cool; pour in a baked pie crust.
Top with meringue.

title: crunch potato chip salad
directions: In medium bowl combine mayonnaise and vinegar.
Stir in remaining ingredients (except potato chips).
Cover and chill. Just before serving, add broken potato chips; toss lightly.

title: corn fritters
directions: Sift flour, salt and baking powder into bowl.
Beat eggs with milk.
Add melted fat and corn; combine the 2 mixtures lightly. Drop from teaspoon into deep fat heated to 365°.
Fry until brown, about 4 to 5 minutes.
Drain on absorbent paper.
Great dipped in syrup.

title: boston baked beans
directions: Soak washed beans overnight.
Add 1 teaspoon soda.
Boil beans gently for 15 minutes; drain and rinse.
Cook gently for 1/2 hour or until they begin to soften.
Make cuts in rind of pork 1/2 inch apart.
Place in bottom of deep baking dish.
Add drained beans and set rest of pork in them, with only scored rind exposed.

title: icebox fruit cake
directions: Melt marshmallows in double boiler.
Add milk.
Crush wafers. Add all ingredients together and mix well. Press in a loaf pan. Chill 2 hours and remove from pan.

title: baked oysters
directions: Put all ingredients on oysters and cook on broil until done. Do not overcook.

title: sour cream and apple coleslaw
directions: Mix sour cream and egg yolks in medium bowl.
Add rest of ingredients except cabbage and apple; mix well.
Pour dressing over cabbage and apple.
Toss until well coated.
Refrigerate at least 30 minutes.
Makes 6 to 8 servings.

title: easy toffee bars
directions: Heat oven to 400°.
Line 13 x 9-inch pan with foil; grease foil with butter.
Arrange graham crackers in prepared pan. (Some crackers may need to be broken apart in order to cover entire bottom of pan.)
In medium saucepan, combine brown sugar and butter; bring to a boil.
Remove from heat; pour over graham crackers.
Bake at 400° for 5 minutes.
Remove from oven; immediately sprinkle with chocolate chips.
When chips are soft, sprinkle with nuts.
Chill about 30 minutes until chocolate is set.
Cut into bars or break into pieces.
Makes 24 bars.

title: spaghetti sauce
directions: Cool tomatoes and pour off water.
Put all ingredients together.
Cook 1 1/2 hours or until as thick as you desire.
Stir occasionally.
(Cook uncovered.)

title: swiss bliss
directions: Spread center of 20-inch sheet of Reynolds Wrap with butter. Cut steak into serving portions.
Arrange in foil, slighlty overlapping portions.
Sprinkle with onion soup mix, mushrooms, green peppers and tomatoes.
Season.
Mix juice, A.1 sauce and cornstarch.
Pour over meat and vegetables.
Bring foil up over and double-fold edges to seal tightly.
Bake 2 hours in 365° oven. Roll back foil and sprinkle with parsley.

title: party meat balls
directions: Mix hamburger, salt, pepper, garlic salt, eggs and crackers. Form mixture into 2-inch balls.
Brown these meat balls and drain off grease.
Put balls into crock-pot or a large pan.
Add chili sauce and jelly over the meat balls.
Simmer for at least 2 hours. Serve hot in the sauce.
This recipe will make a crock-pot full.

title: pineapple-nut salad
directions: Bring pineapple juice to a boil; add lime Jell-O, stirring until dissolved.
Stir in sour cream.
Add pineapple and nuts. Put in 1 1/4-quart ring mold and refrigerate.
This will set in 1 1/2 hours.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: san francisco slaw
directions: In a small jar, combine the vinegar, soy sauce, ginger, garlic and 1/2 teaspoon salt; shake until the salt dissolves.
Add the oil; shake again to combine.
Shred the cabbage.
Cut the snow peas in half lengthwise.
Everything can be done a day ahead up to this point.
A few hours before serving, combine the cabbage, snow peas and the dressing in a bowl; toss to combine.
Sprinkle with the chopped peanuts.

title: mexican party dip
directions: Brown ground beef and sausage.
Put in a crock-pot.
Cut up Velveeta into cubes and put into crock-pot.
Add salsa and jalapenos.
Cook on High until Velveeta is melted; then turn to low.
Serve with tortilla chips.

title: lynchburg lemonade(alcoholic beverages)
directions: Combine all preceding.
Serve over crushed ice.
Garnish with slices of fresh lemon.

title: icebox lemon pie
directions: Crush 2 packages of graham crackers.
Melt 1 stick of butter or margarine and add to the crackers, making the pie crust.
Run in oven until light brown.

title: walnut crisps cookies
directions: Heat oven to 325°.
In medium size bowl, with electric beater, beat butter, sugar, egg, vanilla and salt until fluffy. Beat in flour.
Refrigerate dough, tightly wrapped, at least 1 hour.

title: artichoke dish
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
In a 1 1/2-quart casserole or quiche dish, combine all ingredients.
Bake, uncovered, 20 to 30 minutes or until slightly browned and bubbly.
Serve hot with crackers.

title: swiss vegetable medley
directions: Combine vegetables, soup, 1/2 cup cheese, sour cream, 1/2 of onions, pepper and pimiento.
Pour into 1-quart casserole.
Bake covered at 350° for 35 minutes.
Top with remaining cheese and onions and bake uncovered an additional 10 to 15 minutes or until onions are heated.

title: "fantastic fruit" muffins
directions: Sift flour, soda and salt together into large mixing bowl.
Add all other ingredients and stir well.
Place in container (gallon glass jar works well) and put into refrigerator.
Use as needed (makes 3 dozen or more).
This will keep up to six weeks.
The mixture turns darker and gets even better in time.
Bake at 400° for 20 minutes.

title: mandarin dessert
directions: Dissolve jello in water; add sherbet.
Add nuts and chill!

title: asparagus
directions: Mix eggs, milk, cheese and salt.
Add soft bread and pimentos; stir together.
Fold in asparagus.
Put in casserole.
Top with sesame seed and bake at 300° for 30 minutes.

title: xmas dip
directions: Cut onions and beef into small pieces.
For a good idea use scissors to cut them.
Then mix all ingredients.

title: cranberry butter
directions: Combine cranberries with sugar in small saucepan.
Cook over low heat 10 minutes or until berries have popped and mixture forms sauce.
Cool.
Blend cranberry mixture into soft butter with wooden spoon.
Pack into crocks or molds.
Chill.

title: hot bean dip
directions: Spread cream cheese on bottom of 9 x 13-inch pan.
Add kidney beans; sprinkle with taco seasoning.
Add shredded cheese.
Bake at 350° for 15 to 20 minutes or until bubbly.
Serve with nacho chips.
Enjoy!

title: barbecued squirrel
directions: Cut up the squirrels into serving size pieces.
Dredge in salted and peppered flour and brown in cooking oil.
Prepare barbecue sauce by combining remaining ingredients in a saucepan and cooking over low heat for 15 minutes.
Pour the sauce over the meat, cover and bake at 325° for 45 minutes or until tender. Uncover the pan and broil an additional 15 minutes.

title: cinnamon roll-ups
directions: Mix cream cheese and vanilla until well blended.
Combine cinnamon and sugar in mixing bowl.

title: crab cakes(without crab)
directions: Combine zucchini, breadcrumbs, mayonnaise, Old Bay seasoning, egg and onion.
Add salt and pepper to taste.
Shape into patties. Saute in oil until browned.
Makes 6 servings.

title: mama's pineapple pie
directions: Mix all ingredients together and pour in unbaked pie shell. Bake at 350° for about 45 minutes or until firm in middle.

title: tender pork chops
directions: On high heat, thoroughly brown both sides of chops.

title: cherry pie
directions: Cream together the cream cheese and powdered sugar.
Add whipped cream and blend.
Spread in bottom of pie shell.
Arrange cherry filling on top.
Chill until ready to serve.

title: strawberries and cream cake
directions: Break cake in chunks in a 9 x 13-inch pan or extra large Corning Ware bowl. Mix pudding and milk; add ice cream to pudding and pour over cake.
Mix jello and hot water.
Add frozen strawberries to jello.
Stir until partially set.
Pour over pudding and let set in refrigerator 2 to 3 hours until set.
Do not stir.

title: glazed ham loaf(4 to 5 servings)
directions: In medium bowl with fork, mix first 7 ingredients.
Shape mixture into 7 x 3-inch loaf in ovenproof pan.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Drain pineapple juice into 1-quart pan.
Stir into juice brown sugar and cornstarch.
Heat over medium heat, while stirring, until thickened and bubbly.
Remove from heat; stir in lemon juice and butter.

title: chicken and dressing
directions: Crumble corn bread in large mixing bowl, then add in all other ingredients.
Stir together, then place in large baking pan or dish.
Bake at 350° until slightly brown, 35 to 45 minutes.

title: seasoned crackers
directions: Mix all together in a medium size bowl until well coated and oil is absorbed.
Spread crackers out on paper towels to absorb excess oil.
Store in plastic container in dry place.

title: easy homemade bread
directions: Mix undissolved yeast with 2 cups flour, sugar, salt, shortening, then very hot tap water.
Beat 2 minutes at medium speed, add 1 more cup flour, beat until thick and elastic.
Add as much more flour as you can and beat with mixer.

When dough becomes too stiff to use mixer, add flour gradually and mix with spoon. Put dough on countertop and knead until smooth (5-10 minutes). Cover and leave on countertop and let rise for 30 minutes.
Divide dough in half and squeeze all the air out of the dough.
Place in greased bread pans, cover, let rise 45 minutes or until bread reaches the top of pan.
Bake 400 degrees about 20 minutes.

title: canned apple pie filling
directions: In a large pot, cook and stir together sugar, cornstarch, cinnamon, nutmeg, salt and water until bubbly.
Add lemon juice. Pack apples in quart jars.
Fill with hot syrup.
Seal.
Process in boiling water for 20 minutes.
One-quart of pie filling per 9-inch pastry crust.
Bake at 400° for 50 minutes.

title: crowned pork chops
directions: Salt and pepper pork chops on both sides and place in baking dish.
Mix corn, onion, bell pepper, eggs, salt and pepper and enough cracker crumbs for a medium thick consistency.
Spread over pork chops and bake approximately 1 hour in a 350° oven.

title: crock-pot chicken and rice
directions: Butter crock-pot.
Place in pot and mix: rice, milk and soups (undiluted).
Place chicken on top.
Sprinkle with onion soup mix. Cook on low for 8 hours or on high for 4 hours.

title: sweet potato pudding
directions: Beat
sweet potatoes with mixer; beat eggs until light. Add rest of ingredients and put in greased baking dish.

title: kielbasa and kraut
directions: Saute onion slightly.
Put all ingredients in large casserole and mix well.
Cover and bake for 1 1/2 hours in 325° oven, stirring occasionally.
Add more liquid if too thick.

title: herb batter bread
directions: *Rosemary, parsley, basil, dill and sage.
Mix whatever herbs are your favorite.

title: cooked salad dressing
directions: Mix sugar, flour, salt and mustard in saucepan. Gradually blend in milk and vinegar. Cook over direct low heat, stirring constantly until mixture thickens and boils. Boil 1 minute. Stir at least half of hot mixture into egg yolks. Stir into remaining hot mixture in saucepan. Bring to boil, stirring constantly. Boil 1 minute. Remove from heat and stir in butter. Cool. 2 cups dressing. When using mix with an equal amount of whipped cream, sour cream or mayonnaise.

title: chocolate yogurt cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Melt chocolate in water in 1 quart saucepan over low heat, stirring constantly.
Cool.
Stir in yogurt and set aside.
Cream butter.
Gradually add sugars.
Beat until light and fluffy.
Beat in eggs, one at a time.
Add vanilla.

title: lemon lush
directions: Spread into 9 x 13-inch pan oleo, flour and pecans.
Press down and bake at 350° for 15 minutes.
Mix the following and spread on baked crust:
cream cheese, powdered sugar and Cool Whip.
Next, mix pudding with the milk and put on top of cream cheese mixture.

title: cheese ball
directions: Mix all ingredients together. Wrap in plastic wrap and refrigerate at least 1 hour. Take out and roll in chopped nuts.

title: marinated vegetable salad
directions: Just before serving, pour Good Seasons (garlic salad dressing) over the vegetables.
Mix salad dressing according to package.

title: diet orange sunrise shake
directions: Combine all ingredients in a blender and whip to desired consistency.

title: impossible pie
directions: Put all ingredients together in electric blender, mix well. Pour in ungreased 9-inch glass pie plate.
Bake in a preheated oven at 400° for 10 minutes, reduce oven to 350° for 35 minutes. Do not open oven door until baking time is over.

title: easy dumplings
directions: Boil cut up chicken in salted water until tender.
Remove chicken from broth.
Dredge one tortilla in flour.
Cut in desired pieces and drop in broth.
Do not stir any more than necessary. Continue until you have used all the package of tortillas.
Debone chicken and add to dumplings.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Cook and bone chicken or chicken breasts.
Put in casserole dish.
Mix the soup and sour cream.
Pour over the chicken.
Melt the oleo.
Add the crushed crackers.
Saute. Put on top of chicken. Bake at 350° for about 45 minutes.

title: cherry-pineapple salad
directions: After mixing and spreading on top of congealed salad, sprinkle nuts on top.

title: spicy devil's food cake
directions: Blend well.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes in greased and floured 9-inch pans.

title: quick tomato sauce
directions: Combine all ingredients and simmer 10 minutes.
Tomato sauce is lower in fat than white sauce.

title: oatmeal pecan crispies
directions: Mix together all ingredients.
Drop on an ungreased cookie sheet with a medium sized spoon.
Space cookies about 2 inches apart.
Bake at 375° for 10 minutes.

title: mustard sauce
directions: Bring to a boil.

title: pumpkin chiffon pie
directions: Beat egg yolks and 1/2 cup sugar until thick. Add pumpkin, milk, salt and spices. Cook in double boiler until thick.

Soften gelatin in cold water; stir into hot mixture. Beat egg whites and 1/2 cup sugar into pumpkin mixture. Let mixture cool slightly. Pour cooled mixture into cooled baked shell and chill. Serve with sweetened whipped cream.

title: graham finale cherry pie
directions: To mix the pie, put chocolate squares into white syrup.
Put it in a warm, not hot, place to melt.
Brown butter in small pan, stirring, until golden brown.
Let butter cool, then add it to the chocolate mixture.
Beat egg yolks.
Add sugar and cream this together.
Mix a little milk with the flour and stir until smooth. Add this and the rest of the milk to the egg mixture.
Add chocolate syrup mixture slowly to the egg and flour.
Add vanilla.

title: mexican corn dip
directions: Combine all ingredients, except corn chips, in a bowl. Refrigerate to blend flavors.
Serve with corn chips.

title: hankins applesauce cake
directions: Mix butter, sugar and egg, then add applesauce, flour and spices.
Then add all together dates, soda and 1/2 cup hot water. Work dates until mushy (like potatoes).
Add 1 cup raisins, 1 cup pecans rolled in flour and vanilla.

title: ricotta and spinach quiche
directions: Use frozen or fresh 9-inch uncooked pie shell.
Squeeze all water out of spinach and chop; combine with Ricotta cheese, a little nutmeg and 1/2 cup Parmesan cheese.
Spread over bottom of pastry shell.
Beat eggs lightly; combine with milk and cream. Season with salt and pepper.
Pour over Ricotta and spinach. Sprinkle with remaining Parmesan cheese.
Bake at 375° for about 35 minutes until puffed and set.
Allow quiche to cool for 5 to 10 minutes.

title: divinity candy
directions: Cook first 3 ingredients until it spins a thread, then pour 1/2 of mixture in beaten egg whites.
Cook the other half until it hardens in cool water, then add the other half.
Beat until creamy.
Add vanilla and nuts, if desired.
Pour into buttered pan; cut into squares when cool.

title: prune cake
directions: Sift flour and spice.
Mix first 3 ingredients in mixing bowl with mixer.
Add flour with milk.
Fold in prunes and nuts.
Bake 1 hour at 300°.

title: quick lorraine
directions: Fry the bacon until crisp.
Drain and crumble.
Sprinkle bacon over pie shell.
Grate the cheese and sprinkle over bacon.

title: rockefeller roll cake
directions: This is a one pan cake (9 x 9 x 2-inch).
Do not stir ingredients but add in layers.
Melt butter in pan and sprinkle graham cracker crumbs over the butter; press down.
Add coconut, chocolate chips and nuts in layers, pouring milk over the nuts. Bake at 325° for 30 minutes.
Cool and cut in squares.

title: broccoli bread
directions: Combine all ingredients except oleo.
Pour half of melted oleo into 9 x 13-inch pan and half into mixture.
Pour mixture into pan and bake for 30 minutes at 350°.

title: meat pie roma
directions: Cook meat. Drain. add green pepper and cook until tender. Add sauce mix, paste and water, simmer 10 minutes. Line pan with biscuits. Press and seal. Sprinkle 1/4 c. parmesan cheese over biscuits. Fill with 1/2 meat mixture. Add 2 slices cheese. continue layering ingredients. Bake at 400° 15 to 20 minutes. In a 2 qt. casserole dish.

title: gma's tea ring
directions: Mix first 4 ingredients like pie crust.
Add next 3 ingredients (the yeast should go in warm milk mixture).
Let rise overnight in a cool place (not refrigerator).

title: blueberry salad
directions: Mix jello, water, pineapple and pie filling.
Congeal.
Mix cream cheese, sour cream and sugar.
Spread over congealed salad.

title: salmon log
directions: Drain, flake and remove skin and bones from salmon. Add the remaining ingredients (except pecans); mix thoroughly.
Form into a log or a ball.
At this point, you can either roll it in the pecans or garnish with some parsley sprigs.
Cover and refrigerate for at least 6 hours.
The longer it has to blend, the better.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Boil chicken breast until done.
Cut up chicken in small pieces.
Mix celery soup, chicken soup and the 2 cups of chicken broth together.
In a long baking dish layer chicken, dressing, eggs and soup.
Repeat so that you have two layers each.
Sprinkle some Pepperidge Farm dressing on top and bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: crawfish cornbread
directions: Saute onion and bell pepper in small amount of butter.
Cook until onion becomes transparent.
Add chopped jalapeno pepper. Set aside.
Mix in all ingredients, except crawfish.
Add cooked onion and pepper.
Stir in crawfish tails.
Pour in lightly greased pan.
Bake in preheated oven at 400° for 35 to 45 minutes.

title: layered lettuce salad
directions: Tear lettuce into small, bite size pieces and place in a 9 x 12-inch glass dish.
Layer rest of ingredients in order given. Add sugar to mayonnaise and spread on top as you would frosting. Top with grated cheese.
Cover and refrigerate for 8 to 12 hours. Will keep several days in refrigerator.
Serves 18 to 20.

title: italian popovers
directions: In a bowl, combine egg, milk, water, flour, dressing mix and salt.
Beat 1 1/2 minutes at medium speed.
Add oil.
Beat 30 seconds more.
Don't overbeat.
Pour batter into 6 greased muffin cups, 6 ounces each.
Bake at 475° for 15 minutes.
Reduce temperature to 350° for additional 25 minutes.

title: bean salad
directions: Cook macaroni as directed and drain well.
Put into bowl.
Add onion, pepper, celery, beans and cooked vegetables.
In small pan, heat sugar, flour, mustard and vinegar.
Bring to boil and cool completely, then pour over the combined ingredients.
Refrigerate. Keeps well in refrigerator.

title: pork chop casserole
directions: Spray Dutch oven with non-stick pan spray, place pork chops in bottom. Slice potatoes 1/4 inch, place over pork chops. Add chopped onion. In a bowl mix soups and water. Stir and pour over layers. Bake at 375 degrees until potatoes and meat are tender. If casserole gets dry before it is done, add a little water and finish baking.

title: stir-fried beef and broccoli
directions: Use
cube
steak,
amount
desired.
Dredge with flour, salt and
pepper.
Fry in large frying pan in small amount of cooking oil until brown.
Remove to baking dish.
Rinse frying pan
with enough water to cover the steak.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour.

title: easy key lime pie
directions: In medium bowl, stir together sweetened condensed milk, lime juice and food coloring.
Fold in whipped cream.
Pour into crust. Chill 3 hours or until set.

title: cheese dip for raw vegetables
directions: Blend all ingredients together in the blender.
Refrigerate overnight.
(This is very important.)
Serve raw vegetables.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Cover bottom of a 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan with Ritz crumbs.
Dot with butter.
Cover heavily with diced, cooked chicken.
Combine cream of mushroom soup, sour cream and chicken broth; pour over chicken and spread.
Top with Ritz crumbs.
Bake at 350° for about 30 minutes or until bubbly.

title: crumbly topped apple pie
directions: Stir sliced apples into butter to coat, then mix with sugar and cinnamon.
Mix with fingertips the flour, brown/white sugar and butter.

title: chili con carne
directions: Brown ground beef; drain. Season with taco seasoning. Layer in 9 x 13 pan the meat, Ranch Style beans, corn and cheese. Prepare corn muffin mix as directed and pour over meat mixture. Bake at temperature on corn muffin mix.

title: freezer slaw
directions: Boil
all ingredients together (except for the cabbage) for one minute.
Pour over cabbage.
Cool and freeze.
Remove from freezer on
the
day
it
is to be served.
Allow about 4 hours to thaw.

title: scalloped potatoes
directions: Put potatoes in a lecithin-prepared baking dish.
Liquefy all other ingredients and pour over potatoes.
Cover and bake 1 to 1 1/2 hours at 375°.
(Scalloped potatoes can take a long time so test for doneness.)
Remove cover, sprinkle with paprika and return to oven just long enough to brown.
Makes 6 servings.

title: banana nut bread
directions: Sift flour; measure and add other dry ingredients.
Beat eggs; add yolks, then add mashed bananas and shortening.
Stir all these ingredients together, then add whites of eggs, beaten.
Bake in well-greased loaf pan in moderate oven for 20 to 30 minutes.

title: de sha's corn bread
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Pour into greased pan.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes, or until a pick comes out clean.

title: baked pork chops and rice
directions: Brown pork chops for 20 minutes or until barely done.
Blend milk with soup.
Add water, onion, parsley, salt and pepper.
Mix with rice.
Pour into 9 x 13-inch baking dish.
Add chops.
Pour remaining mixture over top.
Cover with foil.
Bake for 1 hour at 350°.
Garnish with pears or apples, if desired.

title: bonquet
directions: Mix together thoroughly; refrigerate overnight.

title: pinch biscuits
directions: Make dough with all ingredients.
Pinch off a ball.
Place on greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 375° until brown on top.

title: crunched cranberry salad
directions: Bring pineapple juice and water to a boil.
Add raspberry Jell-O and dissolve.
Add pineapple, lemon juice, whole cranberries and walnuts.
Stir until smooth.
Let stand in refrigerator to soft stage, then fold in Cool Whip.
Pour into mold or dish.
Chill until firm.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: hot fudge pudding
directions: Mix together the first 6 ingredients.
Put in cake pan.
Mix together the brown sugar and cocoa; sprinkle on top.
Pour 2 1/2 cups hot water over top.
As it bakes, the sauce goes to the bottom.

title: my granny's rolls
directions: Mix 1 1/2 cups very warm water with 1 package of yeast.
Set aside.
In another large bowl, mix flour, salt, sugar and shortening.
Cut in ingredients until mixture is mixed well.
Add the yeast and water mixture and knead on a floured surface.
Pinch a ball of dough; dip in melted butter.
Place in baking pan and let raise until size is doubled.
Bake at 350° until brown.

title: zucchini bread
directions: Mix eggs, oil, sugar and 1 teaspoon vanilla until smooth.
Add dry ingredients and mix well.
Fold in grated zucchini and blend well.
Bake at 350° for one hour.

title: cream cheese, olive and walnut spread
directions: Using an electric mixer, beat cream cheese until creamy.
Stir in remaining ingredients.
Great for a tea sandwich filling or as a spread for crackers.
Makes 3 cups.

title: chinese fried rice
directions: Heat oil in a large skillet.
Toss in rice and cook until golden brown.
Add onions, salt and meat; mix well.
Hollow center and add eggs.
Scramble; stir in.
Add soy sauce.

title: yankee noodle bake
directions: Brown frankfurters and cook onion in butter or oleo until tender.
Combine with noodles, soup, water and mustard in 1 1/2-quart casserole; top with crumbs.
Bake in a 350° oven for 30 minutes.
Makes 4 servings.

title: taco salad(club member: kristi mayfield)
directions: Cook ground meat until slightly brown; drain. Mix other ingredients and add meat after it has cooled. Taco salad is best served while lettuce is still very crisp.

title: out of this world pie
directions: In double boiler, melt candy bars and marshmallows; mix in milk.
Cool.
Fold in chocolate mix; pour in pie shell and chill.

title: antipasto salad
directions: Remove sausage from casing and brown in skillet with small amount oil.
Cut salami into small cubes.
Cook shells until tender; drain and set aside.
Cook potatoes until done, but firm. Drain and refrigerate until cold and leave peelings on.
Quarter lengthwise.
Cut tomatoes into wedges.
Chop Fettechini peppers and onion.
Cube or dice zucchini in large pieces.
Chop garlic fine. In large pan or bowl, place potatoes, quartered lengthwise, salami, browned Italian sausage and cooked shells and set aside.

title: apricot chicken
directions: Preheat oven to 300°.
In a bowl, mix apricot preserves, dressing and soup mix.
Place the chicken breasts in a large ovenproof baking dish and pour apricot mixture over chicken.
Bake, uncovered, for 2 hours.
Yields 6 servings.

title: pecan pie
directions: In a bowl beat eggs.
Add margarine, vanilla, sugars and flour; stir together.
Add chopped nuts and pour into pie shell. Bake at 350° for 35 minutes.

title: nutmeg cookie logs
directions: Mix together all ingredients.
Press in bottom of pan to 1/2-inch.
Bake at 350° for 8 to 10 minutes.
When cool, put a butter icing on top.

title: chocolate squares
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Combine the granulated sugar, brown sugar, margarine, egg and vanilla.
Gradually add the flour and baking soda.
Spread batter in greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Sprinkle chips over the batter.
Place in oven for 2 minutes, remove and run knife through it to marbleize.
Return to oven and bake an additional 10 to 12 minutes.
Cut as it cools.

title: fantastic chicken
directions: Mix sauce together, spread over chicken pieces in baking dish with large spoon.
Save some sauce to spoon over the last 10 minutes of baking.
Bake at 350° for about 1 1/2 hours.

title: play dough
directions: Mix
dry
ingredients
in saucepan or electric skillet. Mix food
coloring
and
water.
Add water and food coloring; cook
2 minutes or until mixture peels away from sides of pan. Put on wax paper and knead for 5 minutes.
It is ready to play with when it cools.
Store in baggy or airtight container.

title: mini pineapple upside-down cakes
directions: Combine margarine and brown sugar. Spoon into bottom of approximately 20 greased and floured muffin tins. Drain pineapple and place on top of brown sugar. Prepare cake mix as directed. Pour muffin tins 2/3 full of cake mix. Bake at 350° for 20 minutes. Let cool for 5 minutes and turn out on rack to cool.

title: smooth pumpkin pie
directions: Preheat oven to 425°.
Combine ingredients in order given and pour into pie shell.
Bake 15 minutes, then reduce temperature of oven to 350° and bake additional 45 minutes or until knife inserted near center of pie comes out clean.
Cool and garnish with whipped topping (if desired).

title: crab soup
directions: Saute onion in butter.
Add tomato soup and half and half. Heat to a low boil.
Add crabmeat and sherry.
Remove from heat. Salt and pepper to taste.

title: lemon sour cream pound cake
directions: Cream butter and shortening; gradually add sugar, beating well at medium speed of an electric mixer.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating mixture after each addition.
Combine sour cream and milk; stir until smooth.
Combine flour and baking powder; add to creamed mixture alternately with sour cream mixture, beginning and ending with flour mixture.
Mix just until blended after each addition. Stir in lemon flavoring.
Pour batter into a greased and floured 10-inch tube pan.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour and 40 to 45 minutes or until a wooden pick inserted in center comes out clean.
Cool cake in pan 10 to 15 minutes; remove from pan and cool completely.

title: dad's b.b.q. sauce
directions: Mix all ingredients together and use as a marinade or sauce. Enjoy!!

title: weihnachten kuchen(christmas cake)
directions: Sift together the flour and baking powder.
Set aside.
Beat sugar and margarine until fluffy.
Add egg yolks and vanilla to the above.
Add the milk alternately to sugar/egg mixture on low speed.
Turn the batter into 2 greased and floured 9 x 1 1/2-inch round baking pans.

title: louise's holiday salad
directions: Combine the first 10 ingredients together and mix well in a large salad bowl.
Add 1 cup of boiling water to each package of jello.
Add 1/4 cup of cold water for each package.
Chill jellos until set.
Cut in small cubes.
Add to other ingredients.
Put in a large glass salad bowl.
Sprinkle 2 ounces of coconut on top. Add 1 dozen pecan halves.
Refrigerate for about 24 hours.

title: mexican rare bit
directions: Add tomatoes, celery, onion and green pepper to bacon and ground meat.
Simmer for 1/2 hour.
Taste and season.
Put on platter.
Cook 1 pound spaghetti.
Wash and drain.
Spread over meat mixture.
Cut up 1 pound sharp cheese and spread over spaghetti.
Put in oven long enough to melt cheese.

title: mom's curried zucchini soup
directions: Saut washed and diced zucchini with sliced onions in 2 Tbsp. of butter, until soft.
Add stock and cook 20 minutes.
Slice tomatoes and saut briefly in remaining butter.
Add to vegetables and bring to a boil.
Mix flour, curry powder, ginger, salt and cayenne with water and add to soup.
Simmer 6 minutes.
Transfer 2 cups at a time to blender and puree.
Transfer back to pan and reheat.
Add salt and pepper to taste.

title: spinach lasagne
directions: Make this double amount and freeze half.
Freezes beautifully. Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease large lasagne pan(s).

title: vegetable casserole
directions: Mix Veg-All, Cheddar, cheeses, onion, water chestnuts, mayonnaise, salt and pepper together well.
Put in greased casserole dish.
Bake 20 minutes at 350° or until bubbly.
Mix together crushed crackers and melted margarine.
Spread over top of casserole.
Bake 10 minutes or until golden brown.

title: cranberry delight
directions: Whip cream and sugar in a chilled bowl until stiff peaks form. Mix in remaining ingredients.
Pour into a loaf pan and freeze. To serve, thaw slightly and cut into slices.
Serve as a dessert or salad on lettuce leaves.
Makes 8 to 10 servings.

title: homemade chili
directions: Cook hamburger meat and sausage.
Add them to kidney beans and pintos.
Cut up onion; add to mixture.
Add tomato sauce, tomatoes and Chili-O mix.
Simmer for 2 hours.

title: black walnut cake
directions: Mix ingredients like any other cake, adding raisins and nuts last.
Bake in layers at 350° for about 35 minutes.
Put together with Divinity Filling or any white filling.

title: tutti-fruitti log roll
directions: Blend first four ingredients (cheese grated).
Add finely chopped raisins, dates and apricots.
Shape in log roll in aluminum foil.
Chill well.
Roll in finely chopped cherries and walnuts. Place roll in clean aluminum foil and chill until ready to serve. Place in center of serving tray, surrounded by Waverly crackers.

title: italian cream cake
directions: Beat oleo and shortening in mixer.
Add sugar and beat well. Add egg yolks, one at a time.
Sift flour and soda together; add alternating with buttermilk.
Add vanilla.
Fold in coconut and pecans, then add beaten egg whites.
Pour into 3 (8 or 9-inch) tins and bake at 350° for 45 minutes.
Frost with Cream Cheese Frosting.

title: cheddar baked potato slices
directions: Mix together soup, paprika and pepper.
In a greased 2-quart rectangular baking dish, arrange potatoes in overlapping rows. Sprinkle shredded cheese over slices.
Spoon soup mixture over cheese.
Cover with foil and bake at 400° for 45 minutes.
Uncover and bake 10 minutes or until potatoes are fork-tender.
Makes 6 servings.

title: peanut butter cookies
directions: Mix flour, salt and baking soda; set aside.

title: cheese spread
directions: In a saucepan over medium heat, cook sugar, flour, butter, vinegar, egg, milk and salt until thick.
Cool.
Add cheese, eggs and onions.

title: football party dip
directions: Blend cream cheese and Ranch dip.
Stir in bell peppers. Drain and dry olives and chilies.
Add to mixture.
Chill an hour. Using a spatula, form a football shape on a platter.
Chill 4 hours or overnight.
Decorate football using vegetables slices and cheese strips.
Serve with assorted breads, crackers and vegetables.

title: old fashion sponge candy
directions: Combine sugar, syrup and vinegar.
Cook, without stirring, to 300° on a candy thermometer.
Remove from heat quickly.
Stir in baking soda.
Mix well.
Place in buttered pan.
Cool and break into pieces.

title: grilled tomatoes
directions: Wash and core tomatoes.
Slice in half across the "equator." Set on a baking or broiler pan, cut sides up.
Allow 2 small or 1 large half per person.
Sprinkle with bread crumbs, Parmesan, oregano, salt and pepper and top each one with a thin pat of butter.
Broil at 550° until hot and lightly browned, about 8 to 10 minutes.
Watch after 5 minutes, so topping will not burn and blacken.

title: ginger jellies
directions: Spray nonstick 8-inch square pan.
Reserve 1/2 cup applesauce. Combine remaining sauce, ginger, sugar and salt in pot.
Bring to boil and cook 25 minutes. Stir in lemon juice, gelatin and reserved applesauce.
Add coloring.
Cook 10 minutes.
Pour into prepared pan.
Smooth top and cool completely.
Cut into 64 squares.
Coat with 1/3 cup sugar.
Layer jellies between plastic wrap in airtight container and store in refrigerator.

title: have it your way
directions: Get bread out.
Top with any or all things taken out.

title: david's fat-free vegetable soup
directions: Combine all ingredients, bring to a boil.
Reduce to low-medium heat and simmer until vegetables are tender.

title: fluffy dumplings
directions: Sift together flour, baking powder and salt.
Combine milk and salad oil or shortening.
Add to dry ingredients, stirring just until flour is moistened.
Cook dumplings atop hot stew.

title: haystacks
directions: Melt morsels and add other ingredients.
Place on foil in teaspoon amounts.

title: oatmeal cookies
directions: Cook sugar, cocoa, milk and margarine 1 minute (may have to cook longer).
Add peanut butter, oatmeal and vanilla.
Beat until it begins to thicken.
Spoon out on wax paper.
Let set until firm.

title: crab dip
directions: Melt butter and cream cheese in a frying pan.
Add all other ingredients and simmer 5 minutes.
Serve warm with crackers.

title: sweet and sour shrimp
directions: Heat salad oil until hot.
Add celery, peppers and onion; brown lightly.
Work fast and add cornstarch and tomato juice slowly until thickened.
Add brown sugar and lemon juice; cook 10 minutes. Add shrimp and serve over cooked rice.

title: mountain high cake with frosting(mountain dew cake)
directions: Mix all ingredients together using Mountain Dew as the liquid. Bake at 350° for 30 minutes in 3 layers (9-inch pans).

title: banana cool whip cake
directions: Mix cake according to directions on box.
Bake two round layers.
Cool.
Top with sliced bananas.
Spread Cool Whip on top of bananas.
Add second layer.
Put Cool Whip on top and sides. Top with sliced bananas.
Refrigerate.

title: strawberry pie
directions: Line a cooled pastry shell with berries, except for 1 cup. Simmer the 1 cup berries with water for 3 to 4 minutes.
Combine cornstarch and sugar and add to cooked berries.
Cook until the syrup is clear and thick, stirring constantly.
Add lemon juice. Cool slightly and pour mixture over berries in pastry shell. Chill and serve with whipped cream.

title: yale beets
directions: Drain beets.
Combine sugar, cornstarch and salt in saucepan. Add and stir in vinegar and orange juice.
Place over medium heat and cook, stirring constantly, until the mixture comes to a boil and thickens and becomes clear.
Stir in beets and butter; heat thoroughly.
Yields 4 servings.

title: cowboy cookies
directions: Blend together first 3 ingredients.
Add eggs and vanilla. Blend and sift into the batter the next 3 ingredients.
Blend in oatmeal and chocolate chips.
Grease cookie sheets.
Bake at 350° for 8 minutes for chewy cookies or 10 to 12 minutes for crunchy cookies.

title: dump cobbler
directions: Melt oleo in 9 x 13-inch casserole dish.
Mix flour, sugar and milk together.
Batter will be lumpy.
Pour over melted oleo.
Add peaches and juice.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes.
Any fruit can be used.
Good and easy.

title: harvest table apple pie
directions: Prepare crust and roll out half for bottom crust.
Fit in 9 inch pan.
Peel, core and slice apples.
Arrange in crust.
Combine cornstarch, cinnamon, salt, sugar, margarine and Karo syrup.
Pour over apples.
Roll out pastry for top crust.
Cut slits and place over apples.
Fold edges under, seal, and flute.
Bake in 425° oven 45 minutes or until crust is browned and apples are tender.
Remove from oven.
Spread topping over top of pie. return to oven for 10 minutes or until topping is bubbly.
(Place large pan under pie pan to catch any topping that may run off.)
Mix brown sugar, flour, syrup, margarine and nuts and put on top of pie.
(Use the Karo Blue Label syrup.)

title: sour cream-coconut cake
directions: Prepare cake mix according to package directions, making two 8-inch layers.
When completely cool, split both layers.

title: flan
directions: In a heavy saucepan, cook the sugar until it caramelizes.
Pour into a two-quart mold; swirl to cover the bottom and sides (be careful or you will get a bad burn!)
Set aside.
Preheat oven to 375°.
Mix the eggs in a bowl; add condensed milk, milk and vanilla.
Pour the mixture into the caramelized pan; cover.
Set the pan into a larger pan in the oven; cover and pour hot water into the outer pan to reach two-thirds of the way up on the side of the mold.
Bake 1 hour.
Remove from the oven; let cool to room temperature.
Refrigerate overnight.
To serve, run a knife around the edge of the mold; invert the mold onto a plate.
Serves eight.

title: mock enchilada
directions: Fry meat and onion; add salt and pepper to taste.
Add beans and chili and heat.
Put layer of Fritos in baking dish, then meat and beans, then cheese.
Repeat.
Top with crushed Fritos.
Bake at 350° about 20 minutes, or until cheese melts.

title: oyster mushroom stuffing
directions: Using reserved bacon
fat,
saute
onion
and celery in skillet until onions
are
transparent,
but
not
brown.
Add sliced mushrooms; saute 3 minutes longer, stirring constantly. Add sauteed vegetables	to
bread crumbs in large mixing bowl. Add oysters, salt,
bacon,
paprika
seasoning and broth; toss well with a fork.
Stuffs a 12 to 15 pound turkey

title: cinnamon swirl bread
directions: Grease loaf pan.
In large bowl, mix 1/4 cup sugar, yeast, salt and 1 cup flour.
Heat milk, water and 1/4 cup butter until lukewarm.
Add to flour mixture; beat 1 minute.
Add 1 cup additional flour and the egg; beat 2 minutes.
With spoon, stir in 1 to 1 1/2 cups flour until dough holds shape.
Turn out onto floured board.
Knead 8 minutes or until smooth and elastic.
Cover with waxed paper and towel.
Let rest 20 minutes.
Punch dough down and roll into 8 x 15-inch pan.
Brush with melted butter and sprinkle with 2 tablespoons sugar and cinnamon.
Roll up jelly roll fashion.
Seal ends; place seam side down in loaf pan.
Cover with plastic wrap and refrigerate 2 to 4 hours.

title: pink salad
directions: Mix together.
Chill in refrigerator until ready to serve.

title: sweet potato balls
directions: Mix butter, pepper, salt and potatoes.
Shape in balls.
Roll in flour, sprinkle with nuts and dip in melted butter.
Arrange in a shallow pan, and bake for 15 minutes or until brown, 1/4 teaspoon nutmeg may be added.

title: hot pecan spread
directions: Set cream cheese out to soften.
Combine cream cheese and milk; mix well.
Stir in cubed beef, green pepper, onion and seasonings; blend well.
Fold in sour cream.
Spoon into a 9 x 13-inch pan.
When ready to serve, bake at 350° for 20 minutes. Top with chopped pecans that have been sauteed in 6 tablespoons oleo.
Serve hot with Wheat Thins.

title: oven kalua pig
directions: Rub salt and pepper into the pork butt.
Add on the garlic pieces.
Wrap very tightly with aluminum foil.
Bake in a 350° oven for 3 to 4 hours, until the meat falls apart (palahe).
Shred the meat.
Add liquid smoke.
Add salt, if needed.
Add the konbu and let simmer in the oven for about 15 minutes before serving.

title: daing na bangus(seasoned milkfish)
directions: Cut the fish lengthwise along the back.
Lay flat, skin side down, in a shallow dish.
Combine all other ingredients, except oil and flour; pour over the fish.
Let stand, covered, in the refrigerator for at least 1 day, turning once or twice.
Drain; dry thoroughly with paper towel.
Sprinkle all over with flour and fry in hot oil until golden brown on both sides (about 10 minutes).

title: easy turtle brownies
directions: Beat together half of the evaporated milk, all the butter and all the cake mix.
Press half of the dough into the bottom of a greased and floured 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 5 minutes.

title: terrific dessert
directions: Pinch cake into bite-size pieces in large bowl. Chop the candy bars. (Freeze them for 1 hour before chopping to make chopping easier.)
Add candy and Cool Whip with the cake and mix well.
Place in 9 x 13-inch dish and freeze.
Thaw just before you are ready to serve.

title: chicken parmesan
directions: Mix ingredients.
Spoon over chicken. Bake at 375° for 45 to 50 minutes.

title: praline cookie bars
directions: Grease jelly roll pan (approximately 15 x 10 x 1-inch).
Line bottom with whole graham crackers.
Combine brown sugar and butter in saucepan.
Over medium heat, bring to a rolling boil. Stirring, cook for 1 1/2 minutes.
Remove from heat.
When mixture stops bubbling, stir in nuts.
Spoon onto crackers.
Bake at 350° for 10 minutes.

title: raspberry squares
directions: Work flour, butter and sugar together with hands.
Put 2/3 of mixture into a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Spread one pound jar of raspberry preserves over mixture.
Sprinkle remaining crumbs on top.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes or until slightly brown.

title: bibb lettuce dressing
directions: Mix all ingredients together in a large container or glass jar.
Keeps well, but recipe can be easily halved.

title: chocolate cake
directions: Mix all ingredients thoroughly.
Bake in greased pans for 30 to 35 minutes at 350° until tests done.

title: orange julius
directions: Combine in blender and cover.
Blend 30 to 45 seconds.
Serve immediately.

title: scalloped corn
directions: Mix all ingredients together except for the grated cheese into a large casserole dish.
Sprinkle cheese on top.
Bake at 350° for about 45 minutes or until consistency desired.
I usually bake it around 50 to 55 minutes.

title: dianne's best frittata
directions: Heat butter in a 10-inch saute pan with ovenproof handle.
Add potatoes that have been soaked in cold water 15 minutes and dried. Add onion, salt and pepper.
Cover and simmer about 15 minutes, until potatoes are almost tender.
Carefully turn the potatoes. Distribute zucchini slices over potatoes and re-cover the pan.

title: 7 layer casserole
directions: Layer ingredients in a 2-quart baking dish in this order: rice, corn and its liquid, 1 teaspoon salt, 1/8 teaspoon pepper, 1/2 can tomato sauce, 1/2 cup water, onion, ground beef, 1/2 teaspoon salt, 1/8 teaspoon pepper, remaining tomato sauce and 1/4 cup water.
Cover meat evenly with the bacon strips.
Cover casserole.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Uncover; continue to bake for 20 minutes, or until bacon is crisp.
Makes 4 servings.

title: chicken jambalaya
directions: Cut up chicken and brown in salad oil.
Remove chicken and oil from pot.
Return 3 tablespoons oil to pot.
Add onion, celery, garlic, green pepper and tomato.
Cover and stir frequently. Brown slowly.
Return chicken to mixture.
Add rice, water, salt and pepper.
Mix well.
Cook on medium heat 15 minutes using cover and stirring often.
Lower heat and steam 45 minutes or until rice is cooked but not gummy.
Remove cover and stir every 10 minutes or so to ensure cooking evenly.

title: egg filling for pita bread
directions: Blend cream cheese, mayonnaise and seasonings.	Stir in remaining ingredients.
Regular bread may be used for a sandwich.

title: apple and herb stuffing
directions: In large skillet, cook celery and onion in margarine until tender.
Add water and bouillon.
Cook unti bouillon dissolves. In large bowl, combine remaining ingredients.
Add bouillon mixture.
Mix well.
Loosely stuff turkey just before roasting. Place remaining stuffing in greased baking dish.
Cover.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes or until hot.

title: dode's scalloped corn
directions: Mix all ingredients and pour into greased casserole dish. Evenly spread bread or cracker crumbs over top.
Bake, uncovered, at 350° for 1 hour.
Can be refrigerated without bread crumbs if fixed earlier.
Uncover; spread topping and bake.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: frozen fruit salad
directions: Combine cream cheese and mayonnaise; blend until smooth.
Fold in whipped cream, fruit and marshmallows.
Pour into a quart refrigerator tray.
Freeze firm.
Serves 8 to 10.

title: vegetable dip
directions: Mix all ingredients and serve chilled with fresh raw vegetables.
Serves 8-10.

title: breakfast casserole
directions: Cut up bread in bottom of 9 x 13 baking dish.
Slice cheese over top.
Fry pork sausage and drain.
Pour crumbled sausage over top of cheese.
Mix eggs and 1 cup milk.
Pour over top.
Cover, refrigerate overnight.

title: cranberry mold
directions: Dissolve Jell-O in water.
Add cranberry sauce and stir until blended.
Chill until partially thick.
Add sliced bananas and drained fruit cocktail.
Chill until firm.
Great with holiday turkey dinners!!!

title: extra easy cobbler
directions: Melt butter in 8 x 8 x 2-inch cake pan.
Sift together the sugar, flour, salt and baking powder.
Add milk and stir to blend. Add butter, leaving a coating in the pan.
Stir together and pour back into pan.
Add fruit to top of batter, but do not stir.
Bake at 375° for about 40 minutes until pudding rises to top and browns as a crust.

title: pineapple cheesecake
directions: Cook until thickened and set aside.

title: spaghetti bean soup(microwave)
directions: In a 2-quart microwavable casserole with lid, mix all ingredients together, except 1 cup V-8 juice.
Cover and microwave 15 minutes, stopping every 5 minutes to stir.
Add V-8 juice; cover and microwave 5 minutes or until noodles are soft.

title: fresh apple cake
directions: Peel and chop apples; set aside.
Pour oil in large bowl. Add eggs and sugar; beat well.
Mix flour, salt, soda and baking powder; gradually add to creamed mixture.
Add vanilla, apples and nuts.
Grease and flour a 13 x 9-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: sukiyaki
directions: In bowl, combine soy sauce, sugar and broth.
Prepare spinach. Snip into small pieces.
Slice scallions into 2-inch lengths. Cut onion into 1/4-inch slices.
Heat oil in wok or skillet.
Add scallions, onion, mushrooms, bamboo shoots.
Pour sauce mix over it and cook on high for 4 minutes.
Push spinach and meat onto vegetables in wok.
Simmer for 2 minutes.
Push spinach and meat down into sauce.
Cook 3 minutes. Serve on top of hot rice. Serves 4 to 5.

title: corn relish
directions: Cook together, slow, for half hour. Put in jars and seal.

title: alabama biscuits
directions: Dissolve yeast in warm buttermilk.
Set aside.
Sift together flour, salt, soda and sugar.
Cut in shortening.
Add buttermilk and yeast mixture to sifted ingredients.
Stir until well blended. Knead and roll to 1/4-inch thick.
Cut with biscuit cutter on greased baking sheet. Place biscuits so they are touching.
Butter the tops of biscuits. Place a layer of biscuits on top of buttered ones.
Let rise at room temperature for 1 hour.
Bake at 425° until golden brown.

title: creole lima beans
directions: Fry bacon until crisp; then dice.
Cook onion until brown. In a saucepan, pour in tomatoes; add flour, salt, pepper, bay leaf and paprika.
When mixture begins to thicken, add bacon and onion. Finally add lima beans.
Cook over medium heat until thickened.

title: honey curry chicken
directions: Serve this dish with rice, topped with glaze mixture from baking dish.

title: raisin bars
directions: Combine raisins and water; bring to a boil.
Remove from heat. Stir in oil.
Cool to lukewarm and stir in sugar and egg.
Sift dry ingredients together; beat into raisin mix and stir in nuts. Pour into greased 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan.
Bake at 375° for 20 minutes or until done.
Yield:
2 dozen.

title: cherry nut muffin
directions: Mix dry ingredients.
Combine egg and milk.
Add fat to dry ingredients.
Stir until dry ingredients are barely moistened. Fill muffin pan 2/3 full of batter.
Bake 20 to 25 minutes until brown.

title: pretzel pile-ups
directions: Combine the crushed pretzels and peanuts in a large bowl.
Set bowl aside.
Combine sweetened condensed milk, chocolate pieces and butterscotch pieces in a saucepan.
Cook over low heat, stirring constantly, about 5 minutes or until the pieces are melted.
Remove the pan from the heat.
Stir in vanilla.
Pour the chocolate mixture over the pretzel mixture in the bowl.
Stir until thoroughly coated.
Drop by rounded spoonfuls onto waxed paper.
Cool until firm.
Makes 36.

title: blueberry pie squares
directions: On bottom of oblong Pyrex pan (not greased), put blueberry pie mix.
Over this, put white cake mix, dry from box.
Sprinkle nuts over and dot with margarine.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes.

title: inside outside ravioli
directions: Brown ground beef, onion and garlic.
Cook spinach, drain, reserve liquid and add water to measure 1 cup.
Cook shell-roni. Add to meat mixture, spaghetti sauce, tomato sauce, 1 cup spinach liquid and season with salt and pepper.
Simmer 10 minutes.

title: oyster cracker snack
directions: Mix oil, dressing and dill weed, then add crackers and mix carefully.
Bake at 250° for 1 hour; turn every 15 minutes.

title: chicken velvet soup
directions: Blend butter and flour well.
Add warm milk, chicken stock and warm cream.
After cooking well, add 1 quart chicken stock, cooked chicken, salt and pepper.
Yield:
2 1/2 quarts.

title: kielbasi beans
directions: Fry bacon.
Mix all ingredients together in a large casserole dish.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour, covered and 1 hour, uncovered.

title: volcano cake
directions: Melt a stick of butter in a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Cover with pecans and coconut.
Mix cake mix according to box and pour over mixture.
Mix the cream cheese, 1/2 stick butter and confectioners sugar.
Drop over cake mixture.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: oatmeal cookies
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Drop by teaspoonful on cookie sheet, bake at 375 degrees for 10 minutes.

title: quick and easy rice pudding
directions: Combine all ingredients except vanilla in a saucepan; cook over medium heat until thickened, 25 to 30 minutes, stirring often.
Pour into serving dish.
Serve hot or cold.
Makes six 1/2-cup servings.

title: hot cocoa
directions: Mix vanilla and peppermint together and sprinkle over sugar and salt mixture.
Stir until well absorbed by sugar mixture.
Add cocoa; mix well.
Add dry milk; mix well.
Store in airtight container.
To serve, add 2 heaping tablespoons of cocoa mixture to one cup of boiling water.
Enjoy!

title: seven layer casserole
directions: Place in 2-quart casserole in order given.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour, covered, and for 1/2 hour, uncovered, or until bacon is crisp.

title: chocolate roll
directions: Melt margarine	and
chocolate	together.
Cool and add the beaten egg.
Mix in the powdered sugar, nuts and marshmallows. Put coconut
in
bottom
of
long
narrow
pan and roll mixture into a roll in it.	Slice and serve.

title: frozen dessert
directions: Place 2 cups crushed vanilla wafer crumbs in bottom of a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Melt butter and chocolate in a double boiler.
Add powdered sugar and blend.
Add egg yolks, one at a time and heat thoroughly.
Fold in beaten egg whites.
Add vanilla.
Spoon chocolate mixture gently over crushed wafers.
Slice ice cream approximately 1-inch thick and set on top of chocolate layer. Sprinkle remaining wafers on top.
Freeze until firm.

title: quick cream-filled strawberries
directions: Wash and dry strawberries. From point end, split each berry into quarters, but do not cut through stem! Refrigerate. Combine cream and wine in food processor. Allow machine to run without pusher until partially whipped. Add powdered sugar and complete whipping process, being careful not to overwhip. Serve within 4 to 6 hours.

title: strawberry bread
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Combine dry ingredients.
Add eggs, oil, drained strawberries and nuts.
Stir just to moisten and mix. Spoon batter into two greased 9 x 5 x 3-inch loaf pans or 6 small loaf pans.
Bake for 50 to 70 minutes.

title: apple crisp
directions: Mix 1/2 cup sugar, cinnamon, water and lemon juice.
Pour over apples and mix.
Cut up rest for topping.
Bake at 375° for 45 minutes.

title: chicken and doritos
directions: Put a layer of Doritos, layer of chicken and layer of cheese. Mix soups and broth; pour over the layers.
Then put layer of cheese and Doritos last.
Bake for 30 minutes at 350° in oven.

title: green bean casserole
directions: Mix beans with soup; add almonds and onion rings.
Reserve a few onion rings to garnish top.
Bake in 350° oven for 45 minutes.

title: hot chicken salad
directions: Mix together and place in greased 9 x 13-inch pan.

title: papa palmisano's snack'in crackers
directions: Mix ingredients with oil and put in microwave 2 minutes. Pour over crackers.
Mix well.
Then snack away!

title: cheese escalloped corn
directions: Beat egg in mixing bowl.
Stir in remaining ingredients. Spoon in greased, 1-quart casserole.
Bake, uncovered, in 350° oven for about 35 minutes.

title: strawberry jello salad
directions: In medium bowl, add hot water to Jell-O.
Stir to dissolve. Add in frozen strawberries and stir well.
Pour half of mixture into Jell-O mold and put in refrigerator until it gels (30 to 60 minutes required).
Set other half of mixture aside at room temperature until it starts to gel and then add banana and pineapple; stir.
When Jell-O in mold is set, spread with sour cream.
Top with other half of Jell-O mixture and return to fridge to harden.

title: angel fruit pies
directions: Mix Cool Whip and milk together.
Add fruit and lemon juice to mixture.
Pour into pie crusts; chill.
Makes 2 pies.

title: amish fruit swirl coffeecake
directions: Mix all ingredients, except pie filling and glaze.
Spread 2/3 of batter in a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Spread pie filling over batter, then drop remaining batter by tablespoons.
Bake until lightly brown, 25 to 30 minutes, at 350°.
Drizzle with glaze while warm. Yields 12 to 18 servings.

title: shrimp dip
directions: Combine ingredients. Serve with crackers.

title: microwave mango chutney
directions: Peel, half and seed mango and cut into 1/2-inch or smaller cubes.
Combine mango with all other ingredients in deep 1 1/2-quart micro-safe casserole; stir thoroughly.

title: mexican chicken patties(in honor of counterpart maid)
directions: In small bowl, combine chili and cheese.
Put in small saucepan and heat until hot, stirring as often as needed.
Set aside.

title: banana bread
directions: Beat bananas, sugar, butter and eggs.
Add dry ingredients and mix until blended.
Add nuts.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: squash casserole
directions: Cook squash and drain.
Add butter, salt, pepper, pimentos and milk and mix, then add well beaten eggs, onions, cheese and cracker crumbs.
Pour into greased casserole dish and bake at 375° for about 40 minutes.

title: zucchini squares
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Grease oblong pan (13 x 9 x 2-inch).
Mix all ingredients and spread in pan.
Bake until golden brown, about 25 minutes.
Cut into small squares.
Makes about 4 dozen appetizers.

title: one skillet spaghetti
directions: Cook and stir ground beef and onions in large skillet until beef is brown.
Drain off fat.
Stir in tomatoes (with liquid) and remaining ingredients except Cheddar cheese, break up tomatoes. Heat mixture to boiling.
Reduce heat.
Cover and simmer, stirring occasionally, until spaghetti is tender, about 30 minutes.
Add small amount of water if necessary.
Sprinkle with cheese.
Cover and heat until cheese is melted.
Makes 7 servings.

title: strawberry-french toast sandwiches
directions: Spread 1 tablespoon of cream cheese on each of six slices of bread.
Spread 1 1/2 teaspoons jam over the cream cheese.
Top with remaining bread slices to make sandwiches.

title: fruit juice cooler
directions: Combine all ingredients in a large pitcher; mix well.
Pour over ice cubes in serving glasses.

title: shrimp-tomatoes
directions: Cut up boiled shrimp.
Empty centers of tomatoes.
Fill cups (tomatoes) with a mixture of mayonnaise and shrimp.
Serve on a bed of lettuce.

title: hanky-panky
directions: Brown beef and sausage.
Drain.
Add to meat the remaining ingredients except for the bread.
Heat and stir until cheese is melted.
Spread on bread.
Bake at 350° for 10 to 12 minutes.

title: harvard beets
directions: Blend cornstarch, sugar, salt, beet juice and vinegar. Pour over beets in a casserole dish. Add butter. Bake in oven for a few minutes.

title: cheddar scallion cornbread
directions: Preheat oven to 400°. In a small skillet, melt butter over medium heat. Cook scallions until soft, about 3 minutes.

title: chocolate gravy
directions: Mix and add cold water; cook over medium heat until thick!

title: wintery day bean soup
directions: Try to use at least 5 varieties of beans:
Great Northern, navy, black, pinto and red or green split peas.
Rinse beans and place in Dutch oven.
Cover with water; add salt and soak overnight.
Drain; add 2 quarts water and meat.
Simmer for 3 hours.
Add onion, garlic, chili powder, tomatoes and lemon juice. Simmer 45 minutes.
Add salt and pepper to taste.

title: pumpkin pie dessert squares
directions: Reserve 1 cup of yellow cake mix.
Combine remaining cake mix, 1/2 cup margarine and 1 egg.
Press into greased (bottom only) of 9 x 13-inch pan.
Mix pumpkin pie mix, pumpkin spice, brown sugar, 2 eggs and milk together and spread on crust mixture.

title: congealed strawberry salad
directions: Mix Jell-O and pineapple in large saucepan.
Heat on stove until Jell-O dissolves (do not boil).
Allow to cool.
Mix in buttermilk, pecans and Cool Whip until blended.
Pour into an 8 x 12-inch dish or clear glass bowl.
Refrigerate.
May use other flavors of Jell-O and/or fruit.

title: chocolate eclairs
directions: Mix 2 boxes pudding with 3 cups milk; stir in Cool Whip.
Line 9 x 13-inch pan with whole graham crackers.
Add 1/2 pudding mix, add another layer crackers, add remaining pudding.
Add another layer of crackers. Put opened can of icing in microwave for 45 seconds.
Pour over crackers and pudding.
Store overnight in refrigerator.

title: cream puff dessert
directions: Boil together the oleo and water; add flour.
Mix well.
Cool slightly.
Stir in eggs, one at a time.
Mix well and spread into a 9 x 13 inch greased pan.
Bake at 400 degrees for 30 min.
Cool. To pudding add milk and softened cream cheese.
Mix together with a wire whip until lumps disappear.
Pour into cream puff crust. Spread cool whip on top of pudding.
Drizzle Hershey's syrup on top for color.
Refrigerate.
Keeps well for days.

title: bread and butter pickles
directions: Combine salt, cucumbers and onions.
Weigh down with ice.
Let stand 3 to 4 hours.
Drain.
Add all of the rest of the ingredients in a large pot.
Add onion-cucumber mixture and bring to a boil.
Cook 3 to 5 minutes until cucumbers look glassy. Pack into clean, hot jars.
Process in boiling water bath 5 minutes.
Yields 5 to 6 pints.

title: bonbons
directions: Roll wafers until very fine.
Combine all ingredients.
Roll into small balls and dip into melted chocolate over low heat with 1 tablespoon shortening.
Refrigerate overnight.
Serve cold.

title: oven fried chicken
directions: Dip salted chicken in margarine, then roll the chicken in the bread crumbs and cheese mixture.
Place in a baking pan.
Cover with foil paper; bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: kahlua cake
