directions: Follow box recipe for cake (make a sheet cake).
Let it cool, then cut in half.
Place it in a large, clear bowl.
Pour 1/2 cup Kahlua, half of the pudding and 2 Skor bars (broken up) over the cake.
Top with Cool Whip and layer again with 1/2 cup Kahlua, half of the pudding and 2 Skor bars.
Top off with Cool Whip; sprinkle with 1 Skor bar on top.

title: mandarin orange cake
directions: Mix ingredients together by hand. Beat with mixer for 3 minutes.
Pour into well-greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 325° for 40 minutes.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Cook broccoli 5 minutes.
Set aside.
Mix other ingredients together.
Place broccoli in buttered casserole.
Pour mixture over broccoli.
Top with crackers and fine cheese.
You may omit the crackers, if you wish; however, if you use them be sure they are rolled fine.
Bake at 350° for about 35 minutes.

title: pumpkin delight
directions: Mix together all ingredients, except the cake mix.
Beat well and pour into a buttered 9 x 13-inch pan.
Sprinkle the dry cake mix on top of the pumpkin mixture and pat down lightly.
Drizzle 1/2 cup melted butter on top of cake mix; sprinkle with nuts. Bake for 40 to 60 minutes at 350°.

title: cheese dip
directions: Mix together dry mustard, cumin, chili powder and flour.
Add milk slowly; stir well.
Cook over medium heat.
Add cheese and cook until cheese is melted.

title: orange slice cake
directions: Cream butter and sugar.
Add eggs, one at a time.
Add flour alternating with milk.
Roll nuts, orange slices and dates in flour.
Add along with coconut to batter.
Batter is very stiff. Mix with hands.
Bake in tube pan at 250° for 2 to 2 1/2 hours. Top with Orange Sauce.

title: old-fashioned cream gravy
directions: Fry bacon and retain fat.
In hot fat, add flour and stir to thicken.
Pour half and half, cream in and add Cheddar cheese, stirring to mix well.
Cook over low heat, stirring constantly until thick.
Salt to taste.
Serve over biscuits.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: cinnamon punch
directions: Heat water, candy, sugar, and cloves; stirring until melted.
Cool. Remove cloves.
Add juices, mix well.
Just before serving, add 7-Up.

title: apricot nut bread
directions: Soak apricots in warm water for 30 minutes.
Beat sugar, shortening, egg and 1/4 cup water together; add orange.
Sift flour, baking powder, soda and salt together.
Combine liquid and dry ingredients.
Blend in drained apricots and nuts.
Pour into a greased 9 x 5 x 2-inch pan.
Bake for 50 minutes to 1 hour at 325°.
Do not overbake.

title: sweet potato pie
directions: Put all ingredients in blender and mix well.
Pour in 2 pie shells.
Bake at 325° for 35 to 40 minutes.

title: italian spaghetti
directions: Heat oil in heavy skillet.
Add garlic and onion.
Add hamburger and cook and stir until crumbly and brown.
Mix tomato paste, water and seasonings.
Stir into meat.
Cover and simmer over low heat for 1 hour.
When served, sprinkle with Parmesan cheese, if desired.

title: broccoli cheese soup
directions: Saute the onion in oil in a deep large pan. Add the water and bring to a boil. Add bouillon cubes, noodles and broccoli. Cook until tender.
Add cheese, milk, salt, pepper and garlic powder. Cover and simmer.
Yields 16 cups.

title: midwestern supper
directions: Brown hamburger and onion together.
Boil noodles until tender.
Drain.
Mix noodles, hamburger and Cheez Whiz together. Heat until Cheez Whiz melts.

title: hominy casserole
directions: Cook hominy and margarine until liquid is gone.
Add chilies, sour cream and half of cheese.
Place in baking dish and cover with remaining cheese.
Bake at 350° for 15 to 20 minutes.

title: hundred dollar cake
directions: Sift
all
dry	ingredients
together.	Add mayonnaise, cold water and vanilla.	Beat well and pour into a 9 x 13-inch greased and floured pan.
Bake at 350° about 30 minutes.

title: spiced pineapple
directions: Bring sugar and vinegar to a boil.
Add cinnamon and cloves. Pour over pineapple spears.
Marinate for 2 days in refrigerator.

title: peanut butter cookies
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Roll in 1-inch balls.
Flatten with fork.
Bake 10 to 12 minutes at 375°.

title: blonde brownies
directions: Melt margarine; remove from heat.
Stir in sugar until well mixed.
Beat in egg and vanilla until well blended.
Stir in flour and then nuts.
Spread in a greased 8 x 8 x 2-inch pan.
Bake in a preheated 325° oven for 20 to 25 minutes.
Cool and cut.

title: chicken parmesan
directions: Dip chicken breasts in butter, then roll in mixture of stuffing, cheese, parsley and garlic powder.
Place in greased pan (not touching).
Sprinkle remaining mixture over and cover with foil.
Bake at 375° for 1 hour.

title: stuffed onions
directions: Remove a slice from the top of each onion and parboil the onions until almost tender.
Drain and remove the centers, leaving six little cups.
Chop the onion that was scooped out and combine it with ham and soft bread crumbs.
Add seasonings and fat, then refill the onion cups.
Place them in a baking dish.
Cover with fine bread crumbs.
Add the milk and bake at 400° to 450° until tender.

title: soft molasses cake
directions: Stir to a stiff batter with flour (1 1/2 to 2 cups) enough to make a stiff batter.
Then pour over 1 cup of boiling water in which 1 teaspoon soda has been dissolved.
Either loaf or layer.

title: ham and broccoli casserole
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Cook broccoli according to directions; drain well.
Spread broccoli into ungreased 9 x 13-inch baking dish.
Layer ham and cheese over broccoli.
Beat milk and eggs; add Bisquick and beat until smooth.
Pour slowly over cheese. Bake, uncovered, for 1 hour.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: caramel frosting
directions: Cook milk and 2 cups sugar on low heat until it is at a soft ball stage.
Brown	remaining sugar in heavy skillet; add butter and let
simmer
until
sugar dissolves.
Combine the 2 mixtures and add
vanilla extract.
Cool; stir and spread over cake.

title: black bean soup
directions: If using dry beans, pick out broken beans and tiny stones. Wash well.
Cover with water and bring to boil for 5 minutes.
Pour off this water, add 1 quart of water and reheat.
In nonstick skillet, spray with cooking spray and saute onions and garlic until just limp.
Add all ingredients to beans and cook slowly until beans are done.
You may need to add more water.
Serve over white rice and top with chopped onions.
Serves two generously or add salad and serve four.

title: bayou jambalaya
directions: Microwave Directions:
Place onion, green pepper, garlic and butter in 3-quart micro safe dish.
Cover with lid or vented plastic wrap.
Microwave on High for 3 to 4 minutes, stirring once. Stir in rice, ketchup, water, vinegar, black pepper, red pepper, tomato and ham.
Cover and microwave at High 10 to 12 minutes or until mixture comes to a boil.
Microwave at Medium (50%) 18 to 20 minutes until rice is cooked; stirring once.
Stir in shrimp; cover and microwave at High 2 to 3 minutes or until shrimp turn pink. Let stand, covered, 5 minutes before serving.

title: easy drop danish
directions: Heat oven to 450°.
Mix margarine, sugar and Bisquick until crumbly.
Stir in milk until dough forms, beat 15 strokes.
Drop by rounded tablespoonfuls 2 inches apart onto lightly greased cookie sheet.
Make shallow well in center of each with back of spoon; fill with 1 teaspoon preserves.
Bake until golden 10 to 15 minutes.
While warm, drizzle with glaze.
Makes 12 danish.

title: open hot dog
directions: Quarter wieners lengthwise.
Place in skillet and cover with chili; bring to a simmering boil.
Toast bread slices and spread with mustard.
Cover toast with chili and wiener mixture.
Top with cheese and onions and serve.

title: carrot cake
directions: Mix flour, sugar, salt, soda and cinnamon. Mix in buttermilk, oil and vanilla and mix well. Add carrots, pineapple, coconut and nuts.
Pour into greased and floured 9 x 13 pan. Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes or until toothpick inserted into the center comes out clean.

title: zucchini pie
directions: Cook zucchini and onion in margarine for 10 minutes.
Stir in seasonings.
In separate bowl, blend eggs and cheese.
Stir in vegetables.
In a 10 in pie pan, press rolls into a crust; let stand 10 minutes.
(Do not grease pan.)
Spread mustard on crust. Pour vegetable mix in the pie crust.
Bake at 375° for 18 to 20 minutes.

title: sausage-cheese muffins
directions: Brown, crumble and drain sausage.
Beat other ingredients (except Cheddar cheese and sausage) together.
Fold in grated cheese and sausage.
Grease small (mini) muffin tins.
Spoon in batter.
Bake at 450° for 10 minutes.
Makes at least 36 small muffins.

title: pizza pasta
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Bring a large pot of lightly salted water to a boil.
Add pasta and cook for 8 to 10 minutes or until al dente; drain.
In medium skillet over medium high heat, cook beef with onion until beef is brown.
Drain.
Combine beef mixture with spaghetti sauce, pepperoni and cooked pasta and pour into a 9 x 13 inch baking dish.
Top with mozzarella.
Bake in preheated oven for 30 minutes, until cheese is melted and golden.

title: frosted pineapple squares
directions: Mix 1/2 cup sugar, cornstarch or flour and salt in a saucepan. Stir in slightly beaten egg yolks and undrained pineapple chunks. Cook over medium heat, stirring constantly, until mixture comes to a boil.
Set aside to cool.
In a large bowl, thoroughly mix 1 1/3 cups flour, 1 teaspoon sugar and dry yeast.
Combine milk, water and margarine in a saucepan.
Heat over low heat until liquids are warm (margarine need not be melted).
Gradually add to dry ingredients and beat 2 minutes at medium speed with electric mixer, scraping bowl occasionally.
Add egg yolks and 1/2 cup flour or enough flour to make a thick batter.
Beat at high speed 2 minutes, scraping bowl occasionally.
Stir in enough flour to make a soft, moist dough (2 1/4 cups of flour).

title: collectors cocoa cake
directions: Cream margarine and sugar until creamy and fluffy.
Add eggs; beat one at a time on medium speed.
Combine flour, cocoa, soda and salt.
Add alternately with water to creamed mixture.
Bake in 2 greased and floured cake pans.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes for 8-inch pan or 30 to 35 minutes for 9-inch pan.

title: pecan meatballs
directions: Mix ingredients thoroughly.
Heat cooking oil in skillet over medium heat; drop mixture by teaspoonfuls into oil.
Cook until lightly brown on all sides.
Remove from skillet and drain on paper towels.

title: beef-n-noodles au gratin
directions: In a large pan, brown the ground beef. Drain the fat from the beef. Stir in the garlic and onions and cook until tender (about 3 minutes). Cook noodles according to package directions. Add cooked noodles to beef mixture; stir well. Preheat oven to 425°. Add diced tomatoes to beef and noodle mixture; stir. Transfer mixture to a 9 x 13-inch casserole dish. Top with cheese. Bake in preheated oven for 15 minutes or until cheese melts. Makes 4 servings.

title: chicken parmesan
directions: Melt butter.
Add garlic and simmer.
Mix crumbs, cheese and seasonings.
Dip chicken in butter mixture; roll in cheese and crumbs.
Place in pan.
Bake at 350° for 1/2 hour, then at 300° for another 1/2 hour.

title: orange jubilee
directions: Place first 6 ingredients in blender and blend at high speed until ice is crushed.
Pour into serving glasses and garnish with orange peel spirals.

title: blueberry salad
directions: Dissolve gelatin in hot water.
Add crushed pineapple and blueberry pie filling.
Refrigerate until firm.
Mix sour cream with softened cream cheese, sugar and vanilla.
Spread on jello. Top with nuts.
Makes 12 servings.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Cook chicken.
Take off bone.
Cut up.
Cook egg noodles until tender.
Mix chicken soup, mushroom soup and one-half cup of chicken broth.
Put a layer of chicken, layer of noodles, layer of cheese and a layer of the soup.
Repeat this until all gone.
Bake at 325° for about 25 minutes or until it bubbles around the edge.

title: pear relish
directions: Combine and cook together all ingredients, except flour and water.
Cook 4 minutes or until tender.
Mix flour with a little water to make thin paste.
Add to pears.
Cook on medium 10 to 15 minutes until thickens.
Stir often.

title: gooey butter cake
directions: Mix cake mix, butter and eggs by hand. Put in 9 x 13-inch pan. Beat rest of ingredients until smooth. Pour over cake and bake at 350° for 40 minutes.

title: chili relleno squares
directions: Layer cheese and chilies in a lightly greased 12 x 8 x 2-inch baking dish.
Pour eggs over mixture.
Bake at 300° for 45 minutes or until center is firm.
Cut in 2-inch squares.
Yields 2 dozen appetizers.

title: cheese and meat enchiladas
directions: Brown ground beef; drain.
Add 2/3 cup onions; cook until onions are soft. Add tomatoes; stir well and continue cooking for a few minutes.
Add tomato sauce and water (this will make plenty of sauce). Add seasoning. Simmer, cooking sauce down so that it is not too liquidy.
Reserve 1 to 2 cups of sauce for topping.

title: zucchini rolls
directions: Stir first four ingredients together.
Fold in zucchini.
Melt butter in skillet.
Drop in zucchini rounds.
Fry until brown on each side.

title: burger loaf
directions: Combine all ingredients in large bowl, then place in loaf pan to bake.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Serve with gravy.

title: creamy macaroni and cheese bake
directions: Boil macaroni and drain.
Stir together ingredients in a casserole dish and top with cheese.
Bake at 400° for 20 to 25 minutes.

title: gala sour cream dip
directions: Combine all ingredients for dip in small mixing bowl.
Cover and chill for 2 to 3 hours to allow flavors to blend.
Meanwhile, preheat oven to 400°.
Cut a thin slice from top of bread. Carefully hollow out center of bread, leaving a 1-inch shell on sides and bottom.
Cut inside pieces into 1-inch cubes.
Place bread shell and cubes on baking sheet.
Bake about 10 minutes or until toasted.
Cool completely on wire rack.

title: lemonade mousse
directions: Using a fork, combine graham cracker crumbs, sugar and butter. Lightly press 3/4 of the graham cracker mixture on the bottom of a 9 x 13-inch pan.

title: baked corn pudding
directions: Combine all but the butter and mix to blend.
Pour into a buttered casserole.
Dot top with butter.
Bake in oven at 350° for 1 hour or until knife comes out clean.

title: hot fudge sauce
directions: Combine dry ingredients.
Add boiling water, vanilla and butter.
Let boil until desired thickness (you may have to add some water).

title: venison roast
directions: Place 4 strips of bacon and half of the onion in roasting pan. Rub roast with salt, pepper and celery salt.
Place roast over onion and bacon.
Arrange remaining bacon and onion on top of roast.
Sprinkle vinegar over all.
Bake, uncovered, at 300° to 325° for 2 to 3 hours.
Turn often.
Cover, if roast becomes too dry.

title: johnny brazilian casserole
directions: Season meat with salt and pepper; sear in bacon drippings.
Add chopped onion, pepper and garlic and simmer.
Then add cream of tomato soup, cream of mushroom soup and 2 tablespoons Worcestershire sauce and simmer 30 minutes.
Cook 1 package medium-sized noodles in saltwater until done.
Drain well and add to the meat mixture.
Fold in 1/4 to 1/2 pound Velveeta cheese (shredded) and if desired, diced stuffed olives.
Serves 12 or more.

title: mexican corn bread
directions: Mix all together.
Bake in a greased 9 x 13-inch glass pan at 400°.
Invert to serve.
Enjoy!

title: scrumptious one
directions: Saute celery and onion in butter.
Add remaining ingredients except bread crumbs and mix placing them in buttered dish.
Cover with crumbs and bake at 350° for 40 minutes.
Cooked chicken or turkey may be added.

title: foggy pea soup
directions: First prepare the bouillon.

title: open house punch(serves 32)
directions: Chill ingredients.
Mix in punch bowl (7-Up last).
Add drops of food coloring as desired (optional).
Stir.
Add ice, orange and lemon slices.

title: hawaiian meatballs
directions: Combine ground beef, cracker crumbs, evaporated milk, flour and seasoned flour. Mix lightly, but thoroughly. Shape into 60 balls. Roll in flour and brown in shortening. Drain off excess fat. Prepare Sweet and Sour Sauce. Pour over meatballs and simmer, covered, for 15 minutes. Serves 6.

title: brown rice(microwave)
directions: Use microwave container with lid.

title: guacamole surprise
directions: Steam peas.
Combine all ingredients in blender. Process until smooth.
Serve chilled with chips.
Makes 2 cups.

title: pecan puffs
directions: Put this mix in freezer and chill Make small balls.
Bake 45 minutes at 300 degrees and dip in powdered sugar.

title: chocolate peppermint drink
directions: Put 2 cups of chocolate milk and about 3 scoops of ice cream in a blender.
Blend well.
Add peppermint flavoring and 1 teaspoon of crushed peppermint.
Blend a little bit more.
Pour into a glass and put one or two scoops of ice cream on top. Sprinkle some of the crushed peppermint over the top.

title: rod's new year's eve hors d'oeuvres
directions: Blend cream cheese, Worcestershire sauce and horseradish (use horseradish to taste).
Spread on dried beef.
Roll up and cut beef in half.
Secure with toothpick.

title: sour cream pound cake
directions: Cream butter and sugar.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating after each addition.
Add soda to sour cream.
Add flour alternately with sour cream.
Add flavoring.
Bake in a greased and floured tube pan. Bake 1 hour and 15 minutes at 350°.

title: chicken pot pie
directions: Combine chicken, Veg-All, chicken soup and liquid from one can of Veg-All.
Salt and pepper to taste.
Place one pie crust on bottom and one on top of casserole.
Bake at 350° for approximately 35 minutes.

title: kiss-me-quick cookies
directions: Heat oven to 375°.
In large bowl, combine cake mix, oil and eggs; stir by hand until thoroughly moistened.
Stir in candy bits from cake mix.
Shape dough into 1-inch balls.
Place 2 inches apart on ungreased cookie sheets.
Bake at 375° for 6 to 8 minutes, or until edges are light golden brown.
Immediately place chocolate heart candy in center of each cookie.
Cool 1 minute; remove from cookie sheets.

title: rice salad
directions: Put rice in a deep salad bowl.
In separate bowl combine mayonnaise, sour cream, mustard, lemon juice and garlic.
Spread mixture on top of rice and top with celery, tomatoes and green pepper.
Cover and refrigerate for at least 3 hours.

title: vanilla cookies
directions: Stir together the flour, baking powder and salt.
Beat butter, margarine, sugar, egg and vanilla in another bowl until well blended.
Stir in flour mixture; shape into ball.
Wrap in plastic. Refrigerate 2 hours.
Roll out dough on floured surface to 3/8-inch thickness.
Cut into rounds with 2 1/2-inch cookie cutter.
Place on cookie sheet sprayed with cooking spray, 1 1/2 inches apart. Bake at 350° for 12 minutes or until lightly browned at edges. Cool.
Frost with glaze.

title: skillet beans
directions: Saute mushrooms, green pepper and onion in bacon grease.
Add seasonings.
Drain beans and add beans and bacon pieces.
Simmer until heated through.

title: kristen's irresistible old-fashioned fudge
directions: In heavy 6-quart or larger boiler, combine sugar and evaporated milk. Bring to a full boil for 6 minutes, stirring constantly.
Remove from heat and stir in butter.
Add chocolate morsels, vanilla and nuts, mixing until smooth. Quickly pour into buttered 9 x 13-inch pan and refrigerate until firm.

title: spinach fat-free yogurt dip
directions: Measure out 2 cups fat-free plain yogurt.
Chop up the spinach and onion.
Then mix all the ingredients together.

title: potage st. germain(pea soup)
directions: Melt butter in saucepan.
Add peas, carrots, onion and garlic. Cook for about 5 minutes until soft.
Add stock.
Simmer for about 20 minutes.
Put through blender until smooth.
Add cream and serve.

title: cranberry fruit relish
directions: Place the cranberries, orange and apple in a blender or food processor. Cover and process until chunky. Transfer to a bowl. Stir in sugar, pineapple, ginger and nutmeg. Cover and refrigerate for at least 2 hours. Yield: about 4 cups.

title: butterscotch crescents
directions: Heat oven to 375°.
Stir butterscotch chips, coconut, and nuts together.
Unroll crescent dough.
Sprinkle 1 Tbsp. butterscotch mixture on each.
Gently press into dough.
Roll dough up into crescents short end first.
Place in pan edge down. Bake 10-12 minutes or until brown.
Sprinkle top with powdered sugar.

title: crab dip
directions: Mix all ingredients (except crabmeat) well.
I use the mixer. Stir into crabmeat.
Place into 2-quart dish and top with cheese. Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: martha rueff's potato salad
directions: Dice cooked potatoes.
Fry bacon; reduce heat and gently stir in potatoes.
Add salt, pepper and vinegar.
Place eggs and lettuce in large bowl.
Moments before serving, add hot potato mixture and toss quickly.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: christmas cocoa mix
directions: Combine all dry ingredients; mix well.
Combine 1/3 cup dry mix and 1 cup hot water per serving.
Top with marshmallows and serve hot.

title: golden pumpkin pie
directions: Combine all the ingredients in the order in which they are listed, except the unbaked pie shell.
Pour pie filling into the unbaked pie shell.
Bake at 450° for 10 minutes, then turn down to 325° and continue baking for 40 minutes.
Pie is ready when knife inserted in center comes out clean.
Garnish with whipped topping if desired.

title: toffee
directions: Spray a cookie sheet with Pam and spread 2 cups chopped pecans on it.

title: mayonnaise cake
directions: Sift all dry ingredients together.
Add water, mayonnaise and vanilla.
Beat by hand until well blended.
Bake at 350° until lightly browned, 30 to 45 minutes.

title: new england boiled dinner
directions: In Dutch oven, cover corned beef with water.
Add garlic and bay leaves.
Bring to boil; simmer, covered, 2 1/2 hours.
Remove meat.
Add potatoes, carrots and onions.
Cook, covered, 10 minutes; add cabbage.
Cook, covered, 15 to 20 minutes.
Add meat; heat through.
Drain meat and vegetables; season to taste.
Serves 8.

title: puppy chow
directions: Mix all ingredients in large pan, except cereal and powdered sugar.
Melt, then add cereal until well coated.
Put 1 cup powdered sugar in large paper sack.
Add mixture, then add the other cup of powdered sugar to sack.
Close; shake well until coated.
Pour into container.
Put lid on after well cooled and dry.

title: creole pralines
directions: Combine the sugars, water and vinegar.
Cook to soft ball stage (236°).
Add butter, nuts and a few drops of red food coloring.
Remove from heat.
Immediately beat until mixture starts to thicken and becomes cloudy.
Quickly drop by heaping tablespoonfuls onto buttered waxed paper or foil.
Cool.
Makes 14 (3 to 3 1/2-inch) pralines.

title: green and gold squash medley
directions: Heat broiler or grill.
Cook squash and zucchini slices 6 to 8 minutes or until tender, turning once.
In small bowl, whisk together 1 tablespoon each lemon zest and juice, olive oil and mint.
Pour sauce over squash and zucchini.
Sprinkle with olives. Add salt and pepper to taste and garnish with lemon wedges, if desired.
Serve warm or cold.
Makes 6 servings.

title: buffalo style chicken wings
directions: In boiling pan, arrange 3 pounds chicken wings.
Brush with butter sauce mix.
Broil 10 to 15 minutes until wings are golden and tender.

title: easy chicken chili
directions: In a large saucepan, cook the onion and garlic in vegetable oil until soft.
Add the tomatoes and kidney beans.
Add chili powder.
Mix well.
Add chicken and olives.
Let chili simmer on low heat for 45 minutes.

title: oatmeal pie
directions: Melt butter in a heavy saucepan.
Remove from heat and add sugar, corn syrup and oats; blend well.
Add beaten eggs and vanilla.
Pour mixture into unbaked pie shell.
If desired, top with chopped nuts.
Bake in a 325° oven for 45 minutes, or until set.
Yields 1 pie; 6 to 8 servings.

title: cream of mushroom soup
directions: Melt butter in a Dutch oven; saute mushrooms and onion.
Add chicken broth and simmer for 1 hour and 30 minutes.
Before serving, put all of the mushroom mixture through a blender, adding 1 tablespoon flour to each blender full, blending to consistency of thin white sauce.
Pour back into Dutch oven and cream and heat until hot.
Do not boil.
Season to taste.

title: zucchini casserole
directions: Boil zucchini, carrots and onions in water, almost to cover, for 5 minutes.
Drain well.
Mix sour cream and soup together and add to vegetables.
Melt margarine and add both packages from Stove Top stuffing.
Put half of crumb mix on bottom of casserole dish, add vegetables and put remaining crumbs on top.
Bake at 350° for 35 minutes.
Enjoy!!

title: savory party bread
directions: Cut the bread lengthwise and crosswise without cutting through the bottom crust.

Insert cheese slices between all cuts. Combine butter, onions and poppy seeds; drizzle over bread. Wrap in foil and place on baking sheet. Bake at 350° for 15 minutes. Uncover and bake 10 minutes longer or until cheese is melted.

title: barley bread
directions: Mix together; flatten balls of barley dough and fry in hot oil or bake unflattened balls of barley dough.
Put on a sheet pan. Bake 20 to 25 minutes until brown at 400°.

title: cherry pie, billy boy
directions: Drain juice from the cherries and measure out 1 1/2 cups juice. Sift sugar, salt and cornstarch and mix with the juice. Place mixture in the top of a double boiler and cook for 5 minutes to thicken. Stir to prevent sticking.
Add the butter and almond extract. Remove from the heat. Add the cherries. Pour the mixture into the pie shell and top with the other pie crust.
Sprinkle the top with 1 1/2 tablespoons of sugar. Bake at 400° for 45 minutes. Serves 8.

title: chipped beef dip
directions: May adjust measurements of onions and green pepper to taste. Mix up and put in pan (small casserole).
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes.
Let stand 5 to 10 minutes.
Spread on crackers or party rye bread.

title: chicken kabob supreme
directions: Cut chicken into 1-inch pieces; set aside.
Combine oil, soy sauce, wine, corn syrup, sesame seed, lemon juice, garlic powder and ginger; mix well.
Add chicken.
Cover and marinate at least 2 hours in refrigerator.
Remove chicken from marinade, reserving marinade.
Alternate chicken, pineapple and vegetables on skewers. Grill about 6 inches from medium-hot coals for 15 to 20 minutes, or until done, turning and basting often with marinade.
Makes 6.

title: punch
directions: Mix all together and serve.
A good recipe to use when uncertain about quantity needed.

title: spinach fandango
directions: In a large skillet, combine first six ingredients and brown. Salt and pepper to taste.
Place spinach, unthawed, on top of other ingredients.
Cover and steam until mixable.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Cook broccoli 5 minutes.
Drain.
Place in casserole dish. Mix soup and cheese.
Add milk and mayonnaise. Beat egg and add to mixture, then pour mixture over broccoli. Sprinkle bread crumbs on top.
Then pour melted butter over crumbs.
Bake for 45 minutes.

title: fish dinner
directions: Ritz crackers should be crumbled and melt butter.
Mix all together.
Put 2 teaspoons butter in baking dish.
Bake at 400° for 40 to 50 minutes.

title: quick caramel pecan rolls
directions: For caramel sauce, in a small saucepan, combine 1/4 c brown sugar and the flour. Stir in 2 tbsp butter and milk. Cook, stirring constantly, over medium heat till thickened and bubbly. Remove from heat; stir in rum extract. Divide mixture evenly among 8 muffin cups.

title: sauce for meat loaf
directions: Place over top of meat loaf the last 1/2 hour of cooking.

title: strawberry and romaine salad
directions: Toss romaine, onions and dressing together.
Top with strawberries and almonds.
Serves 4-6.

title: bishop bread
directions: Add flour, brown sugar and salt.
Cream with Crisco until mixture looks like a coarse meal.
Reserve 3/4 cup mixture for topping, to remaining add the baking powder, cinnamon, soda and egg.
Gradually add milk.
Beat until smooth.
Turn into greased and floured 8 x 8-inch or 8 x 12-inch pan.
Sprinkle with topping. Bake at 400° for 25 minutes.
Serve hot!!

title: layered skillet dinner
directions: This is cooked on top of stove.
Place bacon in skillet on medium flame.
Make hamburger into patties.
Put on top of bacon when it is sizzling.
Cut potatoes, onions and carrots into 1/2-inch slices.
Layer in order given.
Add 1/2 cup water.
Cover with airtight lid.
On low flame, cook 45 minutes to 1 hour.

title: lasagne casserole
directions: Brown meat slowly; spoon off fat.
Add remaining ingredients. Simmer, uncovered, for 1/2 hour, stirring occasionally. Meanwhile, cook the lasagne noodles and prepare Cheese Filling.

title: 7-up cake
directions: Cream sugar, oleo and Crisco until fluffy.
Add eggs and beat well.
Add flour, 7-Up and flavorings and beat well.
Pour into large tube pan.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour and 20 minutes.

title: linda's carrot cake
directions: Mix together the flour, sugar, cinnamon, baking soda, baking powder and salt.
Drain pineapple, saving syrup.
Add syrup to dry mixture.
Add eggs, oil and vanilla.
Beat for 3 minutes.
Stir in pineapple, carrots and nuts.
Bake at 325° for 1 1/2 hours. Grease and lightly flour Bundt pan.
Cool 10 minutes before unmolding from pan.

title: chocolate syrup cake
directions: Cut up butter and add rest of ingredients; stir.
Bake until test done, about 30 or 35 minutes.
Frost with chocolate frosting.

title: broccoli salad
directions: Combine broccoli, bacon, raisins and sunflower seeds.
Stir together Miracle Whip, sugar and vinegar.
Add dressing to broccoli mixture and stir.

title: potato cassbake
directions: Mix all ingredients except butter and corn flakes.
Put in a casserole dish.
Top with corn flakes, then pour melted butter over top.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: chocolate macaroons(shaped cookies)
directions: Melt chocolate and margarine over very low heat.
Remove from stove and stir in the sugar gradually.
Drop 1 egg in at a time and beat well.
Sift the dry ingredients and blend into the chocolate mixture.
Add vanilla and nuts.
Chill in refrigerator. Form into balls and drop in powdered sugar to coat.
Bake at 375° for 10 to 12 minutes.

title: broccoli quadrettini
directions: In a skillet, cook bacon until crisp, drain and set aside. Cook broccoli in water until crisp-tender.
Cook pasta in boiling water until al dente.
Drain broccoli and chop into 1/4-inch pieces.
Drain pasta and immediately place it back in the pot and toss with butter, bacon, broccoli and cheese.

title: spaghetti bolognese
directions: Saute mushrooms, carrots, garlic, onion, celery and green pepper in Wesson oil in Dutch oven.
Add sausage; cook until sausage loses redness.
Drain fat.
Add remaining ingredients. Simmer, uncovered, approximately 40 minutes, stirring occasionally.
Serve over hot, cooked spaghetti.
Makes 4 to 6 servings.

title: baked shrimp
directions: Spread shrimp out in a shallow pan.
Brush with Dale's steak seasoning.
Sprinkle with salt, pepper, garlic powder and dill weed.
Squeeze lemon over shrimp and add stick of melted butter. Bake at 400° for about 5 minutes.
Drain off most of the liquid. Then sprinkle Tony's creole seasoning and grated sharp Cheddar cheese on top of shrimp.
Top with paprika.
Boil about 3 to 4 minutes.
Serve immediately.
Serve with broccoli salad contained herein.

title: spinach salad
directions: Mix together the honey, salt, mustard, paprika, canola oil and vinegar to make a dressing.
Place the spinach, scallions, oranges, strawberries and cashews in
a large bowl.
Add the dressing just before serving.

title: cheese bread
directions: Mix until smooth.
Spread on French bread and put under broiler until bubbly.
This can be frozen!

title: spiced tea mix
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Store in tightly covered container.
To Use:
Use 2 teaspoons per cup of hot water.

title: banana bread
directions: Cream butter or margarine and sugar.
Add beaten eggs.
Add flour that has been sifted with soda and salt.
Add sour milk and beat well.
Blend in bananas and nuts.
Bake in greased lof pan for 1 to 1 1/2 hours at 350°.
Bread is done when inserted cake tester or toothpick comes out clean.

title: salad ole
directions: Mix sour cream, dressing and taco sauce in with the first 6 ingredients.
Top with cheeses and add Fritos at last minute.

title: grilled sour cream burgers
directions: Combine sour cream dip, bread crumbs, salt and pepper.
Add ground beef or pork.
Mix well and shape into four 1/2-inch patties.
Grill over medium coals, turning once.
For beef, grill until desired doneness.
For pork, grill about 18 minutes or until well done.

title: cheese wafers
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Bake at 375° for 10 minutes.
Do not overcook.

title: quick cherry cake
directions: Mix and cream together margarine and sugar.
Add eggs and almond extract to creamed mixture.
Mix well.
Add flour and baking powder.
Mix until smooth.
Butter a 13 x 9 x 2-inch cake pan.
Put cake batter into pan; then drop by spoonfuls the pie mixture evenly over cake.
Bake at 350° until a toothpick inserted comes out clean.
Dust with powdered sugar.

title: barbecue with chicken
directions: Brown hamburger, onion and celery.
Put all ingredients (except chicken) into crock-pot.
Cook on low for a couple of hours.
Add diced chicken one hour before serving.

title: fiesta chicken casserole
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Prepare noodle dinner as directed on package except using 3/4 cup milk.
Add sauce, chicken, peas, onion, mushrooms, salt and sage.
Mix lightly.
Pour into 1 1/2-quart casserole.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Cook chicken and pick off the bone.
Combine chicken with salt and pepper.
Melt butter in chicken broth.
Pour over stuffing mix and mix well.
Put half of dressing mix in 9 1/2-inch casserole dish.
Cover with chicken mixture and top with remainder of stuffing mix.
Bake in oven at 350° to 375° for about 30 minutes or until slightly browned.

title: egg fu young
directions: Mix onions and veggies in frying pan.
Place small amount of oil, approximately 1/4 c. of veggie mixture.
Stir, and fry until onions are tender. Mix eggs and 2 T. soy sauce, pour 1/4 c. egg mixture over veggies.
Cook on both sides.
Remove and place in oven pan.
Continue until all mixtures are gone.

title: french onion soup
directions: Preheat broiler.
Melt butter in frying pan and fry onions until light brown and tender.
Add water.
Crumble bouillon cubes into water.
Stir and allow to boil for 10 minutes.
Add wine and seasonings.
Stir and cover.
Reduce heat and simmer for 15 minutes.
Pour soup into large casserole dish or 4 individual crocks.
Top with bread first, then cheese.
Broil until cheese is bubbly and golden.
Serve hot.

title: vidalia onions
directions: Peel large onions.
Place in individual ramekins.
Salt and pepper to taste.
Top each with a small pat of margarine. Microwave on High 3 to 4 minutes per onion or until tender. Serves 4.

title: taco spread
directions: Beat ingredients together.
Spread on a platter.
Spread salsa on shredded lettuce, diced tomatoes, sliced black olives, chopped green onions and shredded Cheddar cheese.
Serve with tortilla chips.

title: scalloped potatoes (optional with diced ham)
directions: Put sliced potatoes in a 3 qt. casserole.
Make a white sauce by combining the flour, salt and milk (cold) together.
Pour over potatoes to just cover.
Dot with butter or margarine.
Sprinkle top with pepper.
(Optional:
diced ham blended in or just over top.)
(Also optional: diced onions).

title: snack meatballs
directions: Combine milk, 2 teaspoons Worcestershire sauce and soup mix. Blend well.
Let stand 5 minutes.
Add beef and mix well.
Mixture will be moist.
Shape into balls, using a tablespoonful each. Place on rack in broiler pan.
Broil 5 to 6 inches from heat for 10 to 12 minutes.
Do not turn.
Combine remaining Worcestershire sauce and remaining ingredients in saucepan.
Cook, stirring, until heated through.
Add meatballs and serve.

title: seafood newburg
directions: Cook and devein shrimp.
Lightly brown scallops in a frypan with 1 tablespoon of butter (if using large scallops, cut them into bite size pieces).
Combine all ingredients in a large stock pot and gently warm; do not cover.
Delicious served over rice or in pastry cups.
Yields approximately 20 to 25 servings as part of a buffet.

title: taco casserole
directions: Cook beef, onion and green pepper in skillet until beef is browned; drain.
Add taco seasoning mix and tomato sauce with salt and pepper to taste.
Line a large greased casserole dish with taco chips.
Pour a portion of meat mixture over chips, then alternate layers of cheese, chops and meat.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Serves 4.

title: chocolate pie
directions: Bake and cool pie crust.
Soften gelatin in cold water. Combine 1/3 cup sugar, cornstarch and salt in heavy saucepan. Gradually stir in milk, blending until smooth.
Cook over medium heat, stirring constantly, until filling comes to a boil.
Cook for 5 minutes then remove from heat.
Stir a small amount into beaten egg yolks then add to filling.
Cook for 1 minute.
Remove from heat and stir in gelatin.
Blend melted chocolate and vanilla into filling.
Fill pie shell and let cool.
Serve with whipped cream.

title: apricot-lime salad
directions: Dissolve lime gelatin in hot water. Soak 1 tablespoon gelatin in cold water and add to hot mixture; cool. Add ginger ale.
Pour into 9-inch ring mold. Chill until partially set.
Fill center of apricot halves with cream cheese balls rolled in nuts. Arrange filled apricots in partially set gelatin alternating with cherries.
Chill until firm.
Serve with dressing.

title: million dollar pie(makes 2 pies)
directions: Mix all ingredients in large bowl.
Be sure pineapple is well drained.
Spoon into two graham cracker crusts.
Top with finely crushed nuts.
Refrigerate.
Can be frozen.

title: pavlova
directions: Beat egg whites until light and fluffy.
Add sugar, a spoon at a time, making sure it dissolves. Add the cornstarch with the last spoon of sugar. Add vanilla and vinegar; beat in well.

Pile mixture into a flat baking pan, forming a circle approximately 7-inches in diameter and making the sides higher. Bake in a 200° oven for 1 1/2 to 2 hours until outside is light brown and crisp. Leave in oven, turned off, to cool down for at least 1 hour. Fill with whipped cream and top with fruit.

title: barbecue shrimp
directions: Place shrimp in pan; sprinkle a lot of Tony's seasoning over them.
Put
pats
of butter on shrimp.
Squeeze drops of lemon
on shrimp.
Bake in preheated oven at 350° for about an hour
or until shrimp are tender.
Serve over rice with French bread.

title: deep dish biscuit pizza
directions: Brown hamburger with onion; drain.
Stir in tomato paste, mushroom stems and pieces, oregano, salt and pepper; simmer. Press canned biscuits into greased 9-inch pie pan to form crust. Spoon meat mixture into crust.
Slice 1 tomato; arrange on top. Sprinkle with cheese.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes.
Let stand 45 minutes before serving.

title: throwed rolls(lambert's cafe rolls)
directions: Combine sugar and yeast in tepid water.
Let stand 5 to 10 minutes until yeast begins to foam.
Thoroughly mix milk, butter, sugar, egg and salt in a large bowl.
Stir in yeast mixture and 3 1/2 cups of flour.
Add a bit more, if necessary, to make a soft pliable dough.
Turn dough out on floured board and let it rest while you butter bowl.
Knead dough gently 4 to 5 minutes, adding flour if necessary until dough is smooth and silky.
Return to bowl.
Cover with plastic wrap and let rise in warm place until doubled in size.
Butter a 12 cup muffin tin.
Punch dough down. Pinch off pieces about 1 1/2-inches in diameter (enough to fill 1/2 of muffin cup).
Roll into smooth ball.
Place 2 such pieces in each prepared muffin cup.
(It should be a tight fit.)
Cover dough loosely with plastic wrap for 45 minutes.
Preheat oven to 350°. Bake rolls 20 to 25 minutes or until light brown.
Serve as soon as they are cool enough to throw.
Makes 12 rolls.

title: ham and bean soup
directions: Rinse beans.
Pick out faulty beans and stones.
Mix water with some juice from cooked ham to equal 1 1/2 quarts.
Add to pot.
Add soup bone to pot.
Add onion, celery, carrots and bay leaf.
When beans begin to soften, add potatoes.
Add seminola cooked in boiling water, if desired.
Simmer 20 to 30 minutes or until beans are slightly mushy.

title: corned beef casserole
directions: Don't dilute soups.
Mix all together.
Bake at 375° for 1 hour.

title: chicken dressing casserole
directions: Mix cornmeal, buttermilk, eggs, celery and onions. Bake as you would cornbread until done. Crumble and mix with boiled eggs, stuffing mix and chicken broth. Grease 11 x 14 pan. Pour in half of dressing mixture. Top with deboned chicken. Add remaining dressing.

title: catfish stew(makes 2 gallons)
directions: Dice celery, bell peppers and onions.

Boil catfish for approximately 15 minutes, then remove from water (save water). Squeeze all water from catfish and ensure all bones are removed. Cut bacon in 1-inch pieces and place in large heavy pot over medium heat.
Stir while cooking.
When bacon is done, saute bell peppers and celery.
Add onions; continue to saute until done.
Add salt and pepper.
Cook and drain potatoes.
Combine all ingredients, except red pepper, sugar and Texas Pete.
Reduce to low heat; stir often.
Add red peppers, Texas Pete and brown sugar.
For stronger taste, add saved water or water if too thick.
Season to taste.

title: cranberry-pineapple salad
directions: In a bowl, dissolve gelatin in boiling water.
Break up and stir in cranberry sauce.
Add pineapple, orange juice and lemon juice.
Chill until partially set.
Stir in nuts.
Pour into an 11 x 7 x 2-inch dish.
Chill until firm; cut into squares.
Serve on lettuce leaf and top with spoon of mayonnaise or Cool Whip. Very colorful and pretty.

title: lasagne
directions: Brown ground beef, onion and garlic.
Add Ragu and cottage cheese until hot.
Leave in pan and set aside.
Cook lasagna noodles.
Grate Swiss cheese, Cheddar and Mozzarella cheese.
Mix cheeses together.
Layer noodles, sauce, cheese and meat in dish. Bake for 20 minutes at 350°.

title: protein potassium power
directions: Put ingredients into blender and blend until well mixed. Makes about 3 1/2 cups.

title: tijuana torte
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Brown ground beef and onion in skillet. Add tomatoes with sauce, green chiles and taco seasoning mix. Combine thoroughly and simmer for 10 minutes.
Place a little meat mixture in large round baking dish (about the size of tortilla). Place tortilla on top of meat; add more meat on top and add some Cheddar cheese.
Continue stacking, ending with cheese.
Bake 20 to 25 minutes.

title: zig-zag cake(another prize winner)
directions: For
several
generations standard pastry was made with lard. Most
cooks
had their own supply and for those who had to purchase it, the price was low.
Also lard makes a superior, flaky pastry
(I
still
use
it
sometimes).

title: pound cake
directions: Cream margarine, sugar, and eggs. In separate bowl, mix all dry ingredients; add to the first mixture a little at a time, alternating with milk. Mix well and add flavoring. Pour into a greased and floured tube pan and bake for 3 hours at 350°.

title: ma glockner's coconut cream pie
directions: Combine cheese, sugar, milk and coconut in electric blender. Cover and blend on low speed for 30 seconds.
Fold in whipped topping.
Spoon into pie crust.
Garnish with toasted coconut, if desired.
Freeze until firm.
Let stand at room temperature for 5 minutes before cutting.

title: shrimp salad
directions: Combine all ingredients and chill.
Serve with crackers or on a bed of lettuce.

title: peanut butter squares
directions: Mix together melted butter, confectioners sugar, crushed graham crackers and peanut butter.
Spread in bottom of a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Put in the refrigerator for approximately 15 minutes.
Melt Hershey's chocolate chips in the microwave oven and spread over the bottom layer.
Place in the refrigerator until ready and cut into squares.

title: sunday pot roast
directions: Place roast on large sheet of heavy-duty foil.
Mix soups and cover roast with soup mixture.
Add potatoes and bring foil up and over roast.
Roll and secure edges tightly, about 6 inches above roast.
Bake at 350° about 3 hours.
Serves 8 to 10.

title: chicken imperial
directions: Mix seasoning in melted margarine.
Dip chicken in bread crumbs and place on baking pan lined with foil.
Pour margarine and seasoning over breaded chicken and bake for 1 hour at 350°.

title: spinach casserole
directions: Cook and drain spinach.
Add all ingredients and put in sprayed 9x13 pan. Bake 1 hour at 350 degrees.

title: pineapple casserole
directions: Drain pineapple and reserve liquid.
Mix sugar, pineapple chunks, flour and cheese.
Place in greased casserole dish.
Top with crackers and drizzle juice and butter over top.
Bake at 350° until bubbly.

title: alice's tuna casserole
directions: Cook noodles.
Drain.
Add next seven ingredients.
Mix well. Put in a 13 x 9-inch baking dish.
Top with tortilla chips and cheese.
Bake in 350° oven until hot and bubbly and cheese is melted and brown.
Serve with salsa.
Serves 4 to 6.

title: punch
directions: Mix all juices and sugar.
Add ginger ale when ready to serve.

title: toasted pecan cranberry bark
directions: Line cookie sheet with foil, sprinkle with pecans.
Bake in a pre-heated 325 degree oven 10-15 minutes or until lightly toasted; cool. Coarsely chop the pecans and set aside.
Heat vanilla coating over low heat stirring constantly until smooth.
Stir in pecans, cranberries and nutmeg.
Spread 1/4-inch thick on foil lined cookie sheet.
Refrigerate until firm; break into pieces.

title: baked beans deluxe
directions: In heavy skillet, melt shortening and saute onion and pepper until tender.
Add ground beef and let cook 10 minutes until meat is browned.
Add flour, spices and tomatoes.
Mix well and simmer 10 minutes.
Combine beans, turn into baking dish.
Bake at 375° until hot.
Five minutes before removing from oven add 1/2 cup grated cheese.

title: divinity
directions: Place sugar, water and syrup over low fire and stir only until sugar is dissolved.
Cook to soft ball stage.

Beat egg whites 2 minutes at high speed and pour 1/2 of syrup mixture slowly over egg whites while beating and continue beating while returning syrup to stove and cook until cracks against cup when dropped in cold water.
Add this to egg white mixture.
Beat until it begins to lose gloss.
Add vanilla, salt and nuts.
Drop by spoonful on waxed paper.

title: apple butter
directions: Combine all ingredients in medium saucepan.
Cook over medium heat for 50 minutes or until very thick, stirring occasionally. Store in sealed container in refrigerator for up to 3 weeks.

title: buffet beef in beer(crock-pot)
directions: In crock-pot, mix well beer, soup mix and gravy mix.
In plastic bag, shake flour and steak until coated.
Empty bag contents into crock-pot. Gently stir to coat meat with liquid. Cover and cook on low about 8 hours.
Garnish with dill weed if desired.

title: creamy rhubarb pie
directions: Beat eggs separately but stir together before pouring over rhubarb.
Makes two 9-inch pies.
Bake at 375° for 10 minutes. Reduce heat to 325° for 20 minutes.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Cook broccoli according to package directions.
Drain.
Place broccoli in 9 x 13 inch casserole dish.
Mix flour with milk to make a paste.
Stir until well blended.
Add margarine and cheese. Place over low heat and stir until melted and thick.
Pour over broccoli.
Crush crackers fine and sprinkle over top.
Bake at 350° for 35 minutes.
Best when bubbly hot!

title: pepper beef and rice
directions: Cut beef into thin strips.
Brown beef and onions.
Add sliced pepper, ketchup, sauce, salt, pepper and enough water to cover. Simmer for 1 hour.
Cook rice.
Serve pepper and beef over rice.

title: glazed white potatoes
directions: Cook the potatoes until tender; peel.
Melt the sugar in a heavy skillet until golden brown. Add the butter.
Mix well. Rinse potatoes in cold water and add to sugar-butter mixture.
Stir and heat potatoes until they are brown and shiny.

title: corn bread
directions: Mix all of the ingredients and pour into a 13 x 9-inch pan sprayed with Pam.
Bake at 400° until done.

title: hummus
directions: Blend all ingredients in a food processor.
Enjoy with pita bread, crackers or raw vegetables.

title: strawberry cake
directions: Soften Jell-O in 1/2 cup hot water and let cool. Combine other ingredients; blend all together for 4 minutes. Bake in 3 pans. Bake 30 minutes in 350° oven.

title: cream of broccoli soup
directions: Cook broccoli according to package directions; drain well. Add remaining ingredients.
Cook over low heat until thoroughly heated.
Yield:
about 8 cups.

title: thick hot fudge
directions: In a medium saucepan, over low heat, melt chocolate and butter.
Stir in remaining ingredients.
Cook, stirring constantly, about 5 minutes or until mixture is slightly thickened.
Great for a sundae party!

title: spaghetti aglio olio
directions: Heat olive oil until barely warm.
Add garlic and allow to soak in the oil for 2 to 3 minutes.
Toss with pasta and ground pepper.
Garnish with parsley, basil and thyme.
Serve with tossed green salad or a green vegetable.

title: flipped western omelet
directions: Whip eggs and pour in flipping pan. Cook until set. Pour other ingredients into omelet; flip over and continue cooking until done.

title: louisiana pickled figs
directions: Cover figs with 2 quarts boiling water.
Let stand 5 minutes and drain.
Mix 1 cup water with vinegar and sugar in a large saucepan.
Add spices in bag.
Bring to boil and add figs.
Boil 10 minutes.
Let stand until next day.

title: whole wheat bread
directions: Combine flours.
In a large bowl, mix thoroughly flour mixture, sugar, salt and undissolved yeast.
Combine milk, water and margarine in saucepan.
Heat over low heat until liquids are very warm (120°).
Margarine does not need to melt.
Gradually add to dry ingredients and stir for 2 minutes.
If needed, stir in additional flour to make a stiff dough.
Turn onto a lightly floured board.
Knead until smooth (8 to 10 minutes).
Cover with plastic wrap and clean dish towel.
Let rest for 20 minutes.

title: spinach and beef dip
directions: Mix until well blended the first five ingredients.
Stir in remainder of ingredients until blended.
Serve with chips.

title: roast leg of lamb
directions: Wash meat and set aside in roasting pan.
In a small bowl, mix salt, pepper and minced garlic,
Cut incisions into leg of lamb with a sharp knife.
Into incisions, place seasoning mixture and a little butter.
Spread soft butter over leg, rubbing in rest of seasonings.
Pour juice of lemon over meat in pan.
Cook, covered, at 350° for 1 hour.
Add water to pan drippings and baste often until brown and tender.
Add small potatoes and continue to baste. Uncover last 1/2 hour to crisp skin of roast.

title: corn dogs
directions: Mix dry ingredients.
Add eggs and enough milk to make a thick batter.
Skewer hot dogs and dip into batter, then into hot oil until golden brown.
Having the batter in a large jar would help. Fry, turning once.
Cook about 6 minutes.
Drain on paper towel.

title: fish with rice stuffing
directions: Place fish in shallow pan.
Broil under moderate heat 15 minutes, basting with 2 tablespoons unsalted butter.
Turn; broil 10 minutes.
Season with pepper.
Cook mushrooms and onions in remaining 1/4 cup unsalted butter until tender.
Add rice, seasonings and eggs; mix well.
Cook over low heat until eggs are set.
Mound stuffing in center of serving platter.
Place fish, skin side up, over stuffing.

title: cherub cookies
directions: If dough is wiggly, add a few extra hugs until desired consistency is obtained.
Allow to stand 5 to 10 minutes for proper discipline.

title: vegetable salad
directions: Combine veggies. Marinate several hours in prepared Italian dressing.

title: strawberry pie
directions: Prepare strawberries.
Set aside to drain.
Pie crust should be baked and ready to fill.

title: hot tomato hamburger
directions: Brown meat and onion.
Drain.
Mix tomatoes and soup. Add to hamburger. Crush tortilla chips.
Layer all ingredients in 2-quart casserole, beginning and ending with tortilla chips.
Bake, uncovered, at 350° for 20 minutes or until bubbly.

title: peach brandy
directions: You will need a 1 gallon jar.

title: aaron's potato pancakes
directions: Mix together milk, eggs, potatoes, onion and flour.
Put small amounts into greased griddle or frypan (375° for electric frypan). Fry until brown on both sides, turning once.
Makes approximately 18 pancakes.
Serve with applesauce and sour cream.

title: grape breeze
directions: Combine sugar and water in pot and bring to a boil.
Cover and let stand for 1 hour.
Add grape and lemon juices, then add ginger ale.
Chill before serving.

title: broccoli with mushroom cheese sauce
directions: Cook broccoli in microwave or on stove top.
Heat butter on High for 30 seconds.
Stir in flour and milk.
Cook on High for 3 minutes, stirring every 30 seconds.
Stir in cheese, mushrooms and dill weed.
Cook on High for 1 minute.
Pour sauce over broccoli and serve.

title: seven minute frosting(50 years or older)
directions: In top of double boiler, beat over boiling
water with mixer for 7 minutes.
Remove from water and add vanilla.
Beat until vanilla is mixed in.

title: holiday egg nog
directions: Mix to taste.
Stir and serve cold.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Cook first four ingredients together in 1/2 cup boiling water for 5 to 8 minutes.
Drain.
Add rice, soups and water together with broccoli.
Add Cheddar cheese.
Mix together.
Pour into 13 x 9-inch buttered pan.
Top with crushed Ritz cracker crumbs and dot with butter.
Bake 40 minutes at 350°.

title: mojito
directions: In a tall glass with back of spoon crush mint with sugar and lime juice until sugar is dissolved and stir in rum. Add ice cubes and top off drink with club soda or seltzer water. Stir drink well and garnish with mint and lime.

title: county farm fire department chili
directions: Brown ground beef with onions, salt and pepper; drain.
Then add remaining ingredients except hot sauce.
Bring mixture to a boil, then reduce heat and simmer for 1 hour or until ready to serve.
Just before serving, add the hot sauce.
Yields 8 to 10 large servings.

title: cheese-bacon fingers(yield:  30)
directions: Preheat oven to 325°.
Combine cheese, bacon, mayonnaise, onion and celery salt; blend well.
Spread cheese mixture over each piece of bread.
Place on ungreased baking sheet.
Bake for 10 minutes. Preparation time:
25 minutes; cook time:
10 minutes.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Line an 8 x 12 x 2-inch casserole dish with the dried beef. Wrap the chicken breasts with bacon and lay on top of the beef. Mix cream of chicken soup and sour cream; pour on top of chicken. Bake for 3 hours in a 250° to 375° oven.

title: lasagne
directions: Fry or brown sausages.
Drain off fat.
Add onion and garlic and saute 10 minutes, until onion is brown.
Add tomatoes, water and basil and stir.
Cover and cook over low heat for three hours, stirring occasionally.
Correct seasoning; add parsley.
Place layer of noodles on bottom of buttered baking dish.
Add some sauce.
Mix water and cottage cheese together and spread some of it over sauce.
Sprinkle with Parmesan.
Repeat layers, ending with cottage cheese and
Parmesan on top.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes or until hot and bubbly.
Serves 6.

title: chicken and rice
directions: There is no salt in this recipe.
Scatter rice on bottom of pan.
Mix cream of celery soup with a can of milk.
Pour over rice and stir.
Gently place chicken pieces over rice (don't crowd). Sprinkle dry onion soup mix over chicken.
Cover and bake at 300° for 2 hours.

title: busy-day cake
directions: Grease and lightly flour a 9 x 9 x 2-inch baking pan.
In a small mixer bowl, combine all the ingredients.
Beat with electric mixer on low speed until combined.
Beat 2 minutes on medium speed. Turn into pan.
Bake at 375° for 25 to 30 minutes or until done.

title: lime jello salad
directions: Put the first 3 ingredients in blender; mix until well blended. Pour into a 3-cup jello mold which has been sprayed lightly with Pam.
Add the rest of the ingredients.
Chill until firm.

title: broccoli-ham soup
directions: In a 3-quart saucepan, cook the chopped onion in butter or margarine until tender, but not brown.
Stir in flour, chicken bouillon granules, mustard, thyme and pepper.
Add milk and water all at once.
Cook and stir over medium-high heat until thickened and bubbly.
Stir broccoli and cubed ham into saucepan.
Return to boiling.
Reduce heat; simmer for 4 to 6 minutes more or until broccoli is tender and the soup is heated through, stirring occasionally.
Makes 4 servings.

title: oatmeal peanut butter breakfast squares
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Line a 13 x 9-inch baking pan with foil or use foil pan.

title: mary's rolls
directions: Dissolve yeast in lukewarm water. Add sugar and salt to butter and grated lemon rind. Add flour to mixture and make a dough. Knead the dough until bubbles occur, then let rise until double in size.
Punch down and let rise again.
Make out into rolls and let rise.
Bake at 375° until golden brown.

title: ham-cheese dish
directions: Arrange in layers the bread and ham; then sprinkle with both cheeses.
Repeat another layer of the same ingredients.
Beat with a hand beater the milk, eggs, onion salt and dry mustard.
Pour entire mixture over the top layer.
Refrigerate overnight.
Take dish out of fridge 1 hour before baking.
Crushed corn flakes should be sprinkled over top before putting into oven.
Preheat oven to 375° and bake for 45 minutes.

title: prize winning chili
directions: Brown meat.
Pour off fat.
Add onions and saute until transparent.
Mix all ingredients in large boiler.
Cook on low heat for several hours.

title: summer squash casserole
directions: In saucepan, cook squash and onions in water for 5 minutes; drain well.
Combine soup and sour cream.
Stir in carrots, squash and onion.
Combine stuffing mix in greased 12 x 7 1/2 x 2-inch baking dish.
Spoon vegetable mix over stuffing.
Sprinkle remaining stuffing mixture on top of vegetable mixture.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.
Serves 6.

title: chicken wiggle
directions: Stuff hen with chopped onions and celery; salt and pepper to taste and bake in 350° oven until well done (2 hours).
Drain chicken stock and use to cook spaghetti.
Bone and cut up chicken. Mix cut up chicken with spaghetti, English peas, mushrooms and peppers.
Place in casserole dish and cook in 350° oven for 30 minutes.
Serves 12.

title: rice
directions: Mix all ingredients and bake in oven at 350° for 1 hour.

title: never fail fudge
directions: Put sugar, milk and margarine together, boil and stir until soft ball stage.
Take off stove and add marshmallows, chips, nuts and vanilla.
Stir but don't beat.
Pour into greased pan.

title: italian spam loaf
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
On cutting board, slice bread as though you were going to make sandwiches, being careful not to cut all the way through the bottom crust of bread.

title: apple pudding
directions: Sift flour, sugar, soda and spices together.
Cut in margarine.
Add egg, then apples and nuts.
Pour into greased and floured 9-inch pan and bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes.
Serve with warm sauce or Cool Whip.

title: baked spaghetti
directions: Mix together milk and eggs.
Put drained spaghetti in a large pan.
Put cheese on top.
Pour milk and egg mixture over this. Meat meat on next.
Pour sauce over top.
Bake at 350° for about 30 minutes.

title: corn macaroni salad
directions: In a large bowl, combine the macaroni, corn, celery, green pepper, scallions and tomatoes.
In a medium-sized bowl, combine the remaining ingredients.
Pour over the macaroni mixture and toss to blend.
Cover and chill for at least 3 hours or overnight.

title: bran muffins for dieters
directions: Combine dry ingredients. Combine liquids and add all at once to dry. Stir just to moisten. Makes 15 to 16 large muffins.
Bake at 350° for 18 to 20 minutes.

title: spanish beef on rice
directions: Cook onion, green pepper and celery in hot butter until yellow.
Add cooked tomatoes, salt and pepper and cook slowly 15 minutes.
Drain canned beef and heat until hot and then add remaining ingredients and continue cooking until hot.
Serve on bed of hot steaming rice.

title: bacon biscuits
directions: Sift
dry ingredients.
Cut in bacon fat until crumbly. Add milk
and
form
soft dough.
Turn out on floured board or floured wax
paper.
Knead
lightly.
Pat
to 3/4-inch thick. Cut biscuits
and
bake on ungreased cookie sheet in preheated 450° oven for about 10 minutes.

title: peanut butter cookies
directions: Cream eggs, sugars and shortening.
Add peanut butter.
Add sifted flour and soda.
Mix well.
Drop on ungreased cookie sheet. Bake at 350° for 8 to 12 minutes.

title: rotel chicken
directions: Cook chicken and debone.
Drain saving 1 cup broth.
Cook spaghetti and drain.
Saute onions.
Cut cheese into cubes.
Mix all together.
Add salt to taste.
Put in large baking dish.
Put in preheated oven at 350° for 10 minutes until cheese melts.

title: overnight french toast
directions: Place bread slices in baking dish. Combine eggs, milk, baking powder and vanilla.
Pour over bread.
Cover and refrigerate overnight.

title: chocolate fudge
directions: Cook sugar and water until it boils; add milk and cook until it forms a hard ball in water.
Remove from heat; add chocolate and beat until smooth and thick.
Pour in buttered pan.

title: marshmallow custard
directions: Beat eggs slightly.
Then add the sugar, cream and vanilla. Combine thoroughly.
Place a marshmallow in the bottom of each of 6 custard cups and pour the custard mixture over them.
Place the custards in a pan of hot water and bake at 325° for 40 minutes or until a silver knife will come out clean when inserted in the custard.
Place in the refrigerator to cool and serve in the cups.

title: southwestern hash
directions: Saute the onion and celery in the oil and garlic butter.
Add ground chuck and cook until beef is no longer pink.
Turn off heat and add tomatoes and spaghetti.
Pour into 1 1/2 quart oiled casserole.
Cover with foil and bake at 350 degrees for about 40 to 45 minutes.
Taste and add salt and black pepper, if needed.

title: chili rellenos
directions: Thoroughly mix flour, eggs and half and half.
Set aside. Grate cheeses and set aside.
Alternate in thin layers cheese, chilies and milk mixture.
(Thin layers are the best.)
Top with tomato sauce and remaining 1 cup of cheese.
Bake at 350° for 40 to 50 minutes.
Let stand 15 minutes before serving.

title: peanut butter chocolate chip cookies
directions: Beat together oleo and peanut butter.
Add eggs and brown and white sugar; mix well.
Sift soda and salt to flour and sift.
Stir into sugar mixture; mix well.
Add chocolate chips and nuts if desired.
Drop by teaspoons onto ungreased cookie sheets.
Bake at 350° for 10 to 15 minutes.

title: cornmeal cookies
directions: In large mixer bowl, beat sugar, shortening, eggs and lemon extract or lemon juice with electric mixer until blended.
In bowl, stir together flour, cornmeal, baking powder, nutmeg and salt.
Add to shortening mixture and beat thoroughly.
Stir in raisins.
Drop from teaspoon 2-inches apart onto greased cookie sheet.
Bake in 375° oven for 10 to 12 minutes.
Cool.
Makes 48 cookies.

title: cranberry gelatin mold
directions: Bring water to a boil. In medium saucepan, add water to gelatin; stir until dissolved. Add cranberry sauce and sour cream. Beat with a rotary beater until well blended. Chill until almost set. Fold in oranges and nuts. Spoon into 5-cup gelatin mold (ring). Chill completely.

title: hot tamale pie
directions: Sift cornmeal into rapidly boiling water, stirring constantly. Cook until thick and salt to taste.
Line bottom and sides of large (11 x 7 x 2-inch) baking dish with cornmeal mixture, reserving some for top.
Brown ground meat, garlic, onion and green pepper in the oil.
Add tomatoes, chili powder and salt. Simmer 10 minutes.
Pour into cornmeal lined pan and dot with remaining cornmeal.
Bake in 350° oven for 30 minutes.

title: china boy hash
directions: Heat cooking oil in frying pan, then add next 4 ingredients in the order given.
Saute to soften.
Stir to break up meat and continue cooking until no pink color remains.

title: zucchini bread
directions: Preheat oven to 325°.
Grease two 8 x 4-inch loaf pans generously with shortening.
Line the bottom of pans with waxed paper and grease that.

title: texas jalapeno jelly
directions: Puree jalapenos, half of the green peppers and 1/2 c. vinegar in a blender or food processor; pour into a large kettle.
Repeat with remaining green peppers and another 1/2 c. vinegar.
Add sugar, cayenne and remaining vinegar to kettle.
Bring to a rolling boil over high heat, stirring constantly.
Quickly stir in pectin and return to a boil.
Boil for 1 minute, stirring constantly.
Remove from the heat; skim off foam.
Add food coloring if desired.
Ladle hot liquid into hot jars, leaving 1/4 inch headspace.
Cover with lids.
Process for 10 minutes in a boiling water bath.
Serve over cream cheese with crackers if desired.

title: ham and noodle
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Grease 1 1/2-quart casserole. Cook noodles according to package directions.

title: ham-spaghetti skillet
directions: Dice bacon and fry until crisp.
Remove from skillet.
Use 2 tablespoons bacon drippings and fry onion and bell pepper until tender.
Add ham and brown lightly.
Add garlic, tomatoes and bacon. Simmer for 30 minutes. Remove garlic.
Cook spaghetti in usual manner and drain.
Add spaghetti and cheese to skillet. Simmer, uncovered, about 10 minutes.
Season, if desired.
Serves 4 to 6.
Great dish for leftover ham.
I add a pinch of mixed herbs.

title: sausage-hamburger casserole
directions: Cook hamburger, sausage and onion until done.
Drain.
Cube cheese and add tomatoes.
Microwave cheese and tomatoes at 70% power for 10 minutes.
Stir.
When melted, add meat mixture to this.

title: grilled fish and shrimp
directions: Mix oil, 1/4 cup lemon juice, thyme, paprika, salt and pepper. Toss fish and shrimp in mixture.
Can be marinated up to 4 hours. Preheat charcoal grill or broiler.
Alternate shrimp, fish, onion and peppers on skewers.
Cook 4 to 5 minutes each side.
Sprinkle with remaining lemon juice.

title: porcupines
directions: Mix meat, rice, salt, pepper and onion together.
Shape into balls.
Cook until meat balls are browned on all sides.
Mix remaining ingredients.
Pour over meatballs.
Heat to boiling. Reduce heat.
Cover and simmer for 45 minutes.
Add more water during cooking if necessary.

title: icing for 125-year-old walnut pound cake
directions: Blend butter, sugar and salt.
Add flavoring and 2 tablespoons milk.
Gradually add remaining milk until desired consistency is reached and add nuts.

title: chicken divan
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Melt butter in saucepan over medium heat; blend in flour, slowly add broth and milk and heat, stirring until thickened.
Mix in salt, pepper, nutmeg, 1/4 cup cheese and sherry.
Arrange broccoli in single layer in buttered 2-quart au gratin or shallow casserole and sprinkle with remaining 2 tablespoons cheese.
Top with chicken slices.
Beat cream until soft peaks form and fold in sauce; pour over chicken.
Bake uncovered 1/2 hour until bubbly.
Broil quickly to brown and serve.
Serves 6.

title: morning glory muffins
directions: Combine flour, sugar, soda and cinnamon in mixing bowl and set aside.
Combine carrots, apples, dates, raisins, nuts and prunes. Stir in beaten eggs, oil and vanilla.
Add to dry ingredients, stirring until moistened.
Bake at 375° for 18 to 20 minutes. Makes 14 or 16 muffins.

title: buttermilk pie
directions: Cream together butter and sugar until fluffy.
Mix flour and salt; add eggs one at a time and beat until mixed well.
Add buttermilk and vanilla and beat until well combined.
Pour in pie shell.
Bake at 325° for 50 minutes.

title: candy
directions: Boil over medium heat until soft ball stage the sugar, cream, water and salt.
Take off heat and stir in the margarine, vanilla, cocoa (if using), nuts (if using) and peanut butter.
Mix well. Pour in a buttered pan and cool.

title: roast pork boulanger
directions: Preheat oven to 425°.
Wipe pork with damp paper towels.
Rub outside of pork with cut sides of garlic.
Combine 1 1/2 teaspoons salt, thyme, bay leaf and 1/4 teaspoon pepper; rub over pork to coat well.
Insert garlic slivers, where possible, in any crevices in bone.
Place pork, fat side up, in large shallow roasting pan. Place onion, carrot and parsley under the roast.
Roast, uncovered, 1 hour.
Remove pork and vegetables from roasting pan; discard fat and bay leaf.
Return pork to pan.
Gently toss sliced potato with chopped onion and the parsley, salt and pepper. Arrange around roast.
Heat chicken broth to boiling; pour over potatoes.
Brush with melted butter.
Reduce oven to 400°.
Bake 1 hour longer.
Sprinkle with chopped parsley.

title: hawaiian cake
directions: Bake cake as directed on package; cool.
Have pudding prepared.
With a fork, punch holes in cake.
Slowly pour pineapple juice into cake.
Spread pudding over cake.
Mix drained pineapple, coconut and Cool Whip and spread over cake. Refrigerate overnight.

title: cherry cream dessert
directions: Mix well - chill and serve.

title: spaghetti sauce
directions: Core and cook 1/2 bushel tomatoes to get juice.
Add green peppers, onion, garlic powder and cooking oil.
Cook for 30 minutes.
Add tomato paste, salt, basil, sugar and oregano. Simmer for about 2 hours.
Fill jars with sauce and seal.
Makes 12 or 13 quarts.

title: chocolate pound cake
directions: In a large bowl, beat together butter, sugar and vanilla with an electric mixer on medium speed until light and fluffy, 1 to 2 minutes.
Add cocoa and beat well.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating well after each addition.

title: hash brown casserole
directions: Mix all together and place in casserole.
Bake at 350° for 50 minutes.
If desired, may be topped with buttered bread crumbs, during last 20 minutes of baking.

title: german frikadellen
directions: Crumble crackers and mix all ingredients.
Put oil in a skillet.
Pat into patty and cook until brown.

title: pudding cakes
directions: Mix well. Drop on cookie sheet. Add chocolate chips for design. Bake at 375° for 8 minutes.
Makes 12 to 18 cookies.

title: sweet potato casserole
directions: Melt margarine in casserole dish.
Combine all other ingredients and add about 1/2 of margarine.
Mix well.
Pour into the casserole dish and top with nuts and/or coconut.
Pour remaining margarine on top.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour.

title: lemon bars
directions: Mix margarine with 2 cups flour and powdered sugar.
Put in 9 x 13-inch pan and bake 15 minutes at 350°.
Sift together sugar, 1 tablespoon flour and baking powder.
Beat eggs; add lemon juice. Add to sugar mixture.
Pour on top of crust and bake 25 minutes. Dust with powdered sugar.

title: mandarin orange salad
directions: Mix the cracker crumbs, sugar and oleo.
Press most of this mixture in a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Reserve some crumbs for top.
Blend together the orange juice and Eagle Brand milk.
Stir in the Cool Whip and oranges.
Pour over the crumb crust.
Chill, or you may freeze, being sure to cover with foil or plastic wrap.

title: apple, cranberry, carrot muffins
directions: In large mixing bowl, combine apples and sugar.
Gently fold in cranberries, carrots and nuts.
Combine dry ingredients with a fork in a separate bowl; add to apple mixture, mixing well with fork to moisten dry ingredients.
Combine eggs and oil; stir into apple mixture.
Bake in greased muffin tins at 375° for 20 to 25 minutes.
Cool 5 minutes before removing from tins.
Yield:
18 muffins.

title: fine potato salad
directions: Mix well all ingredients and refrigerate for 1 hour.

title: chicken broccoli casserole
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease a 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking dish. Layer broccoli in baking dish.
Add a layer of chicken.
Heat chicken soup with mayonnaise, lemon juice and curry powder.
Pour soup mixture over chicken.
Sprinkle with cheese.
Bake about 30 minutes, until bubbly hot.

title: favorite white bread
directions: In a large bowl, dissolve yeast and sugar in water.
Let stand until foamy.
Mix in salt, milk and 3 1/2 cups flour.
Mix until thoroughly blended.
Add oil and gradually blend in enough flour to make a soft dough.
Knead 10 minutes.
Shape into ball and place in greased bowl.
Let rise until double in size.
Punch down and make into 2 loaves or 9 x 13-inch pan of rolls.
Let rise again.
Bake at 400° for 30 to 35 minutes.
Will sound hollow when tapped.

title: baked pork chops
directions: Wash pork chops.
Dip in egg, then bread crumbs to coat. Arrange in shallow oven dish.
Cover bottom in water.
Cover dish with tinfoil.
Bake in oven at 325° for 1 hour.

title: chili sauce
directions: Peel tomatoes and onions.
Remove seeds from green peppers; chop fine.
Stir together with salt, sugar, cinnamon, ground cloves, vinegar, Tabasco sauce and hot red peppers (optional). Cook slowly for 4 to 6 hours, or until thick, stirring occasionally.
Pour into hot, sterilized jars and seal.
Makes 4 pints.

title: cheesy asparagus casserole
directions: Melt butter in a heavy saucepan over low heat; add flour, stirring until smooth.
Add soup and Cheddar cheese; cook until cheese melts and mixture is smooth, stirring constantly.
Layer half each of egg slices, asparagus and cheese sauce in lightly greased 10 x 6 x 2-inch baking dish.
Repeat layers; sprinkle bread crumbs.
Bake at 325° for 30 minutes.
Makes 8 servings.

title: pecan squares
directions: Combine first four ingredients and pour into a jelly roll pan. Bake 20 minutes.
Combine remaining ingredients and add to jelly roll pan mixture.
Bake 25 minutes, until set.

title: pecan pie
directions: Mix and pour into 9-inch unbaked crust.
Cook abut 50 minutes at 350°.

title: ginger crinkles
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Mix oil and sugar evenly.
Add egg and beat well.
Stir in syrup.
Sift dry ingredients together and add to other mixture.
Drop teaspoonfuls into sugar and form into balls.
Place on ungreased cookie sheet, 3 inches apart.
Bake 15 minutes.

title: spiced russian tea
directions: Combine first 6 ingredients.
Mix well.
To serve individual servings, place 2 to 3 teaspoons mixture into mug and fill with boiling water.
Garnish with orange slice or a lemon slice, if desired.

title: frozen cucumber pickles
directions: Sprinkle salt over cukes and onions; let stand 2 hours. Drain off water. Combine sugar and vinegar and pour over pickles.
Let stand 10 minutes. Stir and place pickles in freezer containers. Keep frozen at least 2 days before eating. Thaw at room temperature, then keep refrigerated. Will keep in freezer for 1 year.

title: fudge ribbon cake
directions: Prepare cake mix as package directs.
Pour batter into well-greased and floured Bundt pan.
In small bowl, beat cheese, margarine and cornstarch until fluffy.
Gradually beat in condensed milk, then egg and vanilla.
Pour evenly over cake batter.
Bake at 350° for 50 minutes.
Glaze.
Store, covered, in refrigerator.

title: cookie and ice cream frozen dessert(makes 12 servings)
directions: Suggested Toppings:
Whipped cream, chocolate curls, chopped nuts, chocolate syrup and caramel topping.

title: christmas scripture recipe
directions: Cream butter with sugar.
Beat in yolk of eggs, one at a time. Sift together flour, salt, baking powder, cinnamon and spices. Beat into creamed mixture alternately with milk.
Beat whites of eggs until stiff; fold in.

title: yuletide persimmon pudding(in honor of george wilfong)
directions: Mix the baking soda into the pulp, then the sugars which equal 2 1/2 cups all together.
Then add 2 large eggs and mix real well. Next, add the flour, baking powder, cinnamon, vanilla and salt; mix real well.
Melt butter or margarine in a 9 x 13 x 2-inch pan; see that it goes over sides of pan also, as want pan to be well-greased.
After pan is well-greased, pour the remaining butter into the persimmon mixture, stirring it in well.
Then, add milk.
Mix well.
Will be a very thin batter.
Bake at 325°
for 55 to 65 minutes, or until pudding is firm and breaks away from sides of baking pan.
Cool.

title: peaches and cream cake
directions: Mix cake mix, pudding, eggs, water and oil and pour in greased and floured pan.
Arrange peaches on cake batter.
Mix cream cheese, sugar and peach juice; spread on top of peaches.
Bake in 350° oven 50 to 60 minutes.
Sprinkle powdered sugar on top when cool.

title: squash dressing
directions: Saute onion in 1/2 stick margarine.
Add to soup mixture and mix well with cooked and crumbled cornbread.
I double recipe and when I do this I dissolve 3 chicken bouillon cubes in 2 cups water. I also use unsalted margarine.
Pour into baking dish that has been sprayed with Pam and bake in preheated oven at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: hot chicken salad
directions: Mix these 3 ingredients together and sprinkle evenly over chicken mixture.
(Can be done a day ahead.)
Bake at 375° for 30 minutes.
Watch carefully the last 10 minutes or so to be sure almonds don't burn.

title: tortellini salad
directions: Cook tortellini; drain.
Cool in refrigerator.
Mix all other ingredients together; mix with cooled pasta.
Cover and refrigerate until ready to use.

title: chocolate fudge
directions: Combine sugar, milk and butter together in 4-quart saucepan. Cook on low to medium heat.
When starts to boil, cook for about 25 minutes, stirring often.
Mixture will be thick.
(Drop a small amount in cold water to form a ball; if you can pick it up with fingers, it is done).
Turn off stove.
Leave on stove and add marshmallows, chocolate chips, vanilla and nuts.
Stir until mixed well.
Pour into buttered 13 x 9-inch pan. Cool. Cut into squares.

title: hamburger soup
directions: In skillet, brown hamburger; drain.
Add onion, carrots, celery and cabbage.
Combine tomato paste, Worcestershire sauce and beef bouillon.
Add to crock-pot and stir to blend.
Cover and cook on low setting for several hours.
Makes 8 servings.

title: squash casserole
directions: Combine
all
ingredients (except squash) and mix well. Mix with
squash
and pour into a greased dish.
Bake at 375° for about 40 minutes.

title: angel biscuits
directions: Dissolve yeast in warm water.
Sift all dry ingredients together a couple of times in large bowl.
Cut in shortening.
Add buttermilk and yeast mixture; work dough only until well moistened.
Cover and refrigerate to use as needed.
Bake in a 400° oven until nicely browned, about 12 minutes.
Keeps for a full week in refrigerator.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Cook rice according to directions on package.
Cook broccoli several minutes.
Mix and place all ingredients into buttered casserole and bake at 350° for 30 minutes or until brown on top.

title: frozen orange-cranberry mold
directions: Combine cranberry sauce, undiluted orange juice concentrate, sugar and salt; beat with electric or rotary beater to blend. Fold in whipped cream and food coloring.
Turn into 1-quart mold and freeze until firm.
Serves 4 to 6.

title: mom's best split pea soup
directions: Over a hot fire, cover ham bone with 3 to 4 quarts of water and simmer for at least 1 hour.
Remove bone and let cool.
Using the same water, cook the peas with onion, garlic and carrots until soft (about 1 hour).
