Cut ham meat from bone and add to soup. Place covered kettle on back of stove and simmer very slowly until ready to serve, stirring often. Serves 6.

title: good and easy pizza dough
directions: 1. Combine ingredients in the order shown. Add flour until dough is stiff. Let rise if you prefer thick crust.
2. Grease pan. Pat out dough and prick with fork. Turn
edges. Bake at 425° for 7-8 minutes.
3. Freeze or top with sauce and your favorite toppings to
eat right away.
4. Bake at 425° for 10-12 minutes or more until cheese
bubbles. Makes 2 round or 1 oblong pizza.

title: peanut butter balls or deb's buckeyes
directions: Mix first 3 ingredients.
Roll into 1-inch balls.
Melt together in saucepan chips and wax.
Dip peanut butter balls into mixture.
Place on wax paper and let cool.

title: fruit punch
directions: Mix a small can of frozen pineapple juice and a small can of frozen grapefruit juice.
Add ginger ale.
Slice orange and lemon. Add jar of cherries.
Stir in just enough cranberry cocktail juice to give it color.
Add rainbow sherbet.
Don't mix it in. Just let it dissolve in the punch.
Add enough ice to keep it cool.

title: well-done kids
directions: Mix kids and dogs on field, stirring constantly.
Pour brook over pebbles and sprinkle field with flowers.
Cover with skin and bake in sunshine.
When brown, set in bathtub to cool.

title: lemon lime fluff dessert
directions: Pulverize graham crackers to make 1 1/2 cups crumbs.
Blend in sugar and melted margarine.
Reserve scant 1/2 cup and pat rest of mixture into bottom of high rimmed dish approximately 8 x 11-inch.

title: cheese sauce
directions: In blender, combine cottage cheese and milk.
Process until smooth.
In small saucepan, heat mixture over low heat, stirring constantly.
Add cheese and pepper.
Stir until the cheese melts.

title: cranberry candied yams
directions: Cut yams in half lengthwise.
Place in shallow pan.
Mix cranberry sauce and lemon juice well; spread over yams.
Gently warm honey, butter and bourbon; pour over yams.
Bake for 25 minutes at 350°, basting occasionally with honey mixture.
Serves 4.

title: banana tart
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Line pie plate with pastry.
Spread thinly with jam.
Slice bananas and place in plate between layers of jam.
*Make lattice cover by cutting rolled pastry into thin strips and crisscrossing over filling, if desired.
Bake 15 minutes or until the pastry is brown.
Serve hot or cold with hot custard sauce or cream.

title: asparagus casserole
directions: Place asparagus in long baking dish.
Crumble crackers over asparagus.
Mix liquid and soup.
Beat well and pour over asparagus.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.
Cool, then top with sliced boiled eggs.

title: potato salad
directions: Cook and cool potatoes. Remove peeling and chop into bite size pieces. Add onion eggs if desired.

title: california skillet
directions: In large skillet, heat oil.
Add meat and onion and cook until meat is not pink.
Stir in chili powder.
Add remaining ingredients except cheese.
Cover; simmer 20 minutes, stirring often, until pasta is done.
Sprinkle with cheese; cover and cook until cheese melts.

title: pumpkin pie
directions: Blend ingredients well.
Turn into pie shell.
Bake at 350° until knife inserted in center of pie comes out clean.

title: chicken burritos
directions: Spread out crescent roll triangles on baking sheet.
Put 1 tablespoon chicken on each.
Put 1/2 slice of cheese on each and fold over.
Seal edges.
Pour mushroom soup on top of fold-overs. Bake until golden brown following crescent roll directions.
Easy for children to make.

title: chili soup
directions: Cook first 5 ingredients until browned.
Add the last 3 ingredients and simmer for 1 hour.
Good served with cornbread or crackers.

title: home canned sandwich spread
directions: Put first 4 ingredients through a food chopper, then drain. Add vinegar, water and brown sugar.
Cook all together until tender.
Add dry mustard, cornstarch and salt mixed with a little water.
When thickened, add salad dressing.
Bring to a boil, pack and seal.
Process.

title: chicken durango
directions: Mix all ingredients, except chicken.

Marinate chicken in sauce for 3 to 4 hours. Place chicken in baking dish, skin up, and bake uncovered at 325° or until done, which is usually 45 minutes. Baste with lemon butter occasionally as it is cooking.

title: chocolate fudge sauce
directions: Bring cocoa, sugar, milk and syrup to a boil, stirring constantly.
Reduce heat so it keeps a gentle boil and until it forms a soft ball in cold water.
Then add the butter and vanilla; wait 15 minutes and then stir well.
(I bake a chocolate cake, cut in large squares and place an ice cream square in the middle of the cake.
Top with the fudge sauce, whipped cream, nuts and a cherry.)

title: four layer dessert
directions: First Layer:
Mix flour and butter.
Press in pan.
Put nuts over top.
Bake at 300° for 30 minutes.

title: blueberry muffins
directions: In medium bowl, combine flour, sugar, baking powder, salt and spice; mix well.
Put milk, eggs and oil together.
Make a well in center of dry ingredients.
Pour egg mixture into well.
Quickly stir with a fork or spoon just until flour mixture is moistened. Batter will be lumpy.
Gently fold in blueberries.

title: applesauce cake
directions: Mix until smooth and creamy.
Spread on cake.

title: ham loaf
directions: Mix ham, egg, onion, milk and graham cracker crumbs.
Shape into loaf.
Bake 1 hour at 350°.
In meantime, make glaze by mixing brown sugar, vinegar and dry mustard.

title: fruit salad
directions: Drain pineapple chunks, mandarin oranges and grapes.
Add to peach pie filling.
Add marshmallows.
Mix together and refrigerate.
(Make night before.)

title: kroger rodeo supper
directions: Melt butter in skillet.
Cook macaroni as directed on package. Do not add cheese.
While macaroni is cooking, add hamburger and onion in butter.
Drain.
Add tomato sauce.
Fill sauce can with water and add to mixture.
Add chili powder and garlic salt. Drain macaroni and add to mixture.
Sprinkle cheese on top.
Mix with fork.
Simmer 20 minutes.
Serves 4.

title: overnight coffee cake
directions: Combine the first 7 ingredients in a large mixing bowl.
Add buttermilk, butter and eggs.
Beat at low speed with an electric mixer until moistened; beat at medium speed for 3 minutes.
Spoon batter into a greased and floured 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan.

title: feast day cookies
directions: Blend shortening and sugar until fluffy.
In another bowl, mix rest of dry ingredients.
Add to sugar mixture.
Add water gradually until nonsticky dough is formed.
Add pinons.
Roll out on lightly floured board until 1/2-inch thick.
Cut into fancy shapes.
Sprinkle with sugar and cinnamon.
Bake in 375° oven until brown.

title: nasty bars
directions: Combine caramels and evaporated milk in a double boiler. Cook over low heat until caramels are melted and mixture is smooth. Set aside.

title: brownie camp-out coffee can ice cream
directions: Mix first 3 ingredients together and pour in 1-pound coffee can.
(You will probably have enough liquid for two (1-pound) cans.)
Place lid on can and secure with duct tape.
Put this can inside of a 3-pound coffee can.
Place ice all the way around the smaller can.
Sprinkle a little rock salt on top of ice.
Close can.
Roll the can back and forth between several friends for about 10 minutes.
Open the can and drain the water.
Add more ice and salt.
(Pour melted salt water outside on gravel.)
Roll until the ice cream is frozen (30 to 40 minutes).

title: mushroom barley soup
directions: Wash barley and cover with 6 cups beef stock.
Bring to boiling point and simmer until tender and then add butter gradually.
In the remaining stock, boil the vegetables and mushrooms.
Then add the cooked barley and season with salt and pepper.
You can add a few tablespoons of sour cream if you desire.
Makes about 3 gallons.

title: barbecued meatballs
directions: Pour milk over bread crumbs; add meat and salt and pepper. Shape into medium balls; place meatballs in casserole.
Combine water, catsup, vinegar, Worcestershire sauce, sugar, green pepper and onion.
Pour over meatballs.
Bake at 375° for 45 minutes.

title: mama spivey's beef vegetable soup
directions: Cook vegetables in small amount of water until tender.
Cook ground beef and onion in skillet with a little oil until it changes color.
Add ground beef, onion, tomatoes and broth to vegetables and simmer 2 or 3 hours.
Salt and pepper to taste. Lots of pepper is best.

title: easy blackberry cobbler
directions: Pour melted butter in bottom of casserole dish.
Combine flour, sugar and milk.
Pour over butter.
Do not stir.
In saucepan combine berries, 1/2 cup water and 1/2 cup sugar; bring to a boil.
Pour over flour.
Do not stir.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: chocolate chip pie
directions: Preheat oven to 325°.
In a large bowl, beat eggs until foamy. Add flour, sugar and brown sugar. Beat until well blended.
Add in melted butter.
Stir in chocolate chips and walnuts.
Pour into pie shell and bake for 1 hour.

title: fire and ice pickles
directions: Put pickles in large bowl.
Add the rest of the ingredients, except for garlic cloves.
Set for 2 hours, stirring occasionally. Put into jars.
Slice garlic cloves and add to pickles in the jars.
Cover and enjoy!

title: honey oatmeal cookies
directions: Heat oven to 375°.
Mix sugar, shortening, eggs and honey. Stir in remaining ingredients.
Drop dough by rounded teaspoonful about 2 inches apart onto ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake until light brown, 8 to 10 minutes.
Immediately remove from cookie sheet. Makes about 5 dozen cookies.

title: sweet corn pudding
directions: Grate corn and mix it in the milk, rubbing well to get hulls free.
Then rub through a fine sieve to get rid of hulls.
Work the flour and butter to a cream, then beat in sugar and well beaten yolks.
Then add the beaten whites and add all to the corn and milk mixture, with salt to taste.
Bake.
Eat as side dish with cream and sugar as pudding.

title: applesauce
directions: Quarter, core and peel the apples.
Cut apple quarters in half and put them in a saucepan.
Add water and sprinkle on cinnamon. Then cover and simmer until tender, about 20 minutes.
Mash apples with a potato masher or with a blender.
Cool and eat.
Makes 6 small servings.

title: peaches 'n cream pie
directions: Beat pudding, milk, egg and margarine 2 minutes. Pour into a 10-inch greased pie pan. Add a large can of drained, sliced peaches to pudding mixture. Save 3 tablespoons juice.

title: macaroni salad
directions: Cook macaroni; pour in colander and rinse with cold water.
Set aside to cool.
Mix mayonnaise, vinegar, salt and pepper.
Stir in these ingredients with chilled macaroni and vegetables.

title: spectacular chicken & wild rice casserole
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Combine all ingredients in a large bowl.
Transfer to a greased 9x13 inch glass baking dish.
Bake 25 to 30 minutes.
Serves 6 to 8.
If freezing for later use, freeze before baking.

title: dump cake
directions: Dump ingredients in order given in a greased 9 x 13 pan. Bake at 375° for 50 to 60 minutes.
Serve with Cool Whip or ice cream.
(This is a very good last minute dessert.)

title: cream-sauced seafood over fettuccine
directions: Cook fettuccine according to package, but without added salt. Spray an unheated medium saucepan with nonstick spray.
In the saucepan, combine the broth, onions, basil, garlic and pepper. Bring to a boil.
In a medium bowl, use a wire whisk to stir together the milk and flour until smooth.
Stir into the broth mixture.
Cook and stir over medium heat until the mixture thickens and begins to gently boil.
Cook and stir for 1 minute more.
Stir in the shrimp, crabmeat or lobster and snow peas. Cook and stir about 3 minutes or until the seafood is heated through.
Serve over the fettuccine.

title: chicken enchilada
directions: Combine first 4 ingredients and boil for approximately 1 hour. Remove chicken from bone.
Shred chicken; add 1/2 cup diced onion, Parmesan cheese, Monterey Jack and Cheddar cheese to suit taste. Heat corn tortillas (1 to 2 packages) in a skillet with 1 tablespoon of oil.
Spoon chicken mix onto tortilla, roll and place in an 8 x 11-inch glass dish.
In blender, add green chilies, tomatoes, egg and whipping cream.
Blend until smooth.
Pour over tortillas and grate Monterey Jack and Cheddar cheese over top of sauce.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.
Let stand for at least 5 minutes.
Serve with a tossed salad.

title: cream cheese pound cake
directions: Cream the margarine, cream cheese and sugar until light and fluffy. Add salt and vanilla; beat well. Add eggs, one at a time, beating well after each addition. Stir in flour.
Spoon mixture into greased 10-inch tube pan. Bake at 325° for 1 hour and 30 minutes.

title: scallop with broccoli
directions: Heat wok or pan over high heat.
Add oil; heat until hot.
Add garlic (smashed) until smell of aroma.
Then add salt, sugar, scallops, broccoli, ginger and cooking wine and stir for 30 seconds.
Add chicken broth and continue stirring until well done and serve.

title: mandarin orange dessert
directions: Drain oranges; reserve syrup.
Take 1/4 cup of syrup, add water to make 1 cup.
Dissolve Jell-O in boiling water, then add the cup of water and juice.
Add sherbet by spoonfuls, stirring until melted.
Chill until thick.
Fold in oranges.
Save some to garnish.
Return to refrigerator until ready to serve.

title: fruit cocktail, cream cheese salad
directions: Bring fruit cocktail to a boil.
Mix envelope jello in.
Mix in cream cheese, looks curdled.
Cool.
Beat Dream Whip and fold in. Pour in mold.

title: sweet potato casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients together and pour in 2-quart casserole.

title: cottage cheese dessert
directions: Mix together the orange jello, cottage cheese and mandarin oranges.
Fold Cool Whip into jello-cheese mixture; chill.

title: oyster soup
directions: Drain oysters in a colander.
Reserve juice.
Refrigerate until ready to use.
Saute green onions in butter until tender. Add oyster juice and simmer for 15 minutes.
Add oysters and simmer until edges begin to curl.
Add milk, but do not allow milk to boil.
When milk is scalded, add parsley and other seasonings.

title: aunt shirley's chocolate delight
directions: Make pudding.
Place graham crackers (whole) in 8 x 11-inch pan.
Put pudding over crackers, then add layer of Cool Whip. Refrigerate 3 hours or overnight.
Graham crackers will become cake like.
Very easy to do and can be made with pudding of your choice.

title: baking pan coating
directions: In mixer bowl blend shortening and flour until thoroughly creamed.
Then add oil, whipping until the consistency of mayonnaise.
Add coloring, if desired.
Keep in covered, wide mouthed container.
Brush on pan with pastry brush.

title: sausage and liver pate
directions: In skillet, cook sausage and onions until meat is brown and onion tender.
Remove from drippings with slotted spoon.
Use same skillet and cook livers in drippings over medium heat for 8 minutes or until done.
Drain thoroughly and cool lightly.
In blender, combine livers, milk and mustard; process well.
Add sausage, cream cheese, herbs seasoning and garlic powder.
Blend well.
Line a 3 cup mold with plastic wrap.
Spoon in mixture. Chill overnight.
Unmold onto serving plate.
Remove plastic wrap. Garnish with parsley.

title: meaty meatballs
directions: Melt butter in skillet.
Add pepper and onion.
Cook until tender.
Stir in soups and water.
Bring to a boil.
Turn down heat and simmer, stirring occasionally.
While sauce cooks, make the meatballs.
Beat egg in bowl.
Add ground beef, bread pieces, milk and salt.
Shape meatballs about ping-pong ball size.
Drop into simmering sauce for 1 hour or until thick.
Makes 6 servings.

title: cauliflower chowder
directions: In a large saucepan, combine cauliflower and 1/2 cup water. Cover and cook about 5 minutes or until tender.
Do not drain. Cut up large pieces.
Mash all of the cauliflower slightly.
Stir in the condensed potato soup.
Stir in milk and Swiss cheese. Cook and stir until cheese is melted and soup is heated through. Makes 6 servings.

title: celery noodle casserole
directions: Cook beef in large skillet until well browned.
Drain off excess fat.
Add celery and water; cover and simmer 10 minutes or until celery is tender-crisp.
Stir in soup and milk.
Add noodles and cheese.
Mix thoroughly.
Turn into a greased 2-quart casserole.
Top with potato chips.
Bake in a 350° oven for 40 minutes.
Makes 6 servings.

title: frosty mandarin dessert
directions: Drain oranges, reserving juice.
Add water to juice to make 1 cup syrup.
Dissolve jello in 2 cups boiling water.
Add syrup and orange sherbet.
Mix until melted; chill until thick.
Add orange slices.
Pour into large mold; refrigerate until solid.
Remove mold onto bed of lettuce and serve.
Wonderfully fruity and light!

title: fruit spritzer punch
directions: Combine ingredients in a punch bowl.
Makes 27 (4 ounce) servings.

title: oven caramel corn
directions: Place corn in a roaster pan.
Place margarine, sugar, corn syrup and salt in a saucepan.
Boil 5 minutes.
Stir in vanilla and soda.
Pour over popcorn in roaster and stir.
Bake at 250° for 1 hour, stirring every 15 minutes.

title: king's inn shrimp batter
directions: Beat eggs and milk together.
Pour over shrimp and leave overnight.
Drain shrimp and roll in cracker meal before frying.

title: maili turkey loaf
directions: Mix all ingredients and put into loaf pan.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: company beef stew
directions: In Dutch oven, brown meat, a little at a time.
Discard excess fat.
Add salt and pepper.
Stir in beef broth and water.
Bring to a boil.
Add bay leaf and cloves.
Reduce heat.
Simmer, covered, until meat is almost tender, for about 1 1/4 hours.

title: strawberry ice cream
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Mix thoroughly.
Freeze in ice cream freezer according to manufacturer's directions.
Garnish with fresh strawberries.

title: stuffed chicken breasts
directions: Pound chicken breasts between 2 pieces of wax paper until thin.
Lay 2 slices ham and 1 slice cheese on each breast.
Roll up breasts into bundles; secure with toothpicks (if necessary). Beat eggs and milk.
Dip each breast bundle into egg mixture, then roll into bread crumbs to fully cover.
Refrigerate for about 30 minutes or longer to set crumbs.
Lightly brown breasts in skillet on each side.
Bake in a 325° oven, uncovered, for about 20 to 30 minutes.
Add some steamed broccoli or asparagus with rice, and you're set.
Serves 4.

title: supper for twelve
directions: Cover meat with water and boil for 20 minutes.
Add noodles, celery, onion and green pepper.
Boil for 25 minutes longer. Remove from heat.
Add Velveeta cheese and pimento.

title: pinwheels
directions: Mix together dressing mix, cream cheese and onions. Spread on tortillas. Drain pimiento and chilies and blot dry with a paper towel. Sprinkle on top of cream cheese. Roll tortillas tightly and chill at least 2 hours. Cut rolls into 1-inch pieces. Serve with spirals facing up.

title: spicy cheese stuffed shells(makes 4 servings)
directions: Cook shells; rinse in cool water and drain well.

title: creamy brussels sprouts
directions: Cook Brussels sprouts according to package directions. Combine soup, milk and cheese.
Mix together Brussels sprouts and soup mixture.
Grease a 2-quart casserole dish or use nonstick spray.
Bake casserole in an oven preheated to 325° for 30 minutes.

title: chicken, broccoli, pineapple salad
directions: Drain juice from pineapple, reserving 1/2 cup juice.
In large bowl, lightly toss all ingredients and reserved juice.
Cover. Refrigerate overnight to blend flavors.

title: spinach quiche
directions: Line
pie
pan
with pie shell.
Prick sides and bottom. Bake at
for
10 to 12 minutes.
Cook spinach and drain. Cut cheese in 1/2-inch slices.
Mix with flour.
Beat eggs and whip cream;
add
salt
and pepper.
Mix and put in pie shell. Bake 1 hour at 350°.

title: corn pudding
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Combine corn, butter, eggs, flour, salt, pepper and sugar (if desired) in a large bowl and mix thoroughly. Turn corn mixture into a prepared casserole.
Cover lightly with a lid or foil and bake for 1 hour and 15 minutes or until set in the center and crust forms around the edge.
Makes 6 servings.

title: food for the angels
directions: Beat egg whites, then gradually add sugar and vanilla until stiff.
Fold in crackers and nuts.
Place in 10 x 14-inch buttered pan.
Bake 25 to 30 minutes at 350°.
Cool.
Whip the whipping cream and spread on top.
Sprinkle on coconut, if desired.

title: english pea salad
directions: Heat peas almost to boiling point.
Drain.
Add the cheese and cool.
Add all the other chopped ingredients, that have been chopped, and mix into the peas.
Add enough mayonnaise to stir together.
Cool and serve.

title: russian tea
directions: Mix
all ingredients.
Use two rounded teaspoonfuls per large cup hot water.

title: lasagna roll-ups
directions: Cook spinach according to box directions. Squeeze out excess water after cooled. Add Ricotta cheese, garlic, 1 cup Mozzarella, eggs and Parmesan. Mix well. Place large spoonful of mixture on one end of a cooked noodle and sprinkle rest of noodle with Mozzarella cheese. Roll up with spinach mixture in center. Place on side in sprayed 9 x 13 dish. Cover with spaghetti sauce. Cover and bake 30 to 40 minutes at 350°. Uncover and cook an additional 10 minutes.

title: vegetable soup with lentils
directions: Bring to a boil in large saucepan lentils and vegetable broth. Add remaining ingredients.
Reduce heat, cover and simmer 1 hour. Remove bay leaves and puree half of mixture and add to soup.

title: blueberry muffins
directions: Cut first 3 ingredients together until coarse like meal.
Add milk, egg and flavoring to flour mixture; mix.
Fold in blueberries.
Fill greased muffin tin 3/4 full.
Bake at 425° for 15 to 20 minutes, or until brown.
Makes 12 muffins.

title: spiced apple muffins
directions: Mix together sugar, cinnamon, ginger and anise seeds. In a large bowl, mix flour, baking powder, sugar mixture, salt, milk and applesauce. Do not overbeat. Stir in diced apples. Spoon batter into 12 greased muffin cups. Bake at 400°F (205°C) for 20 to 25 minutes or until tops spring back when lightly touched. Serve after muffins have cooled a bit, about 30 minutes.

title: corn bread
directions: Mix corn meal, salt and baking powder.
Then add milk, oil, honey and egg.
Put in muffin tin.
Bake at 425° for 20 to 25 minutes.

title: greek salad
directions: This requires a basic oil and vinegar dressing made with half olive oil and half vinegar.
You can buy a bottled dressing also. I prefer to buy the dressing from the Olive Garden Restaurant in Indianapolis.
Their dressing is great.

title: oysterette snack mix
directions: Mix thoroughly the first 5 ingredients.
Put small amount of crackers and oil mixture in a brown paper bag and shake. Continue until all crackers are coated.
Store in airtight container.
Enjoy!!

title: frozen peach salad
directions: Mash pecans and stir in marshmallows.
Combine sugar, 1/4 cup peach juice and cream cheese.
Beat until fluffy.
Add peaches and marshmallows.
Whip milk and add to peach mixture.
Add pecans and lemon juice.
Freeze in individual molds or in an 8 x 12-inch dish.
Serves 8 to 10.

title: italian meat loaf
directions: Combine ingredients, except cheese, and mix well. Shape and place into shallow	baking dish. Bake at 350° for about 45 minutes.
Add overlapping cheese for last few minutes to melt.

title: evergreen punch
directions: Bring sugar and water to boil in heavy pan.
Boil until sugar dissolves.
Add Kool-Aid and pineapple juice after removing sugar water
from heat.
Freeze this mixture.
Set it out to begin thawing 4 to 6 hours
before serving.
Put in punch bowl and pour ginger ale over the punch before serving.
Makes 16 to 20 servings.

title: water chestnuts with bacon
directions: Slice package of bacon in half.
Wrap individual chestnuts with 1/2 strip of bacon and gently push in toothpick.
Cook in a 350° oven for 1/2 hour.
Mix remaining ingredients and pour over chestnuts.
Return to oven for another 1/2 hour.

title: dinner rolls
directions: Place dough on lightly floured surface.
Divide dough into 12 equal pieces.
Shape each piece into ball.
Place on greased cookie sheet.
Cover and let rise about 30 minutes or until doubled (dough is ready if indentation remains when touched). Heat oven to 350°.
Bake for 20 to 30 minutes or until golden brown.
Makes 12 rolls.

title: miss veda's cabbage slaw
directions: Layer cabbage, onion and bell pepper.
Sprinkle sugar over that and let it set.
Mix vinegar, celery seed, salt and mustard and bring to a boil.
When it comes to a boil over (boils to the top of the boiler) then
pour over the cabbage mixture.
Heat oil and pour over all; mix well.
This will keep for several days in the refrigerator.

title: impossible mexican pie
directions: Heat oven to 400°.
Lightly grease 10-inch pie plate.
Cook and stir ground beef and onion until brown.
Drain.
Stir in taco seasoning mix.
Spread beef mixture in pie plate.
Sprinkle with chilies and cheese.
Beat remaining ingredients until smooth (15 seconds in blender on high or 1 minute with hand beater).
Pour into pie plate.
Bake until golden brown and knife inserted in center comes out clean, 25 to 30 minutes.
Let stand 5 minutes before cutting.
Garnish with peppers and cheese, if desired.

title: payday bars
directions: Stir until boiling the sugar and syrup.
Add peanut butter; stir until melted.
Add peanuts.
Pour over the cereal.
Stir gently.
Spread onto greased cookie pan.
Let set before cutting.

title: green goddess dressing
directions: In a medium bowl, stir together all ingredients until well combined. Cover and chill if not using immediately.

title: ranch style oyster crackers
directions: Preheat oven to 275°.
In a mixing bowl, whisk together vegetable oil, Ranch-style dressing mix, dill weed, lemon pepper and garlic powder.
Pour this mixture over the crackers in a medium bowl.
Stir until crackers are coated.
Arrange the crackers on a large baking sheet.
Bake in the preheated oven for 15-20 minutes.

title: chocolate oatmeal cookies
directions: Mix the first four ingredients; bring to a boil.
Boil for 3 minutes.
Set aside and while hot, stir in oatmeal and vanilla. Drop quickly on wax paper or greased cookie sheet.
Do not bake.

title: herbed oven potatoes
directions: In a shallow bowl, combine the first seven ingredients.
Add potatoes, a few at a time; toss to coat.
Place in a single layer in a greased 15 X 10 X 1 baking pan.
Drizzle with remaining oil mixture.
Bake, uncovered, at 450 degrees for 50-55 minutes or until tender, stirring occasionally.
Sprinkle with parsley. 6 servings.

title: four layer dessert
directions: Cut butter into flour; add nuts.
Spread on bottom of 9 x 13-inch baking dish.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.
Cool.

title: hot mustard
directions: Mix dry mustard, sugar and vinegar.
Let mixture stand overnight. Add eggs.
Boil on low heat, stirring until thick (18 to 20 minutes).
Put in a small jar.
It makes a nice gift!

title: milky way cake
directions: Melt Milky Way bars in double boiler.
Cream 2 sticks oleo and 2 cups sugar. Add eggs, one at a time.

title: peas and almond salad
directions: Combine peas, almonds and onions.
Combine mayonnaise and curry.
Pour over the peas and toss well. Best if made the day before.

title: pronto puppies
directions: Heat cooking oil to 375°. Blend egg and milk. Stir in dry ingredients. Dip wieners in batter. Fry until golden brown (about 2 to 3 minutes on each side). To reheat, place in 400° oven about 5 minutes.

title: broccoli cheese soup
directions: Saute onion 3 minutes.
Add water and bouillon cubes and heat to boiling until cubes dissolve.
Gradually add noodles and salt. Cook 3 minutes (boiling).
Stir in broccoli and garlic powder. Cook 4 minutes more; add milk, cheese and pepper.
Cook until cheese melts.
Can be frozen for 1 month; heat in double boiler.

title: chocolate oatmeal cookies
directions: Mix sugar and cocoa together.
Then put milk and butter in and cook over medium heat until it boils.
Boil for 3 minutes.
Add peanut butter, vanilla and oats and beat well.

title: taco dip
directions: Mix the cream cheese, sour cream and taco seasoning together. Spread onto the bottom of an 11 x 13-inch pan.
Smooth taco sauce over top of mixture.
Top with lettuce, shredded cheese, tomatoes, onions, etc.

title: schubert's cranberry sherbet
directions: Cook cranberries in 2 cups water for 10 minutes, or until berries pop.
Press through sieve.
Combine cranberry juice, sugar and lemon juice; stir in milk.
Add walnuts.
Place in freezer. Freeze until firm, stirring occasionally.

title: vegetable soup with meat
directions: Add all vegetables (except tomatoes) to a large pot.
Cover with water; bring to a boil.
Cook until done.
Add meat, tomatoes, salt and pepper.
Simmer over low heat for 30 to 45 minutes.

title: impossible coconut pie
directions: Combine milk, sugar, biscuit mix, eggs, butter and vanilla in electric blender container or mixer bowl.
Blend at low speed for 3 minutes or beat at medium speed with electric mixer until well blended.
Pour into greased 9-inch pie pan.
Let stand about 5 minutes, then sprinkle with coconut.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes. Serve warm or cool.

title: pumpkin pie
directions: Grease pie pan.
Set oven to 350.
Beat all ingredients until smooth.
Pour in greased pie pan.
Bake at 350 for 55 minutes or until knife comes out clean.

title: spanish rice
directions: Mix ingredients together in 1-quart casserole.
Cover and bake at 350° for 1 hour and 15 minutes.
Stir occasionally.

title: pescatore(italian style shellfish)
directions: In a saucepan, place all ingredients except the shellfish and cook over medium heat for 4 to 5 minutes, until the pieces of onion and green pepper become tender and a saucelike consistency is reached.
Then add the shellfish and simmer for just 5 more minutes, no more or the fish will be overcooked.
Serve over pasta. Serves 4.

title: baked acorn squash
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
In a small bowl combine cracker crumbs and melted oleo.
Set aside.

title: caramel brownies(katie's favorite)
directions: Melt caramels in 1/3 cup evaporated milk.
In a large bowl combine butter, cake mix, cake flour, the other 1/3 cup evaporated milk and pecans.
Mix by hand.
Press 1/2 to 3/4 of dough into 13 x 9-inch baking dish and bake at 350° for 6 minutes.
Sprinkle chips over dough, then spread melted caramels over dough and chips.
Crumble the remaining dough over the caramel and bake at 350° for 15 minutes.
Cool before slicing.

title: five cup fruit salad
directions: Mix together and serve.
Better after chilled.

title: microwave stuffed bell peppers
directions: Cut top off of peppers and remove seeds and membranes inside. Dice the top of the peppers after removing stems.
Brown the ground turkey.
Finely chop the onion.
Mix the cooked turkey with the bread crumbs, salt, pepper, diced bell pepper, diced onion and 1/2 of the can of tomato sauce.
Stuff the peppers with the meat mixture.
Pour the rest of the tomato sauce over the stuffed peppers.
Microwave on High for about 25 to 30 minutes until thoroughly heated and cooked.

title: holiday cranberry cake
directions: Blend cake mix, cream cheese and milk.
Beat with mixer 2 minutes at medium speed.
Add eggs.
Blend and beat 2 additional minutes.
In a small bowl thoroughly combine cranberries, nuts, sugar and mace.
Fold into batter.
Pour into well-greased and floured tube or Bundt pan and bake for 1 hour or until test shows it is done.
Cool 5 minutes and remove pan and cool completely on rack.
Dust with confectioners sugar or ice lightly.
Bake at 350°.

title: chili cheese squares
directions: Spray 8 x 8-inch pan or brush with shortening.
Drain peppers and spread in bottom of pan.
Spread 1 cup of each cheese over peppers.
Drain and layer the other can of peppers over this.
Add rest of cheeses.
Beat eggs, flour and milk together.
Pour over ingredients in pan. Bake at 350° until toothpick inserted in middle comes out clean.

title: heavenly hash
directions: Let jello partly chill, then add remaining ingredients.

title: party pecan pie
directions: Mix first three ingredients together and set aside.
Mix everything together.
Pour into pan and bake at 350° for 20 minutes.
Let cool.
May be topped with Cool Whip and chocolate chips if desired.

title: mud bars
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
In a small bowl, combine flour, baking soda and salt.
Set aside.
In a large bowl, combine brown sugar, butter and vanilla; beat until creamy.
Add egg; beat well. Gradually add flour mixture; mix well.
Stir in 1 1/3 cups chocolate chips and the nuts.
Spread into foil lined 9-inch square baking pan.
Bake for 25 minutes.
Remove from oven and sprinkle remaining chips on top.
Allow to stand until chips become shiny. Spread with spatula.
Let cool.
Chill 5 to 10 minutes to set chocolate.
Cut into bars.

title: baked chicken and sauce
directions: Clean and skin chickens.
Cut onion in half and put in each chicken.
Add soup and enough water to dilute (for 2 cans soup, use approximately 1 1/2 cans water, for 4 cans soup, use approximately 2 1/2 cans water; can use thickening agent, if desired, as it dilutes).

title: cake mix cookies
directions: Mix together, roll out in balls.
Bake for 12 minutes at 350 degrees.
Makes about 3 dozen.
You can add chocolate chips, M&M's, nuts, etc.

title: fruit party dip
directions: Cream together cream cheese and Marshmallow Creme until smooth. Chill until ready to serve.
Great for entertaining!
Serve with any kind of fruit.

title: raisin bran muffins
directions: 1. Preheat oven to 400°.

title: rice pudding
directions: Bake in moderate oven to 300° to 325° for 3 hours, stirring frequently, during first hour. Cover toward the last.

title: susie's sweet mustard
directions: Mix enough vinegar with the mustard and sugar to make a smooth paste.
Stir until sugar is completely dissolved.
Delicious on ham, cold cuts and cheese.

title: cheese grits(from alabama)
directions: In saucepan heat water to boiling.
Slowly add grits, salt and pepper.
Reduce heat, cook 5 minutes.
Heat oven to 400°.
Grease a baking dish.
Beat together milk and egg.
Fold milk mixture and 1/2 cup cheese into grits.
Put into dish.
Top with remaining cheese.
Bake 25 to 30 minutes until cheese is bubbly and brown. Ready to love!
Enjoy!

title: crispix mix
directions: Melt peanut butter and chocolate chips over med. heat.
Pour over cereal in large bowl.
Gently stir, careful not to crush cereal, until all cereal is coated.
Pour powdered sugar into an oven roasting bag (or a clean shopping bag will work).
Pour coated cereal into bag of sugar.
Making sure to hold the top closed, shake bag until all cereal is coated with sugar.
Pour cereal mix onto cookie sheet to cool.
If you have any left after snacking, store in an airtight container.
Enjoy!!

title: milk chocolate bar cake
directions: Prepare cake batter as directed on package.
Pour into 3 greased and floured round cake pans.
Bake at 325 degrees for 20 to 25 minutes or until wooden tooth pick comes out clean.
Cool in pans on wire racks 10 minutes.
Remove from pans and cool completely on wire racks.

title: turtle cake
directions: Mix cake mix as directed on box. Pour 1/2 of batter in a greased and floured 9 x 12-inch pan. Bake 15 minutes at 350°.

title: southern pecan pie
directions: Line pie pan with pastry.
Set aside.
Cream butter with vanilla.
Add sugar gradually.
Mix well.
Add eggs, one at a time.
Blend in chopped pecans, syrup and salt.
Pour into pie shell and bake in preheated 450° oven for 10 minutes.
Remove from oven.
Reduce oven heat to 350°.
Arrange pecan halves on top of filling.
Return to oven and bake for 30 to 35 minutes more.

title: jenny's butter almond cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350 degrees.
Grease and flour a 9-inch cake pan.
Blend sugar and melted butter.
Beat in eggs.
Stir in almond and vanilla extracts.
Add salt, flour, and mix well.
Spread evenly in pan.
Top with almonds and sprinkle on a Tbsp. of sugar.

title: fish loaf le-cal
directions: Place gelatin in water to dissolve.
Add vinegar and other ingredients.
Place in refrigerator until firm.
Makes 2 servings.

title: mom's butterscotch pie filling
directions: Mix all dry ingredients; put into saucepan that has the beaten egg yolks and milk.
Cook until thick and add vanilla.
Enough filling for one large pie.

title: snowball
directions: Shake together all ingredients.
Freeze in pan.
Cut in squares and serve.

title: fireside coffee
directions: Combine all ingredients and store in a container.
To serve, mix 2 teaspoons in a cup of hot water.

title: vinegar pie
directions: Cream butter and sugar.
Add cinnamon, cloves, allspice, salt and flour and blend well.
Slowly stir in beaten egg, water and vinegar.
Cook, stirring constantly, in top of double boiler until thickened.
Pour into baked pie shell that has been baked 3 minutes at 350°.
Pour all ingredients in pie shell and continue baking until golden brown.

title: shrimp creole(8 servings)
directions: Saute over medium heat the green pepper, green onion, celery and garlic in margarine (6 to 8 minutes).
Add tomato paste, water, wine and seasonings.
Stir to blend.
Simmer, stirring frequently, over low heat for 10 minutes.
Add shrimp.
Cover; simmer for 20 minutes.
Serve over rice.

title: holloman's rolls
directions: Mix together flour, milk and mayonnaise.
Drop by spoonfuls into greased muffin pan.
Bake at 350° about 20 minutes.

title: basic pie recipe for all creamed pies
directions: Mix sugar, flour
and
salt;
add
milk
and egg yolks. Cook over low heat
until
thick,
then	add oleo and vanilla. Pour into baked shell.
Top with meringue and bake at 325° for 10 to 15 minutes.

title: tangy chicken
directions: Brown chicken in oleo.
Combine Heinz 57 and water.
Pour over chicken.
Cover and cook 30 to 40 minutes.
Remove cover the last 10 minutes.
Spoon sauce over chicken.

title: tortellini soup
directions: In large pan cook and stir garlic in margarine for 2 to 3 minutes in medium/high heat.
Add broth and tortellini.
Heat to boil, reduce heat, simmer 10 minutes, add spinach and tomatoes and simmer 5 minutes.
Serve topped with cheese.

title: zucchini medley
directions: Slice zucchini and onion and saute in butter until just tender.
Add Italian style tomatoes and cheese and heat until cheese melts.
If you like a little spice to your vegetables, use the salsa tomatoes.

title: cinnamon rolls
directions: Combine cake mix, flour and yeast in large bowl. Stir until well blended. Stir in hot water and knead well. Let rise until double in bulk. Cut dough in half and roll out each on a floured board into a rectangle. Spread each rectangle with2 tablespoons margarine and sprinkle with a mixture of 1/4 cup sugar and 2 teaspoons cinnamon. Sprinkle on nuts and raisins if desired. Roll up, starting at long edge, like a jelly roll. Cut into slices. Place in greased 9 x 13-inch baking pans. Let rise until doubled in size. Bake at 375° for 25 minutes until golden brown. Cool slightly.

title: pasta macaroni and cauliflower
directions: Heat oil, place cuts of cauliflower in olive oil and brown lightly.
Remove when brown, saute onion.
Add tomato sauce.
Stir and replace cauliflower into pot.
Stir and add 3 cans of water (from tomato can).
Water should cover cauliflower in pot.
Add salt and pepper and basil leaves.
Cook until cauliflower is tender, 45 minutes to 1 hour, on low heat with cover on.
Pour over pasta.

title: southern pecan pie
directions: Beat eggs until light.
Add brown sugar, gradually mixing well.
Stir in syrup, salt, vanilla, pecans and butter.
Pour into pie shell.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour or until crust is lightly brown.
Yields 6 servings.

title: burger casserole
directions: Brown hamburger; add onion and pepper.
Cook rice.
Mix meat, rice, soup, Worcestershire sauce, ketchup, salt and pepper together.
Place in a baking dish; sprinkle with cheese.
Bake 30 minutes at 400°.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: eggplant or chicken or veal parmigana
directions: Slice eggplants into 1/4 to 1/2-inch rounds.
Place in colander, salted.
Place a heavy bowl on top (you can fill it with water to make bowl heavier).
Let sit 1 to 2 hours and gently squeeze excess liquid (this step removes most of bitter taste). Add milk or water to eggs and beat in bowl.
Place bread crumbs in separate bowl.
Coat pieces (eggplant, chicken or veal cutlets) with egg mixture and then coat with bread crumbs.
When all pieces are coated, fry to light-medium golden brown, or bake on cookie sheets at 350°.

title: onion-herb hamburger buns
directions: In large bowl, dissolve yeast in the water.
Stir in next 8 ingredients and 3 cups of the flour.
Beat until smooth, about 5 minutes.
Turn dough over in a greased bowl; cover and refrigerate 24 hours to 4 days.
